e": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1477718989054362, "compression_ratio": 1.5485436893203883, "no_speech_prob": 1.4722211080439584e-12}, {"id": 19, "seek": 9560, "start": 118.3, "end": 118.6, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51500, 1033, 13, 51515], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1477718989054362, "compression_ratio": 1.5485436893203883, "no_speech_prob": 1.4722211080439584e-12}, {"id": 20, "seek": 11860, "start": 118.6, "end": 133.38, "text": " In this one, the fire never happens. The books are in pristine condition. However, the centralized catalog is completely deleted. The call numbers on the spines are randomly swapped. And the shelves are shuffled without any documentation at all.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 341, 472, 11, 264, 2610, 1128, 2314, 13, 440, 3642, 366, 294, 582, 42745, 4188, 13, 2908, 11, 264, 32395, 19746, 307, 2584, 22981, 13, 440, 818, 3547, 322, 264, 637, 1652, 366, 16979, 50011, 13, 400, 264, 24349, 366, 402, 33974, 1553, 604, 14333, 412, 439, 13, 51104], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13701422074261835, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732975902973956e-12}, {"id": 21, "seek": 11860, "start": 133.42, "end": 134.85999999999999, "text": " Just total chaos.", "tokens": [51106, 1449, 3217, 14158, 13, 51178], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13701422074261835, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732975902973956e-12}, {"id": 22, "seek": 11860, "start": 135.14, "end": 136.07999999999998, "text": " Total chaos.", "tokens": [51192, 23170, 14158, 13, 51239], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13701422074261835, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732975902973956e-12}, {"id": 23, "seek": 11860, "start": 136.32, "end": 136.57999999999998, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51251, 865, 13, 51264], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13701422074261835, "compression_ratio": 1.5080213903743316, "no_speech_prob": 1.5732975902973956e-12}, {"id": 24, "seek": 13658, "start": 136.58, "end": 155.10000000000002, "text": " And the paper points out this really chilling conclusion. From the perspective of a reader who walks through the front doors searching for a specific concept, the functional outcome of the second library is completely identical to the first.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 264, 3035, 2793, 484, 341, 534, 31047, 10063, 13, 3358, 264, 4585, 295, 257, 15149, 567, 12896, 807, 264, 1868, 8077, 10808, 337, 257, 2685, 3410, 11, 264, 11745, 9700, 295, 264, 1150, 6405, 307, 2584, 14800, 281, 264, 700, 13, 51291], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10950867809466462, "compression_ratio": 1.5252525252525253, "no_speech_prob": 1.585637328903322e-12}, {"id": 25, "seek": 13658, "start": 155.24, "end": 157.82000000000002, "text": " Wow. Yeah. You just cannot find the book.", "tokens": [51298, 3153, 13, 865, 13, 509, 445, 2644, 915, 264, 1446, 13, 51427], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10950867809466462, "compression_ratio": 1.5252525252525253, "no_speech_prob": 1.585637328903322e-12}, {"id": 26, "seek": 13658, "start": 158.0, "end": 158.9, "text": " You can't find it.", "tokens": [51436, 509, 393, 380, 915, 309, 13, 51481], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10950867809466462, "compression_ratio": 1.5252525252525253, "no_speech_prob": 1.585637328903322e-12}, {"id": 27, "seek": 15890, "start": 158.9, "end": 170.16, "text": " Right. The second library has achieved flawless preservation of its collection, but it has completely dismantled the environmental conditions under which that collection operates.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 440, 1150, 6405, 575, 11042, 45693, 27257, 295, 1080, 5765, 11, 457, 309, 575, 2584, 30506, 1493, 264, 8303, 4487, 833, 597, 300, 5765, 22577, 13, 50928], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08749266612676927, "compression_ratio": 1.6891385767790261, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813642913868446e-12}, {"id": 28, "seek": 15890, "start": 170.32, "end": 171.48000000000002, "text": " It's essentially a graveyard.", "tokens": [50936, 467, 311, 4476, 257, 42607, 13, 50994], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08749266612676927, "compression_ratio": 1.6891385767790261, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813642913868446e-12}, {"id": 29, "seek": 15890, "start": 171.48000000000002, "end": 187.54000000000002, "text": " It functions exactly like a graveyard of perfectly intact data. And that scenario perfectly illustrates the central distinction established in the text. The author is drawing this really rigid boundary between a system's capacity to remember", "tokens": [50994, 467, 6828, 2293, 411, 257, 42607, 295, 6239, 23493, 1412, 13, 400, 300, 9005, 6239, 41718, 264, 5777, 16844, 7545, 294, 264, 2487, 13, 440, 3793, 307, 6316, 341, 534, 22195, 12866, 1296, 257, 1185, 311, 6042, 281, 1604, 51797], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08749266612676927, "compression_ratio": 1.6891385767790261, "no_speech_prob": 1.9813642913868446e-12}, {"id": 30, "seek": 18754, "start": 187.54, "end": 189.92, "text": " and its capacity to recall.", "tokens": [50365, 293, 1080, 6042, 281, 9901, 13, 50484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 31, "seek": 18754, "start": 190.23999999999998, "end": 195.84, "text": " Okay. Let's unpack this. Or actually, let's unpack this because it's really the difference between existence and access.", "tokens": [50500, 1033, 13, 961, 311, 26699, 341, 13, 1610, 767, 11, 718, 311, 26699, 341, 570, 309, 311, 534, 264, 2649, 1296, 9123, 293, 2105, 13, 50780], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 32, "seek": 18754, "start": 196.07999999999998, "end": 196.23999999999998, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50792, 865, 13, 50800], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 33, "seek": 18754, "start": 196.23999999999998, "end": 203.04, "text": " In the paper's formal terminology, we are looking at preservation versus reachability.", "tokens": [50800, 682, 264, 3035, 311, 9860, 27575, 11, 321, 366, 1237, 412, 27257, 5717, 2524, 2310, 13, 51140], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 34, "seek": 18754, "start": 203.44, "end": 205.0, "text": " Right. Two very different things.", "tokens": [51160, 1779, 13, 4453, 588, 819, 721, 13, 51238], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 35, "seek": 18754, "start": 205.18, "end": 213.94, "text": " Yeah. Preservation is defined simply as the persistence of a state. Like, does the magnetic charge exist on the server? Does the ink remain on the page?", "tokens": [51247, 865, 13, 2718, 6864, 307, 7642, 2935, 382, 264, 37617, 295, 257, 1785, 13, 1743, 11, 775, 264, 12688, 4602, 2514, 322, 264, 7154, 30, 4402, 264, 11276, 6222, 322, 264, 3028, 30, 51685], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 36, "seek": 18754, "start": 214.38, "end": 215.64, "text": " Is the file saved?", "tokens": [51707, 1119, 264, 3991, 6624, 30, 51770], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15802494395862926, "compression_ratio": 1.6804511278195489, "no_speech_prob": 1.6621397183960718e-12}, {"id": 37, "seek": 21564, "start": 215.64, "end": 231.67999999999998, "text": " Exactly. Reachability, on the other hand, is the ability of a future agent like you or me to actually navigate from our current temporal and informational position to that specific piece of past content.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 35904, 2310, 11, 322, 264, 661, 1011, 11, 307, 264, 3485, 295, 257, 2027, 9461, 411, 291, 420, 385, 281, 767, 12350, 490, 527, 2190, 30881, 293, 49391, 2535, 281, 300, 2685, 2522, 295, 1791, 2701, 13, 51167], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06445967873861623, "compression_ratio": 1.4, "no_speech_prob": 1.7077959055603054e-12}, {"id": 38, "seek": 23168, "start": 231.68, "end": 237.98000000000002, "text": " And to really understand the mechanics of this, the author maps information systems using graph theory.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 281, 534, 1223, 264, 12939, 295, 341, 11, 264, 3793, 11317, 1589, 3652, 1228, 4295, 5261, 13, 50680], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12270135879516601, "compression_ratio": 1.6794871794871795, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214554434707985e-12}, {"id": 39, "seek": 23168, "start": 238.0, "end": 238.9, "text": " Oh, graph theory, yeah.", "tokens": [50681, 876, 11, 4295, 5261, 11, 1338, 13, 50726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12270135879516601, "compression_ratio": 1.6794871794871795, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214554434707985e-12}, {"id": 40, "seek": 23168, "start": 238.9, "end": 253.3, "text": " Yeah. So if you visualize an information ecosystem as this complex network, the individual pieces of data, so the research papers, the historical accounts, the websites, those function as the nodes.", "tokens": [50726, 865, 13, 407, 498, 291, 23273, 364, 1589, 11311, 382, 341, 3997, 3209, 11, 264, 2609, 3755, 295, 1412, 11, 370, 264, 2132, 10577, 11, 264, 8584, 9402, 11, 264, 12891, 11, 729, 2445, 382, 264, 13891, 13, 51446], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12270135879516601, "compression_ratio": 1.6794871794871795, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214554434707985e-12}, {"id": 41, "seek": 23168, "start": 253.68, "end": 255.52, "text": " They are the static destinations.", "tokens": [51465, 814, 366, 264, 13437, 37787, 13, 51557], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12270135879516601, "compression_ratio": 1.6794871794871795, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214554434707985e-12}, {"id": 42, "seek": 23168, "start": 255.96, "end": 257.8, "text": " Got it. The nodes are the stuff.", "tokens": [51579, 5803, 309, 13, 440, 13891, 366, 264, 1507, 13, 51671], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12270135879516601, "compression_ratio": 1.6794871794871795, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214554434707985e-12}, {"id": 43, "seek": 25780, "start": 257.8, "end": 268.34000000000003, "text": " Right. The stuff. And the mechanisms we use to move between them, like hyperlinks, search engine queries, library classification systems, or academic citations.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 440, 1507, 13, 400, 264, 15902, 321, 764, 281, 1286, 1296, 552, 11, 411, 9848, 75, 16431, 11, 3164, 2848, 24109, 11, 6405, 21538, 3652, 11, 420, 7778, 4814, 763, 13, 50892], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1223898645657212, "compression_ratio": 1.4308510638297873, "no_speech_prob": 2.020141432607092e-12}, {"id": 44, "seek": 25780, "start": 268.7, "end": 268.92, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50910, 865, 13, 50921], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1223898645657212, "compression_ratio": 1.4308510638297873, "no_speech_prob": 2.020141432607092e-12}, {"id": 45, "seek": 25780, "start": 269.04, "end": 272.62, "text": " Those operate as the edges or the transformational pathways.", "tokens": [50927, 3950, 9651, 382, 264, 8819, 420, 264, 4088, 1478, 22988, 13, 51106], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1223898645657212, "compression_ratio": 1.4308510638297873, "no_speech_prob": 2.020141432607092e-12}, {"id": 46, "seek": 25780, "start": 272.94, "end": 275.02, "text": " Right. Okay. So this makes so much sense.", "tokens": [51122, 1779, 13, 1033, 13, 407, 341, 1669, 370, 709, 2020, 13, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1223898645657212, "compression_ratio": 1.4308510638297873, "no_speech_prob": 2.020141432607092e-12}, {"id": 47, "seek": 27502, "start": 275.02, "end": 291.03999999999996, "text": " I kind of think of it like this. If I throw a perfectly labeled, hermetically sealed box into an impossibly massive, infinitely expanding warehouse, but I fail to write down the aisle and the shelf number, I've succeeded at preservation.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 733, 295, 519, 295, 309, 411, 341, 13, 759, 286, 3507, 257, 6239, 21335, 11, 720, 5537, 984, 21514, 2424, 666, 364, 38802, 3545, 5994, 11, 36227, 14702, 22244, 11, 457, 286, 3061, 281, 2464, 760, 264, 30916, 293, 264, 15222, 1230, 11, 286, 600, 20263, 412, 27257, 13, 51166], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10512412035906757, "compression_ratio": 1.5209302325581395, "no_speech_prob": 2.0270551730205977e-12}, {"id": 48, "seek": 27502, "start": 291.24, "end": 293.24, "text": " You have. The box is totally safe.", "tokens": [51176, 509, 362, 13, 440, 2424, 307, 3879, 3273, 13, 51276], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10512412035906757, "compression_ratio": 1.5209302325581395, "no_speech_prob": 2.0270551730205977e-12}, {"id": 49, "seek": 27502, "start": 293.58, "end": 296.79999999999995, "text": " The box hasn't degraded at all. It is completely safe.", "tokens": [51293, 440, 2424, 6132, 380, 24740, 292, 412, 439, 13, 467, 307, 2584, 3273, 13, 51454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10512412035906757, "compression_ratio": 1.5209302325581395, "no_speech_prob": 2.0270551730205977e-12}, {"id": 50, "seek": 29680, "start": 296.8, "end": 309.16, "text": " But it is entirely unreachable. Unless I am willing to just, you know, walk every single aisle of an infinite structure, that box functionally does not exist.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 309, 307, 7696, 517, 16226, 712, 13, 16581, 286, 669, 4950, 281, 445, 11, 291, 458, 11, 1792, 633, 2167, 30916, 295, 364, 13785, 3877, 11, 300, 2424, 2445, 379, 775, 406, 2514, 13, 50983], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06136519472363969, "compression_ratio": 1.4751131221719458, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779864615163674e-12}, {"id": 51, "seek": 29680, "start": 309.3, "end": 318.66, "text": " What's fascinating here is that historically our foundational theories of information have had a massive blind spot regarding that exact warehouse aisle.", "tokens": [50990, 708, 311, 10343, 510, 307, 300, 16180, 527, 32195, 13667, 295, 1589, 362, 632, 257, 5994, 6865, 4008, 8595, 300, 1900, 22244, 30916, 13, 51458], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06136519472363969, "compression_ratio": 1.4751131221719458, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779864615163674e-12}, {"id": 52, "seek": 29680, "start": 318.76, "end": 319.26, "text": " Like, really?", "tokens": [51463, 1743, 11, 534, 30, 51488], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06136519472363969, "compression_ratio": 1.4751131221719458, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779864615163674e-12}, {"id": 53, "seek": 31926, "start": 319.26, "end": 334.21999999999997, "text": " Yeah. Take Claude Shannon's 1948 mathematical theory of communication, for example. It was built around signal fidelity. You know, ensuring a message sent from point A arrived at point B without being corrupted by noise.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 13, 3664, 12947, 2303, 28974, 311, 38833, 18894, 5261, 295, 6101, 11, 337, 1365, 13, 467, 390, 3094, 926, 6358, 46404, 13, 509, 458, 11, 16882, 257, 3636, 2279, 490, 935, 316, 6678, 412, 935, 363, 1553, 885, 39480, 538, 5658, 13, 51113], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14516048666871625, "compression_ratio": 1.411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 1.734952893156505e-12}, {"id": 54, "seek": 31926, "start": 334.3, "end": 335.32, "text": " Right. Very structural.", "tokens": [51117, 1779, 13, 4372, 15067, 13, 51168], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14516048666871625, "compression_ratio": 1.411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 1.734952893156505e-12}, {"id": 55, "seek": 31926, "start": 335.59999999999997, "end": 343.2, "text": " Yes. And then Lushana Fulriti's later philosophy of information focused heavily on semantic value and truthfulness.", "tokens": [51182, 1079, 13, 400, 550, 441, 1498, 2095, 479, 425, 3210, 72, 311, 1780, 10675, 295, 1589, 5178, 10950, 322, 47982, 2158, 293, 3494, 26872, 13, 51562], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14516048666871625, "compression_ratio": 1.411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 1.734952893156505e-12}, {"id": 56, "seek": 34320, "start": 343.2, "end": 349.46, "text": " But both of those paradigms assume the receiver already knows what channel to tune into.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 1293, 295, 729, 13480, 328, 2592, 6552, 264, 20086, 1217, 3255, 437, 2269, 281, 10864, 666, 13, 50678], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09993322035845588, "compression_ratio": 1.5753968253968254, "no_speech_prob": 1.890815629068676e-12}, {"id": 57, "seek": 34320, "start": 349.65999999999997, "end": 352.59999999999997, "text": " Oh, interesting. They assume the data is already right in front of you.", "tokens": [50688, 876, 11, 1880, 13, 814, 6552, 264, 1412, 307, 1217, 558, 294, 1868, 295, 291, 13, 50835], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09993322035845588, "compression_ratio": 1.5753968253968254, "no_speech_prob": 1.890815629068676e-12}, {"id": 58, "seek": 34320, "start": 352.64, "end": 363.44, "text": " Exactly. They largely ignored the temporal navigational dimension of actually finding the signal in a sea of noise decades after it was original broadcast.", "tokens": [50837, 7587, 13, 814, 11611, 19735, 264, 30881, 7407, 1478, 10139, 295, 767, 5006, 264, 6358, 294, 257, 4158, 295, 5658, 7878, 934, 309, 390, 3380, 9975, 13, 51377], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09993322035845588, "compression_ratio": 1.5753968253968254, "no_speech_prob": 1.890815629068676e-12}, {"id": 59, "seek": 34320, "start": 364.03999999999996, "end": 369.65999999999997, "text": " That structural blind spot explains so much about how we build technology today.", "tokens": [51407, 663, 15067, 6865, 4008, 13948, 370, 709, 466, 577, 321, 1322, 2899, 965, 13, 51688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09993322035845588, "compression_ratio": 1.5753968253968254, "no_speech_prob": 1.890815629068676e-12}, {"id": 60, "seek": 36966, "start": 369.66, "end": 375.82000000000005, "text": " I mean, preservation and reachability are handled by entirely divergent engineering disciplines.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 27257, 293, 2524, 2310, 366, 18033, 538, 7696, 18558, 6930, 7043, 21919, 13, 50673], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13554900884628296, "compression_ratio": 1.5967078189300412, "no_speech_prob": 1.943045984525993e-12}, {"id": 61, "seek": 36966, "start": 376.20000000000005, "end": 380.36, "text": " Right. The architectural separation between the two is just staggering.", "tokens": [50692, 1779, 13, 440, 26621, 14634, 1296, 264, 732, 307, 445, 42974, 13, 50900], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13554900884628296, "compression_ratio": 1.5967078189300412, "no_speech_prob": 1.943045984525993e-12}, {"id": 62, "seek": 36966, "start": 381.36, "end": 392.22, "text": " The engineers developing RAID storage arrays, redundant cloud architectures, digital preservation standards, they're focused exclusively on node persistence.", "tokens": [50950, 440, 11955, 6416, 14626, 2777, 6725, 41011, 11, 40997, 4588, 6331, 1303, 11, 4562, 27257, 7787, 11, 436, 434, 5178, 20638, 322, 9984, 37617, 13, 51493], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13554900884628296, "compression_ratio": 1.5967078189300412, "no_speech_prob": 1.943045984525993e-12}, {"id": 63, "seek": 36966, "start": 392.70000000000005, "end": 394.3, "text": " They lock down the data.", "tokens": [51517, 814, 4017, 760, 264, 1412, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13554900884628296, "compression_ratio": 1.5967078189300412, "no_speech_prob": 1.943045984525993e-12}, {"id": 64, "seek": 36966, "start": 394.52000000000004, "end": 395.84000000000003, "text": " They just want to keep the box safe.", "tokens": [51608, 814, 445, 528, 281, 1066, 264, 2424, 3273, 13, 51674], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13554900884628296, "compression_ratio": 1.5967078189300412, "no_speech_prob": 1.943045984525993e-12}, {"id": 65, "seek": 39584, "start": 395.84, "end": 407.91999999999996, "text": " Exactly. Meanwhile, a completely separate cohort of engineers, the ones building search algorithms, indexing bots, hyperlink protocols, they are tasked with reachability.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 13879, 11, 257, 2584, 4994, 28902, 295, 11955, 11, 264, 2306, 2390, 3164, 14642, 11, 8186, 278, 35410, 11, 9848, 22473, 20618, 11, 436, 366, 38621, 365, 2524, 2310, 13, 50969], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0920649494033262, "compression_ratio": 1.652014652014652, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426277655787191e-12}, {"id": 66, "seek": 39584, "start": 408.4, "end": 409.4, "text": " They build the edges.", "tokens": [50993, 814, 1322, 264, 8819, 13, 51043], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0920649494033262, "compression_ratio": 1.652014652014652, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426277655787191e-12}, {"id": 67, "seek": 39584, "start": 409.65999999999997, "end": 425.34, "text": " And because these two mechanisms operate completely independently, driven by totally different corporate incentives and technical constraints, the navigational layer can suffer a catastrophic collapse while the storage layer remains completely uncompromised.", "tokens": [51056, 400, 570, 613, 732, 15902, 9651, 2584, 21761, 11, 9555, 538, 3879, 819, 10896, 23374, 293, 6191, 18491, 11, 264, 7407, 1478, 4583, 393, 9753, 257, 34915, 15584, 1339, 264, 6725, 4583, 7023, 2584, 8585, 28722, 2640, 13, 51840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0920649494033262, "compression_ratio": 1.652014652014652, "no_speech_prob": 1.6426277655787191e-12}, {"id": 68, "seek": 42534, "start": 425.34, "end": 431.11999999999995, "text": " Which leads right into how this actually happens, because the paper doesn't just leave this as a theoretical framework.", "tokens": [50365, 3013, 6689, 558, 666, 577, 341, 767, 2314, 11, 570, 264, 3035, 1177, 380, 445, 1856, 341, 382, 257, 20864, 8388, 13, 50654], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14629231691360473, "compression_ratio": 1.5477178423236515, "no_speech_prob": 2.2103601501205494e-12}, {"id": 69, "seek": 42534, "start": 431.61999999999995, "end": 438.41999999999996, "text": " The author outlines a taxonomy of how this breakdown manifests in our daily digital environments.", "tokens": [50679, 440, 3793, 40125, 257, 3366, 23423, 295, 577, 341, 18188, 50252, 294, 527, 5212, 4562, 12388, 13, 51019], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14629231691360473, "compression_ratio": 1.5477178423236515, "no_speech_prob": 2.2103601501205494e-12}, {"id": 70, "seek": 42534, "start": 438.76, "end": 442.34, "text": " Yeah, the five failure modes. This part was wild.", "tokens": [51036, 865, 11, 264, 1732, 7763, 14068, 13, 639, 644, 390, 4868, 13, 51215], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14629231691360473, "compression_ratio": 1.5477178423236515, "no_speech_prob": 2.2103601501205494e-12}, {"id": 71, "seek": 42534, "start": 442.9, "end": 449.88, "text": " We see systems successfully hoard the data, but completely fail at reachability in several distinct ways.", "tokens": [51243, 492, 536, 3652, 10727, 45940, 264, 1412, 11, 457, 2584, 3061, 412, 2524, 2310, 294, 2940, 10644, 2098, 13, 51592], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14629231691360473, "compression_ratio": 1.5477178423236515, "no_speech_prob": 2.2103601501205494e-12}, {"id": 72, "seek": 44988, "start": 449.88, "end": 454.44, "text": " A prime example is what the text identifies as namespace laundering.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 5835, 1365, 307, 437, 264, 2487, 34597, 382, 5288, 17940, 17245, 1794, 13, 50593], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20832233958774143, "compression_ratio": 1.5528846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.361765514061198e-12}, {"id": 73, "seek": 44988, "start": 454.54, "end": 455.62, "text": " Namespace laundering.", "tokens": [50598, 426, 1632, 17940, 17245, 1794, 13, 50652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20832233958774143, "compression_ratio": 1.5528846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.361765514061198e-12}, {"id": 74, "seek": 44988, "start": 456.24, "end": 458.08, "text": " Which happens a lot on social media, right?", "tokens": [50683, 3013, 2314, 257, 688, 322, 2093, 3021, 11, 558, 30, 50775], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20832233958774143, "compression_ratio": 1.5528846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.361765514061198e-12}, {"id": 75, "seek": 44988, "start": 458.08, "end": 461.2, "text": " But constantly on large social infrastructure.", "tokens": [50775, 583, 6460, 322, 2416, 2093, 6896, 13, 50931], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20832233958774143, "compression_ratio": 1.5528846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.361765514061198e-12}, {"id": 76, "seek": 44988, "start": 462.0, "end": 471.52, "text": " So, consider a massive digital community aggregated under a specific conceptual banner, perhaps a forum dedicated to historical architecture.", "tokens": [50971, 407, 11, 1949, 257, 5994, 4562, 1768, 16743, 770, 833, 257, 2685, 24106, 24348, 11, 4317, 257, 17542, 8374, 281, 8584, 9482, 13, 51447], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20832233958774143, "compression_ratio": 1.5528846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.361765514061198e-12}, {"id": 77, "seek": 47152, "start": 471.52, "end": 477.58, "text": " Over the years, it accumulates a dense audience and a deep archive of discourse.", "tokens": [50365, 4886, 264, 924, 11, 309, 12989, 26192, 257, 18011, 4034, 293, 257, 2452, 23507, 295, 23938, 13, 50668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14117802394909806, "compression_ratio": 1.5860655737704918, "no_speech_prob": 2.1761041319595664e-12}, {"id": 78, "seek": 47152, "start": 477.65999999999997, "end": 479.18, "text": " Oh, lots of valuable content.", "tokens": [50672, 876, 11, 3195, 295, 8263, 2701, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14117802394909806, "compression_ratio": 1.5860655737704918, "no_speech_prob": 2.1761041319595664e-12}, {"id": 79, "seek": 47152, "start": 479.29999999999995, "end": 480.84, "text": " Tons of infrastructural value.", "tokens": [50754, 314, 892, 295, 6534, 1757, 1807, 2158, 13, 50831], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14117802394909806, "compression_ratio": 1.5860655737704918, "no_speech_prob": 2.1761041319595664e-12}, {"id": 80, "seek": 47152, "start": 481.4, "end": 490.59999999999997, "text": " But eventually, the administrators altered the title and stated purpose of the space to something entirely unrelated, usually to monetize the traffic.", "tokens": [50859, 583, 4728, 11, 264, 27754, 28783, 264, 4876, 293, 11323, 4334, 295, 264, 1901, 281, 746, 7696, 38967, 11, 2673, 281, 15556, 1125, 264, 6419, 13, 51319], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14117802394909806, "compression_ratio": 1.5860655737704918, "no_speech_prob": 2.1761041319595664e-12}, {"id": 81, "seek": 47152, "start": 490.79999999999995, "end": 495.41999999999996, "text": " Oh, right. Like when a niche meme page suddenly turns into a crypto promotion board overnight.", "tokens": [51329, 876, 11, 558, 13, 1743, 562, 257, 19956, 21701, 3028, 5800, 4523, 666, 257, 17240, 15783, 3150, 13935, 13, 51560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14117802394909806, "compression_ratio": 1.5860655737704918, "no_speech_prob": 2.1761041319595664e-12}, {"id": 82, "seek": 49542, "start": 495.42, "end": 506.82, "text": " Exactly. The user base remains physically subscribed, the older posts might even technically still exist deep in the feed, but the original semantic identity is quietly overwritten.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 440, 4195, 3096, 7023, 9762, 16665, 11, 264, 4906, 12300, 1062, 754, 12120, 920, 2514, 2452, 294, 264, 3154, 11, 457, 264, 3380, 47982, 6575, 307, 19141, 670, 26859, 13, 50935], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1272372257562331, "compression_ratio": 1.6122448979591837, "no_speech_prob": 1.950642121786861e-12}, {"id": 83, "seek": 49542, "start": 507.34000000000003, "end": 515.86, "text": " So, the path from the present to the community's actual history passes through a signpost that points to a completely different reality.", "tokens": [50961, 407, 11, 264, 3100, 490, 264, 1974, 281, 264, 1768, 311, 3539, 2503, 11335, 807, 257, 1465, 23744, 300, 2793, 281, 257, 2584, 819, 4103, 13, 51387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1272372257562331, "compression_ratio": 1.6122448979591837, "no_speech_prob": 1.950642121786861e-12}, {"id": 84, "seek": 49542, "start": 516.36, "end": 521.48, "text": " Precisely. The node is essentially corrupted at the level of its identifier.", "tokens": [51412, 48746, 736, 13, 440, 9984, 307, 4476, 39480, 412, 264, 1496, 295, 1080, 45690, 13, 51668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1272372257562331, "compression_ratio": 1.6122448979591837, "no_speech_prob": 1.950642121786861e-12}, {"id": 85, "seek": 52148, "start": 521.48, "end": 526.44, "text": " The prior meaning is not explicitly deleted, it is paved over.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4059, 3620, 307, 406, 20803, 22981, 11, 309, 307, 42989, 670, 13, 50613], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16323505865560994, "compression_ratio": 1.4814814814814814, "no_speech_prob": 2.3070436620115098e-12}, {"id": 86, "seek": 52148, "start": 527.14, "end": 532.82, "text": " A new user joining post-transition inherits a completely distorted map of the network.", "tokens": [50648, 316, 777, 4195, 5549, 2183, 12, 24999, 849, 9484, 1208, 257, 2584, 33431, 4471, 295, 264, 3209, 13, 50932], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16323505865560994, "compression_ratio": 1.4814814814814814, "no_speech_prob": 2.3070436620115098e-12}, {"id": 87, "seek": 52148, "start": 533.2, "end": 533.26, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [50951, 3153, 13, 50954], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16323505865560994, "compression_ratio": 1.4814814814814814, "no_speech_prob": 2.3070436620115098e-12}, {"id": 88, "seek": 52148, "start": 533.44, "end": 541.72, "text": " And moving from social networks to structured knowledge bases, the author identifies a different mechanism, encyclopedic consolidation.", "tokens": [50963, 400, 2684, 490, 2093, 9590, 281, 18519, 3601, 17949, 11, 264, 3793, 34597, 257, 819, 7513, 11, 465, 34080, 27277, 299, 39114, 13, 51377], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16323505865560994, "compression_ratio": 1.4814814814814814, "no_speech_prob": 2.3070436620115098e-12}, {"id": 89, "seek": 52148, "start": 542.1, "end": 543.5, "text": " Right. The Wikipedia example.", "tokens": [51396, 1779, 13, 440, 28999, 1365, 13, 51466], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16323505865560994, "compression_ratio": 1.4814814814814814, "no_speech_prob": 2.3070436620115098e-12}, {"id": 90, "seek": 54350, "start": 543.5, "end": 554.34, "text": " Yeah, this is the practice of merging distinct articles or viewpoints into a single canonical entry, a process heavily utilized by platforms like Wikipedia.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 341, 307, 264, 3124, 295, 44559, 10644, 11290, 420, 1910, 20552, 666, 257, 2167, 46491, 8729, 11, 257, 1399, 10950, 28158, 538, 9473, 411, 28999, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09439616906838338, "compression_ratio": 1.46524064171123, "no_speech_prob": 1.9810646179063696e-12}, {"id": 91, "seek": 54350, "start": 554.72, "end": 561.38, "text": " Okay, wait, wait. Isn't merging Wikipedia articles a good thing? Doesn't that clean up the clutter and help the user?", "tokens": [50926, 1033, 11, 1699, 11, 1699, 13, 6998, 380, 44559, 28999, 11290, 257, 665, 551, 30, 12955, 380, 300, 2541, 493, 264, 40614, 293, 854, 264, 4195, 30, 51259], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09439616906838338, "compression_ratio": 1.46524064171123, "no_speech_prob": 1.9810646179063696e-12}, {"id": 92, "seek": 56138, "start": 561.38, "end": 571.6, "text": " From an architectural standpoint, I'd think removing redundancy and resolving conflicting layouts accelerates your ability to find the currently accepted consensus.", "tokens": [50365, 3358, 364, 26621, 15827, 11, 286, 1116, 519, 12720, 27830, 6717, 293, 49940, 43784, 46100, 10172, 1024, 428, 3485, 281, 915, 264, 4362, 9035, 19115, 13, 50876], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11693609677828275, "compression_ratio": 1.5269709543568464, "no_speech_prob": 1.6747695895033554e-12}, {"id": 93, "seek": 56138, "start": 571.6, "end": 575.48, "text": " Well, it undeniably optimizes the network for the present moment.", "tokens": [50876, 1042, 11, 309, 674, 15711, 1188, 5028, 5660, 264, 3209, 337, 264, 1974, 1623, 13, 51070], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11693609677828275, "compression_ratio": 1.5269709543568464, "no_speech_prob": 1.6747695895033554e-12}, {"id": 94, "seek": 56138, "start": 576.1, "end": 581.4399999999999, "text": " Consolidation clears away the navigational friction for anyone seeking the current canonical view.", "tokens": [51101, 6923, 401, 327, 399, 47033, 1314, 264, 7407, 1478, 17710, 337, 2878, 11670, 264, 2190, 46491, 1910, 13, 51368], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11693609677828275, "compression_ratio": 1.5269709543568464, "no_speech_prob": 1.6747695895033554e-12}, {"id": 95, "seek": 56138, "start": 581.54, "end": 582.82, "text": " Right, which is usually what you want.", "tokens": [51373, 1779, 11, 597, 307, 2673, 437, 291, 528, 13, 51437], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11693609677828275, "compression_ratio": 1.5269709543568464, "no_speech_prob": 1.6747695895033554e-12}, {"id": 96, "seek": 58282, "start": 582.82, "end": 586.94, "text": " Yes, but the author terms this path compression with loss.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 11, 457, 264, 3793, 2115, 341, 3100, 19355, 365, 4470, 13, 50571], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11552469229992525, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.665722677319682e-12}, {"id": 97, "seek": 58282, "start": 587.6600000000001, "end": 593.12, "text": " The minority perspectives, the nuanced debates, and the prior consensus states are not erased.", "tokens": [50607, 440, 16166, 16766, 11, 264, 45115, 24203, 11, 293, 264, 4059, 19115, 4368, 366, 406, 38359, 13, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11552469229992525, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.665722677319682e-12}, {"id": 98, "seek": 58282, "start": 593.58, "end": 601.1600000000001, "text": " They are perfectly preserved within the backend database, specifically within the edit histories of the consolidated page.", "tokens": [50903, 814, 366, 6239, 22242, 1951, 264, 38087, 8149, 11, 4682, 1951, 264, 8129, 30631, 295, 264, 49008, 3028, 13, 51282], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11552469229992525, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.665722677319682e-12}, {"id": 99, "seek": 58282, "start": 601.3000000000001, "end": 605.44, "text": " Oh, I see. They're still there, but the mechanism of finding them is broken.", "tokens": [51289, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 814, 434, 920, 456, 11, 457, 264, 7513, 295, 5006, 552, 307, 5463, 13, 51496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11552469229992525, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.665722677319682e-12}, {"id": 100, "seek": 58282, "start": 605.6800000000001, "end": 606.24, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51508, 7587, 13, 51536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11552469229992525, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.665722677319682e-12}, {"id": 101, "seek": 60624, "start": 606.24, "end": 611.58, "text": " Google's web crawlers are optimized to index the front-facing canonical page.", "tokens": [50365, 3329, 311, 3670, 13999, 11977, 366, 26941, 281, 8186, 264, 1868, 12, 44046, 46491, 3028, 13, 50632], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15330021381378173, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579732800367733e-12}, {"id": 102, "seek": 60624, "start": 611.58, "end": 622.82, "text": " They intentionally avoid crawling deep, dynamic database queries like historical edit logs to save processing power and avoid duplicate content penalties.", "tokens": [50632, 814, 22062, 5042, 32979, 2452, 11, 8546, 8149, 24109, 411, 8584, 8129, 20820, 281, 3155, 9007, 1347, 293, 5042, 23976, 2701, 35389, 13, 51194], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15330021381378173, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579732800367733e-12}, {"id": 103, "seek": 60624, "start": 623.2, "end": 627.64, "text": " So the external indexing algorithms actively ignore the past.", "tokens": [51213, 407, 264, 8320, 8186, 278, 14642, 13022, 11200, 264, 1791, 13, 51435], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15330021381378173, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579732800367733e-12}, {"id": 104, "seek": 60624, "start": 627.82, "end": 628.1800000000001, "text": " They do.", "tokens": [51444, 814, 360, 13, 51462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15330021381378173, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579732800367733e-12}, {"id": 105, "seek": 60624, "start": 628.54, "end": 634.28, "text": " A general user arriving via a standard search engine encounters only the polished present.", "tokens": [51480, 316, 2674, 4195, 22436, 5766, 257, 3832, 3164, 2848, 26310, 787, 264, 29079, 1974, 13, 51767], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15330021381378173, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579732800367733e-12}, {"id": 106, "seek": 63428, "start": 634.28, "end": 647.76, "text": " The historical states are flawlessly preserved on Wikipedia servers, yet they remain fundamentally unreachable to anyone who lacks the specialized technical intent to manually excavate that backend architecture.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 8584, 4368, 366, 13717, 12048, 22242, 322, 28999, 15909, 11, 1939, 436, 6222, 17879, 517, 16226, 712, 281, 2878, 567, 31132, 264, 19813, 6191, 8446, 281, 16945, 24933, 19083, 300, 38087, 9482, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 107, "seek": 63428, "start": 648.12, "end": 653.12, "text": " So it's an environment that sanitizes the present by burying the pathways to the past.", "tokens": [51057, 407, 309, 311, 364, 2823, 300, 24533, 5660, 264, 1974, 538, 2779, 1840, 264, 22988, 281, 264, 1791, 13, 51307], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 108, "seek": 63428, "start": 653.48, "end": 654.4399999999999, "text": " Beautifully put.", "tokens": [51325, 10584, 15386, 829, 13, 51373], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 109, "seek": 63428, "start": 654.64, "end": 661.1999999999999, "text": " And that structural reality segues perfectly into another pervasive breakdown the author highlights, which is access restriction.", "tokens": [51383, 400, 300, 15067, 4103, 3896, 1247, 6239, 666, 1071, 680, 39211, 18188, 264, 3793, 14254, 11, 597, 307, 2105, 29529, 13, 51711], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 110, "seek": 63428, "start": 661.62, "end": 662.28, "text": " Ah, yeah.", "tokens": [51732, 2438, 11, 1338, 13, 51765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 111, "seek": 63428, "start": 662.72, "end": 663.4599999999999, "text": " The paywalls.", "tokens": [51787, 440, 1689, 16256, 82, 13, 51824], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 112, "seek": 63428, "start": 663.4599999999999, "end": 663.8399999999999, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51824, 1079, 13, 51843], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14640714554559617, "compression_ratio": 1.6013513513513513, "no_speech_prob": 1.7693256798914647e-12}, {"id": 113, "seek": 66384, "start": 663.84, "end": 669.0400000000001, "text": " This is where the tension between nodes and edges becomes highly institutionalized.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 307, 689, 264, 8980, 1296, 13891, 293, 8819, 3643, 5405, 18391, 1602, 13, 50625], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14722795919938522, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 2.307413158111893e-12}, {"id": 114, "seek": 66384, "start": 669.5, "end": 677.5600000000001, "text": " The classic example here is the academic publishing industry and the use of DOIs, or digital object identifier.", "tokens": [50648, 440, 7230, 1365, 510, 307, 264, 7778, 17832, 3518, 293, 264, 764, 295, 10699, 6802, 11, 420, 4562, 2657, 45690, 13, 51051], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14722795919938522, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 2.307413158111893e-12}, {"id": 115, "seek": 66384, "start": 677.74, "end": 677.9200000000001, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51060, 1779, 13, 51069], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14722795919938522, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 2.307413158111893e-12}, {"id": 116, "seek": 66384, "start": 678.0, "end": 682.2800000000001, "text": " The DOI system is actually a massive triumph of preservation engineering.", "tokens": [51073, 440, 10699, 40, 1185, 307, 767, 257, 5994, 29156, 295, 27257, 7043, 13, 51287], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14722795919938522, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 2.307413158111893e-12}, {"id": 117, "seek": 66384, "start": 682.48, "end": 691.82, "text": " It guarantees that even if a journal changes its domain or migrates its servers, the identifier consistently resolves to the correct document.", "tokens": [51297, 467, 32567, 300, 754, 498, 257, 6708, 2962, 1080, 9274, 420, 6186, 12507, 1080, 15909, 11, 264, 45690, 14961, 7923, 977, 281, 264, 3006, 4166, 13, 51764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14722795919938522, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 2.307413158111893e-12}, {"id": 118, "seek": 69182, "start": 691.82, "end": 693.7600000000001, "text": " The node is totally secure.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 9984, 307, 3879, 7144, 13, 50462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2889236191571769, "compression_ratio": 1.4382022471910112, "no_speech_prob": 2.159372290352901e-12}, {"id": 119, "seek": 69182, "start": 693.7600000000001, "end": 693.96, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50462, 865, 13, 50472], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2889236191571769, "compression_ratio": 1.4382022471910112, "no_speech_prob": 2.159372290352901e-12}, {"id": 120, "seek": 69182, "start": 693.96, "end": 697.94, "text": " And the structural edge pointing to it is permanently maintained.", "tokens": [50472, 400, 264, 15067, 4691, 12166, 281, 309, 307, 24042, 17578, 13, 50671], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2889236191571769, "compression_ratio": 1.4382022471910112, "no_speech_prob": 2.159372290352901e-12}, {"id": 121, "seek": 69182, "start": 698.48, "end": 709.1800000000001, "text": " Yet, when a user attempts to traverse that edge, they're intercepted by a hard systemic boundary like a paywall or an institutional authentication protocol.", "tokens": [50698, 10890, 11, 562, 257, 4195, 15257, 281, 45674, 300, 4691, 11, 436, 434, 24700, 292, 538, 257, 1152, 23789, 12866, 411, 257, 1689, 16256, 420, 364, 18391, 26643, 10336, 13, 51233], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2889236191571769, "compression_ratio": 1.4382022471910112, "no_speech_prob": 2.159372290352901e-12}, {"id": 122, "seek": 70918, "start": 709.18, "end": 718.16, "text": " The link functions flawlessly, but it is gated by commercial or institutional conditions entirely divorced from the information itself.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 2113, 6828, 13717, 12048, 11, 457, 309, 307, 290, 770, 538, 6841, 420, 18391, 4487, 7696, 27670, 490, 264, 1589, 2564, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12063921292622884, "compression_ratio": 1.5228426395939085, "no_speech_prob": 2.529247427815462e-12}, {"id": 123, "seek": 70918, "start": 718.8399999999999, "end": 729.68, "text": " For an independent researcher or a citizen scientist without a massive university endowment behind them, the text is undeniably preserved, but entirely unreachable.", "tokens": [50848, 1171, 364, 6695, 21751, 420, 257, 13326, 12662, 1553, 257, 5994, 5454, 917, 47966, 2261, 552, 11, 264, 2487, 307, 674, 15711, 1188, 22242, 11, 457, 7696, 517, 16226, 712, 13, 51390], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12063921292622884, "compression_ratio": 1.5228426395939085, "no_speech_prob": 2.529247427815462e-12}, {"id": 124, "seek": 72968, "start": 729.68, "end": 734.3599999999999, "text": " It's like the network is essentially partitioned based on the economic status of the agent.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 411, 264, 3209, 307, 4476, 24808, 292, 2361, 322, 264, 4836, 6558, 295, 264, 9461, 13, 50599], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2543888825636644, "compression_ratio": 1.1704545454545454, "no_speech_prob": 2.371005735496423e-12}, {"id": 125, "seek": 72968, "start": 734.6999999999999, "end": 735.14, "text": " Absolutely.", "tokens": [50616, 7021, 13, 50638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2543888825636644, "compression_ratio": 1.1704545454545454, "no_speech_prob": 2.371005735496423e-12}, {"id": 126, "seek": 73514, "start": 735.14, "end": 741.92, "text": " And that concept of partition networks becomes even more literal with the forced failure mode, link rot.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 3410, 295, 24808, 9590, 3643, 754, 544, 20411, 365, 264, 7579, 7763, 4391, 11, 2113, 4297, 13, 50704], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 127, "seek": 73514, "start": 742.26, "end": 742.72, "text": " Look rot.", "tokens": [50721, 2053, 4297, 13, 50744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 128, "seek": 73514, "start": 742.8199999999999, "end": 744.3, "text": " The classic 404 error.", "tokens": [50749, 440, 7230, 3356, 19, 6713, 13, 50823], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 129, "seek": 73514, "start": 744.46, "end": 744.98, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50831, 7587, 13, 50857], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 130, "seek": 73514, "start": 745.76, "end": 748.08, "text": " This is the physical degradation of the graph.", "tokens": [50896, 639, 307, 264, 4001, 40519, 295, 264, 4295, 13, 51012], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 131, "seek": 73514, "start": 748.62, "end": 757.3199999999999, "text": " Studies tracking the lifespan of URLs in judicial opinions, academic papers, and journalistic reporting reveal a staggering decay rate.", "tokens": [51039, 17515, 11603, 264, 40361, 295, 43267, 294, 26581, 11819, 11, 7778, 10577, 11, 293, 6708, 3142, 10031, 10658, 257, 42974, 21039, 3314, 13, 51474], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 132, "seek": 73514, "start": 757.56, "end": 758.84, "text": " It's terrifying, honestly.", "tokens": [51486, 467, 311, 18106, 11, 6095, 13, 51550], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 133, "seek": 73514, "start": 759.0, "end": 759.48, "text": " It is.", "tokens": [51558, 467, 307, 13, 51582], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17261466551362797, "compression_ratio": 1.4637096774193548, "no_speech_prob": 2.2366240803872728e-12}, {"id": 134, "seek": 75948, "start": 759.48, "end": 769.02, "text": " Domains lapse, organizations restructure their directories without implementing server-side redirects, or content is just quietly migrated.", "tokens": [50365, 16674, 2315, 49757, 11, 6150, 1472, 2885, 641, 5391, 530, 1553, 18114, 7154, 12, 1812, 29066, 82, 11, 420, 2701, 307, 445, 19141, 48329, 13, 50842], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1366255667901808, "compression_ratio": 1.4381443298969072, "no_speech_prob": 2.1336725788967392e-12}, {"id": 135, "seek": 75948, "start": 769.34, "end": 779.04, "text": " So the underlying node, like the PDF, the Oracle, the dataset, might still be perfectly intact on an offline backup drive somewhere.", "tokens": [50858, 407, 264, 14217, 9984, 11, 411, 264, 17752, 11, 264, 25654, 11, 264, 28872, 11, 1062, 920, 312, 6239, 23493, 322, 364, 21857, 14807, 3332, 4079, 13, 51343], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1366255667901808, "compression_ratio": 1.4381443298969072, "no_speech_prob": 2.1336725788967392e-12}, {"id": 136, "seek": 75948, "start": 779.16, "end": 779.46, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51349, 1779, 13, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1366255667901808, "compression_ratio": 1.4381443298969072, "no_speech_prob": 2.1336725788967392e-12}, {"id": 137, "seek": 77946, "start": 779.46, "end": 789.02, "text": " But the hyperlink, the vital string of characters that actually formed the bridge from your current digital location to that specific node, has evaporated.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 264, 9848, 22473, 11, 264, 11707, 6798, 295, 4342, 300, 767, 8693, 264, 7283, 490, 428, 2190, 4562, 4914, 281, 300, 2685, 9984, 11, 575, 26315, 770, 13, 50843], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 138, "seek": 77946, "start": 789.46, "end": 790.98, "text": " It yields a 404 error.", "tokens": [50865, 467, 32168, 257, 3356, 19, 6713, 13, 50941], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 139, "seek": 77946, "start": 791.5400000000001, "end": 794.1800000000001, "text": " It's a navigational pointer aiming at a void.", "tokens": [50969, 467, 311, 257, 7407, 1478, 23918, 20253, 412, 257, 22009, 13, 51101], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 140, "seek": 77946, "start": 794.44, "end": 798.72, "text": " You can't even cross the bridge to verify if the destination still exists.", "tokens": [51114, 509, 393, 380, 754, 3278, 264, 7283, 281, 16888, 498, 264, 12236, 920, 8198, 13, 51328], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 141, "seek": 77946, "start": 798.86, "end": 803.2800000000001, "text": " Which introduces perhaps the most philosophically challenging failure mode in the taxonomy.", "tokens": [51335, 3013, 31472, 4317, 264, 881, 14529, 984, 7595, 7763, 4391, 294, 264, 3366, 23423, 13, 51556], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 142, "seek": 77946, "start": 804.0400000000001, "end": 805.36, "text": " Archival isolation.", "tokens": [51594, 10984, 3576, 16001, 13, 51660], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 143, "seek": 77946, "start": 805.6, "end": 806.84, "text": " This one blew my mind.", "tokens": [51672, 639, 472, 19075, 452, 1575, 13, 51734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 144, "seek": 77946, "start": 807.1800000000001, "end": 808.0400000000001, "text": " It's fascinating.", "tokens": [51751, 467, 311, 10343, 13, 51794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1313588991077668, "compression_ratio": 1.5971731448763251, "no_speech_prob": 1.8759225943465463e-12}, {"id": 145, "seek": 80804, "start": 808.04, "end": 818.98, "text": " The paper examines massive institutional repositories using the September 11 digital archive held by the Library of Congress as a primary case study.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3035, 1139, 1652, 5994, 18391, 22283, 2083, 1228, 264, 7216, 2975, 4562, 23507, 5167, 538, 264, 12806, 295, 6426, 382, 257, 6194, 1389, 2979, 13, 50912], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13431541124979654, "compression_ratio": 1.4977168949771689, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014860015039044e-12}, {"id": 146, "seek": 80804, "start": 819.5, "end": 820.92, "text": " Which is a massive collection, right?", "tokens": [50938, 3013, 307, 257, 5994, 5765, 11, 558, 30, 51009], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13431541124979654, "compression_ratio": 1.4977168949771689, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014860015039044e-12}, {"id": 147, "seek": 80804, "start": 820.92, "end": 828.06, "text": " A staggering collection of firsthand digital artifacts, emails, early web pages from 2001.", "tokens": [51009, 316, 42974, 5765, 295, 38599, 4562, 24617, 11, 12524, 11, 2440, 3670, 7183, 490, 16382, 13, 51366], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13431541124979654, "compression_ratio": 1.4977168949771689, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014860015039044e-12}, {"id": 148, "seek": 80804, "start": 828.76, "end": 830.4399999999999, "text": " Its preservation is absolute.", "tokens": [51401, 6953, 27257, 307, 8236, 13, 51485], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13431541124979654, "compression_ratio": 1.4977168949771689, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014860015039044e-12}, {"id": 149, "seek": 80804, "start": 830.88, "end": 832.1999999999999, "text": " It is totally safe.", "tokens": [51507, 467, 307, 3879, 3273, 13, 51573], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13431541124979654, "compression_ratio": 1.4977168949771689, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014860015039044e-12}, {"id": 150, "seek": 83220, "start": 832.2, "end": 839.26, "text": " Yet, for the average citizen just typing a query into a mainstream search engine, it might as well not exist.", "tokens": [50365, 10890, 11, 337, 264, 4274, 13326, 445, 18444, 257, 14581, 666, 257, 15960, 3164, 2848, 11, 309, 1062, 382, 731, 406, 2514, 13, 50718], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16549531151266658, "compression_ratio": 1.540909090909091, "no_speech_prob": 1.5191832167249508e-12}, {"id": 151, "seek": 83220, "start": 839.4200000000001, "end": 840.1, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50726, 7587, 13, 50760], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16549531151266658, "compression_ratio": 1.540909090909091, "no_speech_prob": 1.5191832167249508e-12}, {"id": 152, "seek": 83220, "start": 840.6, "end": 848.9000000000001, "text": " The archive's internal architecture does not interface seamlessly with the proprietary algorithms that govern public search visibility.", "tokens": [50785, 440, 23507, 311, 6920, 9482, 775, 406, 9226, 38083, 365, 264, 38992, 14642, 300, 1980, 1908, 3164, 19883, 13, 51200], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16549531151266658, "compression_ratio": 1.540909090909091, "no_speech_prob": 1.5191832167249508e-12}, {"id": 153, "seek": 83220, "start": 849.08, "end": 855.0400000000001, "text": " So unless you already possess the specific prior knowledge that this archive exists,", "tokens": [51209, 407, 5969, 291, 1217, 17490, 264, 2685, 4059, 3601, 300, 341, 23507, 8198, 11, 51507], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16549531151266658, "compression_ratio": 1.540909090909091, "no_speech_prob": 1.5191832167249508e-12}, {"id": 154, "seek": 85504, "start": 855.04, "end": 861.04, "text": " and you navigate directly to its internal search bar, the content remains totally hidden.", "tokens": [50365, 293, 291, 12350, 3838, 281, 1080, 6920, 3164, 2159, 11, 264, 2701, 7023, 3879, 7633, 13, 50665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22582440498547676, "compression_ratio": 1.353846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.176086134203503e-12}, {"id": 155, "seek": 85504, "start": 861.04, "end": 861.68, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50665, 1779, 13, 50697], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22582440498547676, "compression_ratio": 1.353846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.176086134203503e-12}, {"id": 156, "seek": 85504, "start": 861.8, "end": 866.0, "text": " And this raises a crucial point regarding the fundamental nature of navigation.", "tokens": [50703, 400, 341, 19658, 257, 11462, 935, 8595, 264, 8088, 3687, 295, 17346, 13, 50913], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22582440498547676, "compression_ratio": 1.353846153846154, "no_speech_prob": 2.176086134203503e-12}, {"id": 157, "seek": 86600, "start": 866.0, "end": 871.26, "text": " It demonstrates that reachability is not an objective property of the data.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 31034, 300, 2524, 2310, 307, 406, 364, 10024, 4707, 295, 264, 1412, 13, 50628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18293147892146916, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892567430993542e-12}, {"id": 158, "seek": 86600, "start": 871.26, "end": 872.54, "text": " Oh, that's a cute distinction.", "tokens": [50628, 876, 11, 300, 311, 257, 4052, 16844, 13, 50692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18293147892146916, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892567430993542e-12}, {"id": 159, "seek": 86600, "start": 873.06, "end": 873.22, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50718, 1779, 13, 50726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18293147892146916, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892567430993542e-12}, {"id": 160, "seek": 86600, "start": 873.38, "end": 876.1, "text": " It is a relational property dependent on the agent.", "tokens": [50734, 467, 307, 257, 38444, 4707, 12334, 322, 264, 9461, 13, 50870], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18293147892146916, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892567430993542e-12}, {"id": 161, "seek": 86600, "start": 876.62, "end": 885.96, "text": " The text formalizes this by saying reachability is a function of the navigational resources available to a specific class of agent at a specific moment in time.", "tokens": [50896, 440, 2487, 9860, 5660, 341, 538, 1566, 2524, 2310, 307, 257, 2445, 295, 264, 7407, 1478, 3593, 2435, 281, 257, 2685, 1508, 295, 9461, 412, 257, 2685, 1623, 294, 565, 13, 51363], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18293147892146916, "compression_ratio": 1.6059113300492611, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892567430993542e-12}, {"id": 162, "seek": 88596, "start": 885.96, "end": 896.76, "text": " So that implies a credentialed archivist and a high school student inhabit vastly different realities, even when they're interacting with the exact same underlying internet.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 300, 18779, 257, 22034, 292, 3912, 592, 468, 293, 257, 1090, 1395, 3107, 21863, 41426, 819, 27785, 11, 754, 562, 436, 434, 18017, 365, 264, 1900, 912, 14217, 4705, 13, 50905], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17889219585217928, "compression_ratio": 1.6513409961685823, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782028682699955e-12}, {"id": 163, "seek": 88596, "start": 897.0600000000001, "end": 897.6600000000001, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [50920, 48746, 736, 13, 50950], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17889219585217928, "compression_ratio": 1.6513409961685823, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782028682699955e-12}, {"id": 164, "seek": 88596, "start": 898.5400000000001, "end": 907.02, "text": " The archivist possesses the structural maps, the Boolean search syntax, and the institutional access to traverse the graph.", "tokens": [50994, 440, 3912, 592, 468, 17490, 279, 264, 15067, 11317, 11, 264, 23351, 28499, 3164, 28431, 11, 293, 264, 18391, 2105, 281, 45674, 264, 4295, 13, 51418], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17889219585217928, "compression_ratio": 1.6513409961685823, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782028682699955e-12}, {"id": 165, "seek": 88596, "start": 907.58, "end": 913.48, "text": " The high school student is entirely reliant on the edges surfaced by algorithmic search engines.", "tokens": [51446, 440, 1090, 1395, 3107, 307, 7696, 1039, 5798, 322, 264, 8819, 9684, 3839, 538, 9284, 299, 3164, 12982, 13, 51741], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17889219585217928, "compression_ratio": 1.6513409961685823, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782028682699955e-12}, {"id": 166, "seek": 88596, "start": 913.5600000000001, "end": 914.94, "text": " Which is pretty limiting.", "tokens": [51745, 3013, 307, 1238, 22083, 13, 51814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17889219585217928, "compression_ratio": 1.6513409961685823, "no_speech_prob": 1.4782028682699955e-12}, {"id": 167, "seek": 91494, "start": 914.94, "end": 926.3800000000001, "text": " And if the massive, heavily funded archives are failing to maintain reachability for the general public, it forces this critical pivot in the paper.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 498, 264, 5994, 11, 10950, 14385, 25607, 366, 18223, 281, 6909, 2524, 2310, 337, 264, 2674, 1908, 11, 309, 5874, 341, 4924, 14538, 294, 264, 3035, 13, 50937], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15190961884289253, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.839814758874958e-12}, {"id": 168, "seek": 91494, "start": 926.8800000000001, "end": 933.0400000000001, "text": " Like, what type of system actually succeeds at maintaining semantic continuity over centuries?", "tokens": [50962, 1743, 11, 437, 2010, 295, 1185, 767, 49263, 412, 14916, 47982, 23807, 670, 13926, 30, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15190961884289253, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.839814758874958e-12}, {"id": 169, "seek": 91494, "start": 933.4000000000001, "end": 935.7600000000001, "text": " The paper's answer is highly counterintuitive.", "tokens": [51288, 440, 3035, 311, 1867, 307, 5405, 5682, 686, 48314, 13, 51406], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15190961884289253, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.839814758874958e-12}, {"id": 170, "seek": 91494, "start": 936.1, "end": 942.94, "text": " Because the systems that demonstrate the greatest resilience over deep time often lack formal archival infrastructure entirely.", "tokens": [51423, 1436, 264, 3652, 300, 11698, 264, 6636, 19980, 670, 2452, 565, 2049, 5011, 9860, 3912, 3576, 6896, 7696, 13, 51765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15190961884289253, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.839814758874958e-12}, {"id": 171, "seek": 94294, "start": 942.94, "end": 945.12, "text": " Right. No servers.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 883, 15909, 13, 50474], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2021622657775879, "compression_ratio": 1.59915611814346, "no_speech_prob": 3.057027287561853e-12}, {"id": 172, "seek": 94294, "start": 945.4000000000001, "end": 945.6600000000001, "text": " None.", "tokens": [50488, 14492, 13, 50501], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2021622657775879, "compression_ratio": 1.59915611814346, "no_speech_prob": 3.057027287561853e-12}, {"id": 173, "seek": 94294, "start": 946.32, "end": 949.74, "text": " The author introduces the paradigm of the dense local system.", "tokens": [50534, 440, 3793, 31472, 264, 24709, 295, 264, 18011, 2654, 1185, 13, 50705], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2021622657775879, "compression_ratio": 1.59915611814346, "no_speech_prob": 3.057027287561853e-12}, {"id": 174, "seek": 94294, "start": 950.3800000000001, "end": 958.6600000000001, "text": " These are structures like traditional craft guilds, religious congregations, or multi-generational communities inhabiting a specific geographic area.", "tokens": [50737, 1981, 366, 9227, 411, 5164, 8448, 37435, 82, 11, 7185, 23002, 763, 11, 420, 4825, 12, 21848, 1478, 4456, 16934, 1748, 257, 2685, 32318, 1859, 13, 51151], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2021622657775879, "compression_ratio": 1.59915611814346, "no_speech_prob": 3.057027287561853e-12}, {"id": 175, "seek": 94294, "start": 959.0200000000001, "end": 962.4200000000001, "text": " Yeah, these systems are not utilizing redundant rate arrays.", "tokens": [51169, 865, 11, 613, 3652, 366, 406, 26775, 40997, 3314, 41011, 13, 51339], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2021622657775879, "compression_ratio": 1.59915611814346, "no_speech_prob": 3.057027287561853e-12}, {"id": 176, "seek": 94294, "start": 962.9000000000001, "end": 966.94, "text": " They are not digitizing their historical records or maintaining rigid taxonomies.", "tokens": [51363, 814, 366, 406, 14293, 3319, 641, 8584, 7724, 420, 14916, 22195, 3366, 12481, 530, 13, 51565], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2021622657775879, "compression_ratio": 1.59915611814346, "no_speech_prob": 3.057027287561853e-12}, {"id": 177, "seek": 96694, "start": 966.94, "end": 972.6, "text": " Their formal preservation mechanisms are almost non-existent.", "tokens": [50365, 6710, 9860, 27257, 15902, 366, 1920, 2107, 12, 18217, 317, 13, 50648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20825714053529681, "compression_ratio": 1.2946428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 2.3348053091593046e-12}, {"id": 178, "seek": 96694, "start": 972.6, "end": 979.2600000000001, "text": " Yet their capacity to retain and transmit complex semantic meaning is unparalleled.", "tokens": [50648, 10890, 641, 6042, 281, 18340, 293, 17831, 3997, 47982, 3620, 307, 517, 2181, 336, 31689, 13, 50981], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20825714053529681, "compression_ratio": 1.2946428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 2.3348053091593046e-12}, {"id": 179, "seek": 97926, "start": 979.26, "end": 983.98, "text": " And the mechanism driving this is what the author calls path density.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 264, 7513, 4840, 341, 307, 437, 264, 3793, 5498, 3100, 10305, 13, 50601], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16332316080729167, "compression_ratio": 1.5811965811965811, "no_speech_prob": 2.316448031655649e-12}, {"id": 180, "seek": 97926, "start": 984.18, "end": 985.26, "text": " Path density.", "tokens": [50611, 21914, 10305, 13, 50665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16332316080729167, "compression_ratio": 1.5811965811965811, "no_speech_prob": 2.316448031655649e-12}, {"id": 181, "seek": 97926, "start": 985.42, "end": 985.78, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50673, 1779, 13, 50691], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16332316080729167, "compression_ratio": 1.5811965811965811, "no_speech_prob": 2.316448031655649e-12}, {"id": 182, "seek": 97926, "start": 986.42, "end": 992.16, "text": " The community's graph is saturated with redundant, overlapping navigational edges.", "tokens": [50723, 440, 1768, 311, 4295, 307, 25408, 365, 40997, 11, 33535, 7407, 1478, 8819, 13, 51010], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16332316080729167, "compression_ratio": 1.5811965811965811, "no_speech_prob": 2.316448031655649e-12}, {"id": 183, "seek": 97926, "start": 992.84, "end": 1004.76, "text": " Present actions are continuously linked to past knowledge through shared oral history, repeated daily rituals, material culture, and the physical integration of elders within the active community.", "tokens": [51044, 33253, 5909, 366, 15684, 9408, 281, 1791, 3601, 807, 5507, 19338, 2503, 11, 10477, 5212, 29082, 11, 2527, 3713, 11, 293, 264, 4001, 10980, 295, 22737, 1951, 264, 4967, 1768, 13, 51640], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16332316080729167, "compression_ratio": 1.5811965811965811, "no_speech_prob": 2.316448031655649e-12}, {"id": 184, "seek": 100476, "start": 1004.76, "end": 1014.26, "text": " So if a single edge fails, like perhaps an elder passes away or a specific physical artifact is lost, the graph doesn't collapse.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 498, 257, 2167, 4691, 18199, 11, 411, 4317, 364, 12995, 11335, 1314, 420, 257, 2685, 4001, 34806, 307, 2731, 11, 264, 4295, 1177, 380, 15584, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1100637611301466, "compression_ratio": 1.6015325670498084, "no_speech_prob": 3.818388747550694e-12}, {"id": 185, "seek": 100476, "start": 1014.34, "end": 1014.88, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [50844, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1100637611301466, "compression_ratio": 1.6015325670498084, "no_speech_prob": 3.818388747550694e-12}, {"id": 186, "seek": 100476, "start": 1014.98, "end": 1023.88, "text": " Because there are dozens of alternative pathways maintained by the collective consciousness of the group, still pointing toward that exact same historical concept.", "tokens": [50876, 1436, 456, 366, 18431, 295, 8535, 22988, 17578, 538, 264, 12590, 10081, 295, 264, 1594, 11, 920, 12166, 7361, 300, 1900, 912, 8584, 3410, 13, 51321], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1100637611301466, "compression_ratio": 1.6015325670498084, "no_speech_prob": 3.818388747550694e-12}, {"id": 187, "seek": 100476, "start": 1024.46, "end": 1030.6, "text": " They don't require a static archive because they are continuously engaged in the traversal of their own history.", "tokens": [51350, 814, 500, 380, 3651, 257, 13437, 23507, 570, 436, 366, 15684, 8237, 294, 264, 23149, 304, 295, 641, 1065, 2503, 13, 51657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1100637611301466, "compression_ratio": 1.6015325670498084, "no_speech_prob": 3.818388747550694e-12}, {"id": 188, "seek": 103060, "start": 1030.6, "end": 1031.48, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50409], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 189, "seek": 103060, "start": 1031.78, "end": 1041.76, "text": " And building on that principle, the author scales the concept of path density to the largest cognitive infrastructure we possess, which is human language.", "tokens": [50424, 400, 2390, 322, 300, 8665, 11, 264, 3793, 17408, 264, 3410, 295, 3100, 10305, 281, 264, 6443, 15605, 6896, 321, 17490, 11, 597, 307, 1952, 2856, 13, 50923], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 190, "seek": 103060, "start": 1042.06, "end": 1043.76, "text": " Language is a navigation system.", "tokens": [50938, 24445, 307, 257, 17346, 1185, 13, 51023], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 191, "seek": 103060, "start": 1043.8, "end": 1044.76, "text": " I love this part.", "tokens": [51025, 286, 959, 341, 644, 13, 51073], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 192, "seek": 103060, "start": 1044.9399999999998, "end": 1045.5, "text": " It's brilliant.", "tokens": [51082, 467, 311, 10248, 13, 51110], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 193, "seek": 103060, "start": 1046.08, "end": 1049.12, "text": " Language operates as a generational navigation system.", "tokens": [51139, 24445, 22577, 382, 257, 48320, 17346, 1185, 13, 51291], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 194, "seek": 103060, "start": 1049.8999999999999, "end": 1058.12, "text": " When a population speaks a specific language, they are actively traversing a vast inherited subgraph of human meaning.", "tokens": [51330, 1133, 257, 4415, 10789, 257, 2685, 2856, 11, 436, 366, 13022, 23149, 278, 257, 8369, 27091, 1422, 34091, 295, 1952, 3620, 13, 51741], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17738273408677843, "compression_ratio": 1.6290322580645162, "no_speech_prob": 1.875920642782636e-12}, {"id": 195, "seek": 105812, "start": 1058.12, "end": 1065.12, "text": " The grammar, the idioms, the vocabulary, they all contain embedded conceptual frameworks.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 22317, 11, 264, 18014, 4785, 11, 264, 19864, 11, 436, 439, 5304, 16741, 24106, 29834, 13, 50715], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09476315077914986, "compression_ratio": 1.6074074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.0047321008104246e-12}, {"id": 196, "seek": 105812, "start": 1065.1799999999998, "end": 1071.3999999999999, "text": " And the paper analyzes the structural fallout when a dominant language displaces a regional one.", "tokens": [50718, 400, 264, 3035, 6459, 12214, 264, 15067, 2100, 346, 562, 257, 15657, 2856, 14996, 2116, 257, 10964, 472, 13, 51029], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09476315077914986, "compression_ratio": 1.6074074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.0047321008104246e-12}, {"id": 197, "seek": 105812, "start": 1071.6399999999999, "end": 1071.9799999999998, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51041, 1779, 13, 51058], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09476315077914986, "compression_ratio": 1.6074074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.0047321008104246e-12}, {"id": 198, "seek": 105812, "start": 1072.36, "end": 1084.02, "text": " When standardized French eradicated regional dialects, or when colonial English and Spanish reorganized indigenous territories, the result was not simply a swap of dictionaries.", "tokens": [51077, 1133, 31677, 5522, 33078, 3587, 10964, 24652, 82, 11, 420, 562, 19066, 3669, 293, 8058, 41203, 1602, 15511, 25195, 11, 264, 1874, 390, 406, 2935, 257, 18135, 295, 22352, 4889, 13, 51660], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09476315077914986, "compression_ratio": 1.6074074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.0047321008104246e-12}, {"id": 199, "seek": 105812, "start": 1084.02, "end": 1087.8, "text": " It was a catastrophic restructuring of the reachability graph.", "tokens": [51660, 467, 390, 257, 34915, 1472, 1757, 1345, 295, 264, 2524, 2310, 4295, 13, 51849], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09476315077914986, "compression_ratio": 1.6074074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.0047321008104246e-12}, {"id": 200, "seek": 108812, "start": 1088.12, "end": 1105.52, "text": " The prior semantic states, the complex environmental knowledge encoded in indigenous taxonomies, the localized historical narratives, they weren't necessarily destroyed the exact moment the new language was imposed, but they became fundamentally unreachable to the subsequent generations.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4059, 47982, 4368, 11, 264, 3997, 8303, 3601, 2058, 12340, 294, 15511, 3366, 12481, 530, 11, 264, 44574, 8584, 28016, 11, 436, 4999, 380, 4725, 8937, 264, 1900, 1623, 264, 777, 2856, 390, 26491, 11, 457, 436, 3062, 17879, 517, 16226, 712, 281, 264, 19962, 10593, 13, 51235], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1415797655399029, "compression_ratio": 1.5078534031413613, "no_speech_prob": 2.8053371257941162e-12}, {"id": 201, "seek": 110552, "start": 1105.52, "end": 1106.52, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28502631187438965, "compression_ratio": 1.3388429752066116, "no_speech_prob": 2.4757730587854354e-12}, {"id": 202, "seek": 110552, "start": 1106.52, "end": 1116.52, "text": " The children only inherited the navigational edges provided by the new dominant language, and those edges simply did not connect to the old conceptual nodes.", "tokens": [50415, 440, 2227, 787, 27091, 264, 7407, 1478, 8819, 5649, 538, 264, 777, 15657, 2856, 11, 293, 729, 8819, 2935, 630, 406, 1745, 281, 264, 1331, 24106, 13891, 13, 50915], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28502631187438965, "compression_ratio": 1.3388429752066116, "no_speech_prob": 2.4757730587854354e-12}, {"id": 203, "seek": 111652, "start": 1116.52, "end": 1123.52, "text": " Contrast that displacement with the paper's analysis of the Arabic language.", "tokens": [50365, 4839, 4148, 300, 21899, 365, 264, 3035, 311, 5215, 295, 264, 19938, 2856, 13, 50715], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485493381818137, "compression_ratio": 1.404494382022472, "no_speech_prob": 2.334596491820884e-12}, {"id": 204, "seek": 111652, "start": 1123.52, "end": 1136.52, "text": " Arabic has maintained profound semantic continuity for over 14 centuries, surviving massive geographic expansion, the rise and fall of empires, intense technological shifts.", "tokens": [50715, 19938, 575, 17578, 14382, 47982, 23807, 337, 670, 3499, 13926, 11, 24948, 5994, 32318, 11260, 11, 264, 6272, 293, 2100, 295, 4012, 3145, 11, 9447, 18439, 19201, 13, 51365], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485493381818137, "compression_ratio": 1.404494382022472, "no_speech_prob": 2.334596491820884e-12}, {"id": 205, "seek": 113652, "start": 1136.52, "end": 1143.72, "text": " And it hasn't survived merely through rigid, tensile preservation, but through forced, continuous traversal.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 309, 6132, 380, 14433, 17003, 807, 22195, 11, 10688, 794, 27257, 11, 457, 807, 7579, 11, 10957, 23149, 304, 13, 50725], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14250302588802644, "compression_ratio": 1.6031128404669261, "no_speech_prob": 2.0683650105157714e-12}, {"id": 206, "seek": 113652, "start": 1144.28, "end": 1145.94, "text": " The mechanism is active use.", "tokens": [50753, 440, 7513, 307, 4967, 764, 13, 50836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14250302588802644, "compression_ratio": 1.6031128404669261, "no_speech_prob": 2.0683650105157714e-12}, {"id": 207, "seek": 113652, "start": 1146.26, "end": 1155.36, "text": " The liturgical requirements, the daily recitation of the Quran, the classical literary frameworks, and the unbroken chains of scholarly commentary.", "tokens": [50852, 440, 7997, 46736, 7728, 11, 264, 5212, 850, 4614, 295, 264, 19375, 11, 264, 13735, 24194, 29834, 11, 293, 264, 517, 37947, 12626, 295, 39589, 23527, 13, 51307], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14250302588802644, "compression_ratio": 1.6031128404669261, "no_speech_prob": 2.0683650105157714e-12}, {"id": 208, "seek": 113652, "start": 1156.22, "end": 1164.54, "text": " All of this requires millions of individuals to actively parse and navigate 7th century syntax and semantics every single day.", "tokens": [51350, 1057, 295, 341, 7029, 6803, 295, 5346, 281, 13022, 48377, 293, 12350, 1614, 392, 4901, 28431, 293, 4361, 45298, 633, 2167, 786, 13, 51766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14250302588802644, "compression_ratio": 1.6031128404669261, "no_speech_prob": 2.0683650105157714e-12}, {"id": 209, "seek": 116454, "start": 1164.54, "end": 1170.5, "text": " Here's where it gets really interesting, because it clarifies that survival is an action, not a state.", "tokens": [50365, 1692, 311, 689, 309, 2170, 534, 1880, 11, 570, 309, 6093, 11221, 300, 12559, 307, 364, 3069, 11, 406, 257, 1785, 13, 50663], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.137120557635018, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.5540611292562687e-12}, {"id": 210, "seek": 116454, "start": 1171.04, "end": 1173.18, "text": " It actually reminds me of a specific image.", "tokens": [50690, 467, 767, 12025, 385, 295, 257, 2685, 3256, 13, 50797], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.137120557635018, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.5540611292562687e-12}, {"id": 211, "seek": 116454, "start": 1173.68, "end": 1178.6, "text": " So imagine a narrow dirt trail cutting through a dense, rapidly growing forest.", "tokens": [50822, 407, 3811, 257, 9432, 11483, 9924, 6492, 807, 257, 18011, 11, 12910, 4194, 6719, 13, 51068], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.137120557635018, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.5540611292562687e-12}, {"id": 212, "seek": 116454, "start": 1178.72, "end": 1179.82, "text": " Hey, I'm picturing it.", "tokens": [51074, 1911, 11, 286, 478, 2317, 1345, 309, 13, 51129], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.137120557635018, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.5540611292562687e-12}, {"id": 213, "seek": 116454, "start": 1179.92, "end": 1187.08, "text": " If you want that path to survive, paving it with concrete and walking away is actually a failure of engineering.", "tokens": [51134, 759, 291, 528, 300, 3100, 281, 7867, 11, 280, 6152, 309, 365, 9859, 293, 4494, 1314, 307, 767, 257, 7763, 295, 7043, 13, 51492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.137120557635018, "compression_ratio": 1.5947136563876652, "no_speech_prob": 2.5540611292562687e-12}, {"id": 214, "seek": 118708, "start": 1187.08, "end": 1193.96, "text": " The roots will eventually crack the foundation, the canopy will block the light, and the forest will just reclaim it.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 10669, 486, 4728, 6226, 264, 7030, 11, 264, 38235, 486, 3461, 264, 1442, 11, 293, 264, 6719, 486, 445, 40074, 309, 13, 50709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11068189750283451, "compression_ratio": 1.5251396648044693, "no_speech_prob": 1.7554049576776198e-12}, {"id": 215, "seek": 118708, "start": 1194.32, "end": 1204.02, "text": " The only way the path survives is if people continuously choose to walk on it, day after day, their physical movement actively beating back the overgrowth.", "tokens": [50727, 440, 787, 636, 264, 3100, 46231, 307, 498, 561, 15684, 2826, 281, 1792, 322, 309, 11, 786, 934, 786, 11, 641, 4001, 3963, 13022, 13497, 646, 264, 670, 49747, 13, 51212], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11068189750283451, "compression_ratio": 1.5251396648044693, "no_speech_prob": 1.7554049576776198e-12}, {"id": 216, "seek": 120402, "start": 1204.02, "end": 1209.86, "text": " That is a perfect analogy, that active maintenance is the defining variable.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 257, 2176, 21663, 11, 300, 4967, 11258, 307, 264, 17827, 7006, 13, 50657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21628142625857621, "compression_ratio": 1.425233644859813, "no_speech_prob": 3.081088986375824e-12}, {"id": 217, "seek": 120402, "start": 1210.4, "end": 1215.02, "text": " And the text notes that this maintenance does not have to be entirely organic, right?", "tokens": [50684, 400, 264, 2487, 5570, 300, 341, 11258, 775, 406, 362, 281, 312, 7696, 10220, 11, 558, 30, 50915], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21628142625857621, "compression_ratio": 1.425233644859813, "no_speech_prob": 3.081088986375824e-12}, {"id": 218, "seek": 120402, "start": 1215.06, "end": 1217.86, "text": " It can be legally and structurally engineered.", "tokens": [50917, 467, 393, 312, 21106, 293, 6594, 6512, 38648, 13, 51057], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21628142625857621, "compression_ratio": 1.425233644859813, "no_speech_prob": 3.081088986375824e-12}, {"id": 219, "seek": 120402, "start": 1218.16, "end": 1219.32, "text": " Right, the Quebec example.", "tokens": [51072, 1779, 11, 264, 38903, 1365, 13, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21628142625857621, "compression_ratio": 1.425233644859813, "no_speech_prob": 3.081088986375824e-12}, {"id": 220, "seek": 120402, "start": 1219.6399999999999, "end": 1219.94, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51146, 1079, 13, 51161], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21628142625857621, "compression_ratio": 1.425233644859813, "no_speech_prob": 3.081088986375824e-12}, {"id": 221, "seek": 120402, "start": 1220.58, "end": 1225.1, "text": " The author examines Quebec's 1977 Chart de la Lange Fran\u00e7aise.", "tokens": [51193, 440, 3793, 1139, 1652, 38903, 311, 35092, 49762, 368, 635, 441, 933, 17288, 5297, 908, 13, 51419], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21628142625857621, "compression_ratio": 1.425233644859813, "no_speech_prob": 3.081088986375824e-12}, {"id": 222, "seek": 122510, "start": 1225.1, "end": 1232.4399999999998, "text": " Now, in standard political discourse, this legislation is analyzed purely as a cultural protectionist measure.", "tokens": [50365, 823, 11, 294, 3832, 3905, 23938, 11, 341, 11329, 307, 28181, 17491, 382, 257, 6988, 6334, 468, 3481, 13, 50732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15651447432381765, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.7902378798145824e-12}, {"id": 223, "seek": 122510, "start": 1232.86, "end": 1240.24, "text": " But through the lens of graph theory, it is a brilliant deployment of a structural constraint designed to maintain semantic edges.", "tokens": [50753, 583, 807, 264, 6765, 295, 4295, 5261, 11, 309, 307, 257, 10248, 19317, 295, 257, 15067, 25534, 4761, 281, 6909, 47982, 8819, 13, 51122], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15651447432381765, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.7902378798145824e-12}, {"id": 224, "seek": 122510, "start": 1240.62, "end": 1242.4199999999998, "text": " Wait, explain the mechanism there.", "tokens": [51141, 3802, 11, 2903, 264, 7513, 456, 13, 51231], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15651447432381765, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.7902378798145824e-12}, {"id": 225, "seek": 122510, "start": 1242.4199999999998, "end": 1249.12, "text": " How does a piece of administrative legislation act as a structural constraint on a theoretical network?", "tokens": [51231, 1012, 775, 257, 2522, 295, 17900, 11329, 605, 382, 257, 15067, 25534, 322, 257, 20864, 3209, 30, 51566], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15651447432381765, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.7902378798145824e-12}, {"id": 226, "seek": 122510, "start": 1249.36, "end": 1250.6999999999998, "text": " I mean, practically speaking.", "tokens": [51578, 286, 914, 11, 15667, 4124, 13, 51645], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15651447432381765, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.7902378798145824e-12}, {"id": 227, "seek": 125070, "start": 1250.7, "end": 1262.74, "text": " Well, by legally enforcing the use of the French language in commercial transactions, public signage, workplace infrastructure, the law establishes strict boundary conditions.", "tokens": [50365, 1042, 11, 538, 21106, 25495, 2175, 264, 764, 295, 264, 5522, 2856, 294, 6841, 16856, 11, 1908, 1465, 609, 11, 15328, 6896, 11, 264, 2101, 8327, 279, 10910, 12866, 4487, 13, 50967], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10373989741007487, "compression_ratio": 1.5051020408163265, "no_speech_prob": 2.1933479338320794e-12}, {"id": 228, "seek": 125070, "start": 1263.3600000000001, "end": 1271.32, "text": " It forces the daily transactional edges of the society to remain tethered to the francophone semantic graph.", "tokens": [50998, 467, 5874, 264, 5212, 46688, 1966, 8819, 295, 264, 4086, 281, 6222, 256, 1666, 292, 281, 264, 30514, 32561, 47982, 4295, 13, 51396], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10373989741007487, "compression_ratio": 1.5051020408163265, "no_speech_prob": 2.1933479338320794e-12}, {"id": 229, "seek": 125070, "start": 1271.44, "end": 1272.22, "text": " Ah, I see.", "tokens": [51402, 2438, 11, 286, 536, 13, 51441], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10373989741007487, "compression_ratio": 1.5051020408163265, "no_speech_prob": 2.1933479338320794e-12}, {"id": 230, "seek": 127222, "start": 1272.22, "end": 1282.7, "text": " Without that constraint, the overwhelming gravitational pull of the English-speaking North American economy would naturally reroute those daily paths.", "tokens": [50365, 9129, 300, 25534, 11, 264, 13373, 28538, 2235, 295, 264, 3669, 12, 14579, 4067, 2665, 5010, 576, 8195, 43819, 14040, 729, 5212, 14518, 13, 50889], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12758068371844547, "compression_ratio": 1.5698924731182795, "no_speech_prob": 2.16759965011859e-12}, {"id": 231, "seek": 127222, "start": 1282.82, "end": 1283.0, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50895, 1779, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12758068371844547, "compression_ratio": 1.5698924731182795, "no_speech_prob": 2.16759965011859e-12}, {"id": 232, "seek": 127222, "start": 1283.3, "end": 1294.84, "text": " The law prevents a rapid transition where the immediate path, the existing cultural nodes, would become unreachable due to a mass migration to a different navigational infrastructure.", "tokens": [50919, 440, 2101, 22367, 257, 7558, 6034, 689, 264, 11629, 3100, 11, 264, 6741, 6988, 13891, 11, 576, 1813, 517, 16226, 712, 3462, 281, 257, 2758, 17011, 281, 257, 819, 7407, 1478, 6896, 13, 51496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12758068371844547, "compression_ratio": 1.5698924731182795, "no_speech_prob": 2.16759965011859e-12}, {"id": 233, "seek": 127222, "start": 1295.1000000000001, "end": 1295.44, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [51509, 3153, 13, 51526], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12758068371844547, "compression_ratio": 1.5698924731182795, "no_speech_prob": 2.16759965011859e-12}, {"id": 234, "seek": 127222, "start": 1295.8600000000001, "end": 1300.94, "text": " If we connect this to the bigger picture, it really changes how you view, well, everything.", "tokens": [51547, 759, 321, 1745, 341, 281, 264, 3801, 3036, 11, 309, 534, 2962, 577, 291, 1910, 11, 731, 11, 1203, 13, 51801], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12758068371844547, "compression_ratio": 1.5698924731182795, "no_speech_prob": 2.16759965011859e-12}, {"id": 235, "seek": 130094, "start": 1300.94, "end": 1302.7, "text": " So what does this all mean for us?", "tokens": [50365, 407, 437, 775, 341, 439, 914, 337, 505, 30, 50453], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1449240006898579, "compression_ratio": 1.4575471698113207, "no_speech_prob": 1.958284229219842e-12}, {"id": 236, "seek": 130094, "start": 1303.02, "end": 1315.88, "text": " We have moved from examining the dead links in your bookmarks folder to the structural burying of Wikipedia's history, all the way to centuries-old liturgical practices and modern linguistic legislation.", "tokens": [50469, 492, 362, 4259, 490, 34662, 264, 3116, 6123, 294, 428, 1446, 37307, 10820, 281, 264, 15067, 2779, 1840, 295, 28999, 311, 2503, 11, 439, 264, 636, 281, 13926, 12, 2641, 7997, 46736, 7525, 293, 4363, 43002, 11329, 13, 51112], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1449240006898579, "compression_ratio": 1.4575471698113207, "no_speech_prob": 1.958284229219842e-12}, {"id": 237, "seek": 130094, "start": 1316.02, "end": 1317.0800000000002, "text": " It's quite a journey.", "tokens": [51119, 467, 311, 1596, 257, 4671, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1449240006898579, "compression_ratio": 1.4575471698113207, "no_speech_prob": 1.958284229219842e-12}, {"id": 238, "seek": 130094, "start": 1317.5, "end": 1317.9, "text": " It is.", "tokens": [51193, 467, 307, 13, 51213], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1449240006898579, "compression_ratio": 1.4575471698113207, "no_speech_prob": 1.958284229219842e-12}, {"id": 239, "seek": 130094, "start": 1318.04, "end": 1320.18, "text": " And the logical through line is absolute.", "tokens": [51220, 400, 264, 14978, 807, 1622, 307, 8236, 13, 51327], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1449240006898579, "compression_ratio": 1.4575471698113207, "no_speech_prob": 1.958284229219842e-12}, {"id": 240, "seek": 132018, "start": 1320.18, "end": 1335.5, "text": " If we want to guarantee the survival of meaning, whether we are talking about a civilization's historical record or just your own personal research database, the author insists we must meet three distinct constructive requirements.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 321, 528, 281, 10815, 264, 12559, 295, 3620, 11, 1968, 321, 366, 1417, 466, 257, 18036, 311, 8584, 2136, 420, 445, 428, 1065, 2973, 2132, 8149, 11, 264, 3793, 50137, 321, 1633, 1677, 1045, 10644, 30223, 7728, 13, 51131], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 241, "seek": 132018, "start": 1335.7, "end": 1335.92, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51141, 1779, 13, 51152], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 242, "seek": 132018, "start": 1336.1200000000001, "end": 1337.42, "text": " The three requirements.", "tokens": [51162, 440, 1045, 7728, 13, 51227], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 243, "seek": 132018, "start": 1337.5, "end": 1339.24, "text": " First, note persistence.", "tokens": [51231, 2386, 11, 3637, 37617, 13, 51318], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 244, "seek": 132018, "start": 1340.14, "end": 1344.5800000000002, "text": " We must ensure the physical or digital manifestation of the data survives.", "tokens": [51363, 492, 1633, 5586, 264, 4001, 420, 4562, 29550, 295, 264, 1412, 46231, 13, 51585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 245, "seek": 132018, "start": 1344.6200000000001, "end": 1345.72, "text": " Keep the file safe.", "tokens": [51587, 5527, 264, 3991, 3273, 13, 51642], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 246, "seek": 132018, "start": 1345.94, "end": 1346.14, "text": " Yep.", "tokens": [51653, 7010, 13, 51663], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19755469921023347, "compression_ratio": 1.5731707317073171, "no_speech_prob": 2.201412012750592e-12}, {"id": 247, "seek": 134614, "start": 1346.14, "end": 1348.94, "text": " Second, edge maintenance.", "tokens": [50365, 5736, 11, 4691, 11258, 13, 50505], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15085536358403226, "compression_ratio": 1.4701986754966887, "no_speech_prob": 1.7900194130768265e-12}, {"id": 248, "seek": 134614, "start": 1349.5, "end": 1359.3000000000002, "text": " We must actively sustain the transformational pathways, the indexing algorithms, the citations, and the cultural practices that actually allow a user to move toward that data.", "tokens": [50533, 492, 1633, 13022, 6769, 264, 4088, 1478, 22988, 11, 264, 8186, 278, 14642, 11, 264, 4814, 763, 11, 293, 264, 6988, 7525, 300, 767, 2089, 257, 4195, 281, 1286, 7361, 300, 1412, 13, 51023], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15085536358403226, "compression_ratio": 1.4701986754966887, "no_speech_prob": 1.7900194130768265e-12}, {"id": 249, "seek": 134614, "start": 1359.42, "end": 1360.5600000000002, "text": " Keep the link alive.", "tokens": [51029, 5527, 264, 2113, 5465, 13, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15085536358403226, "compression_ratio": 1.4701986754966887, "no_speech_prob": 1.7900194130768265e-12}, {"id": 250, "seek": 136056, "start": 1360.56, "end": 1363.08, "text": " And third, path coherence.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 2636, 11, 3100, 26528, 655, 13, 50491], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14029992543734038, "compression_ratio": 1.4311377245508983, "no_speech_prob": 2.1842673069566443e-12}, {"id": 251, "seek": 136056, "start": 1363.8799999999999, "end": 1375.32, "text": " We must verify that the edges we are maintaining actually resolve to the correct historical meaning, ensuring they haven't been quietly redirected by commercial incentives or algorithmic shifts.", "tokens": [50531, 492, 1633, 16888, 300, 264, 8819, 321, 366, 14916, 767, 14151, 281, 264, 3006, 8584, 3620, 11, 16882, 436, 2378, 380, 668, 19141, 29066, 292, 538, 6841, 23374, 420, 9284, 299, 19201, 13, 51103], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14029992543734038, "compression_ratio": 1.4311377245508983, "no_speech_prob": 2.1842673069566443e-12}, {"id": 252, "seek": 136056, "start": 1375.44, "end": 1376.2, "text": " Which is crucial.", "tokens": [51109, 3013, 307, 11462, 13, 51147], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14029992543734038, "compression_ratio": 1.4311377245508983, "no_speech_prob": 2.1842673069566443e-12}, {"id": 253, "seek": 137620, "start": 1376.2, "end": 1376.56, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50383], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 254, "seek": 137620, "start": 1376.56, "end": 1387.9, "text": " But the brutal reality of our current era is that both our massive tech conglomerates and our own personal habits are almost entirely fixated on just the first requirement.", "tokens": [50383, 583, 264, 17878, 4103, 295, 527, 2190, 4249, 307, 300, 1293, 527, 5994, 7553, 416, 7191, 14301, 1024, 293, 527, 1065, 2973, 14100, 366, 1920, 7696, 3191, 770, 322, 445, 264, 700, 11695, 13, 50950], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 255, "seek": 137620, "start": 1388.7, "end": 1390.56, "text": " We optimize for node persistence.", "tokens": [50990, 492, 19719, 337, 9984, 37617, 13, 51083], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 256, "seek": 137620, "start": 1391.32, "end": 1392.88, "text": " We upgrade our cloud tiers.", "tokens": [51121, 492, 11484, 527, 4588, 40563, 13, 51199], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 257, "seek": 137620, "start": 1393.16, "end": 1394.68, "text": " We stockpile hard drives.", "tokens": [51213, 492, 4127, 79, 794, 1152, 11754, 13, 51289], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 258, "seek": 137620, "start": 1394.82, "end": 1395.76, "text": " We amass data.", "tokens": [51296, 492, 669, 640, 1412, 13, 51343], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 259, "seek": 137620, "start": 1396.46, "end": 1399.68, "text": " But true semantic continuity cannot be bought.", "tokens": [51378, 583, 2074, 47982, 23807, 2644, 312, 4243, 13, 51539], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 260, "seek": 137620, "start": 1400.0, "end": 1401.82, "text": " It requires active coordination.", "tokens": [51555, 467, 7029, 4967, 21252, 13, 51646], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 261, "seek": 137620, "start": 1402.48, "end": 1405.5800000000002, "text": " Storage is not the invariant in the equation of memory.", "tokens": [51679, 36308, 307, 406, 264, 33270, 394, 294, 264, 5367, 295, 4675, 13, 51834], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21592692420596168, "compression_ratio": 1.6392156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 2.3993107847730677e-12}, {"id": 262, "seek": 140558, "start": 1405.58, "end": 1409.96, "text": " The local redundancy of active pathways is the invariant.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 2654, 27830, 6717, 295, 4967, 22988, 307, 264, 33270, 394, 13, 50584], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 263, "seek": 140558, "start": 1410.6599999999999, "end": 1416.6, "text": " If a system is not actively maintaining and traversing its connections, it is not preserving knowledge.", "tokens": [50619, 759, 257, 1185, 307, 406, 13022, 14916, 293, 23149, 278, 1080, 9271, 11, 309, 307, 406, 33173, 3601, 13, 50916], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 264, "seek": 140558, "start": 1417.0, "end": 1420.3, "text": " It is merely hoarding disconnected nodes in the dark.", "tokens": [50936, 467, 307, 17003, 45940, 278, 29426, 13891, 294, 264, 2877, 13, 51101], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 265, "seek": 140558, "start": 1420.56, "end": 1421.46, "text": " Hoarding in the dark.", "tokens": [51114, 3631, 515, 278, 294, 264, 2877, 13, 51159], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 266, "seek": 140558, "start": 1421.62, "end": 1421.76, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [51167, 3153, 13, 51174], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 267, "seek": 140558, "start": 1421.8999999999999, "end": 1422.02, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51181, 865, 13, 51187], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 268, "seek": 140558, "start": 1422.52, "end": 1425.26, "text": " Meaning is not an object that can be locked in a vault.", "tokens": [51212, 19948, 307, 406, 364, 2657, 300, 393, 312, 9376, 294, 257, 27134, 13, 51349], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 269, "seek": 140558, "start": 1425.6799999999998, "end": 1428.8999999999999, "text": " It is a dynamic property of a system in motion.", "tokens": [51370, 467, 307, 257, 8546, 4707, 295, 257, 1185, 294, 5394, 13, 51531], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21636143734580593, "compression_ratio": 1.6372093023255814, "no_speech_prob": 1.9493913861606815e-12}, {"id": 270, "seek": 142890, "start": 1428.9, "end": 1434.7800000000002, "text": " Which leaves us with a critical, lingering question to consider as we conclude this deep dive.", "tokens": [50365, 3013, 5510, 505, 365, 257, 4924, 11, 49542, 1168, 281, 1949, 382, 321, 16886, 341, 2452, 9192, 13, 50659], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11320892061506, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.8540733184857494e-12}, {"id": 271, "seek": 142890, "start": 1435.52, "end": 1439.98, "text": " The author's framework really forces us to confront a rapidly approaching horizon.", "tokens": [50696, 440, 3793, 311, 8388, 534, 5874, 505, 281, 12422, 257, 12910, 14908, 18046, 13, 50919], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11320892061506, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.8540733184857494e-12}, {"id": 272, "seek": 142890, "start": 1440.92, "end": 1451.92, "text": " If the survival of meaning strictly requires a limited, actively navigable path, what happens to human reachability in an era dominated by automated content generation?", "tokens": [50966, 759, 264, 12559, 295, 3620, 20792, 7029, 257, 5567, 11, 13022, 7407, 712, 3100, 11, 437, 2314, 281, 1952, 2524, 2310, 294, 364, 4249, 23755, 538, 18473, 2701, 5125, 30, 51516], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11320892061506, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.8540733184857494e-12}, {"id": 273, "seek": 145192, "start": 1451.92, "end": 1453.7, "text": " That is the big unknown.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 264, 955, 9841, 13, 50454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1489891560872396, "compression_ratio": 1.5217391304347827, "no_speech_prob": 1.8318018542989867e-12}, {"id": 274, "seek": 145192, "start": 1453.7, "end": 1454.48, "text": " All right.", "tokens": [50454, 1057, 558, 13, 50493], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1489891560872396, "compression_ratio": 1.5217391304347827, "no_speech_prob": 1.8318018542989867e-12}, {"id": 275, "seek": 145192, "start": 1455.3200000000002, "end": 1475.26, "text": " When generative AI systems are capable of instantly flooding the network with millions of perfectly preserved, syntactically flawless, but semantically redundant nodes every single hour, does that massive overabundance of data automatically destroy our capacity to maintain coherent paths?", "tokens": [50535, 1133, 1337, 1166, 7318, 3652, 366, 8189, 295, 13518, 24132, 264, 3209, 365, 6803, 295, 6239, 22242, 11, 23980, 578, 984, 45693, 11, 457, 4361, 49505, 40997, 13891, 633, 2167, 1773, 11, 775, 300, 5994, 670, 455, 997, 719, 295, 1412, 6772, 5293, 527, 6042, 281, 6909, 36239, 14518, 30, 51532], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1489891560872396, "compression_ratio": 1.5217391304347827, "no_speech_prob": 1.8318018542989867e-12}, {"id": 276, "seek": 145192, "start": 1475.3600000000001, "end": 1476.52, "text": " It's a daunting thought.", "tokens": [51537, 467, 311, 257, 37657, 1194, 13, 51595], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1489891560872396, "compression_ratio": 1.5217391304347827, "no_speech_prob": 1.8318018542989867e-12}, {"id": 277, "seek": 147652, "start": 1476.52, "end": 1477.56, "text": " It really is.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 534, 307, 13, 50417], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13483333587646484, "compression_ratio": 1.6055776892430278, "no_speech_prob": 2.5542651761051305e-12}, {"id": 278, "seek": 147652, "start": 1478.06, "end": 1487.66, "text": " If the warehouse expands exponentially faster than we can draw the map, does our obsession with generating and preserving information ultimately guarantee our inability to find it?", "tokens": [50442, 759, 264, 22244, 33706, 37330, 4663, 813, 321, 393, 2642, 264, 4471, 11, 775, 527, 30521, 365, 17746, 293, 33173, 1589, 6284, 10815, 527, 33162, 281, 915, 309, 30, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13483333587646484, "compression_ratio": 1.6055776892430278, "no_speech_prob": 2.5542651761051305e-12}, {"id": 279, "seek": 147652, "start": 1487.8, "end": 1488.0, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50929, 865, 13, 50939], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13483333587646484, "compression_ratio": 1.6055776892430278, "no_speech_prob": 2.5542651761051305e-12}, {"id": 280, "seek": 147652, "start": 1488.0, "end": 1493.6399999999999, "text": " It's definitely a structural paradox to reflect on the next time you hit save on yet another document.", "tokens": [50939, 467, 311, 2138, 257, 15067, 26221, 281, 5031, 322, 264, 958, 565, 291, 2045, 3155, 322, 1939, 1071, 4166, 13, 51221], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13483333587646484, "compression_ratio": 1.6055776892430278, "no_speech_prob": 2.5542651761051305e-12}, {"id": 281, "seek": 147652, "start": 1494.34, "end": 1499.94, "text": " Ask yourself, are you merely preserving an isolated state or are you actually maintaining the path?", "tokens": [51256, 12320, 1803, 11, 366, 291, 17003, 33173, 364, 14621, 1785, 420, 366, 291, 767, 14916, 264, 3100, 30, 51536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13483333587646484, "compression_ratio": 1.6055776892430278, "no_speech_prob": 2.5542651761051305e-12}], "language": "en"}
