, 264, 2390, 2564, 307, 6239, 23493, 13, 51051], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 17, "seek": 3000, "start": 44.28, "end": 46.519999999999996, "text": " Not a single book has been singed.", "tokens": [51079, 1726, 257, 2167, 1446, 575, 668, 1522, 292, 13, 51191], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 18, "seek": 3000, "start": 46.6, "end": 46.9, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51195, 865, 13, 51210], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 19, "seek": 3000, "start": 47.120000000000005, "end": 49.1, "text": " The temperature is strictly controlled.", "tokens": [51221, 440, 4292, 307, 20792, 10164, 13, 51320], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 20, "seek": 3000, "start": 49.42, "end": 52.14, "text": " The humidity is, like, totally optimized.", "tokens": [51336, 440, 24751, 307, 11, 411, 11, 3879, 26941, 13, 51472], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 21, "seek": 3000, "start": 52.64, "end": 55.82, "text": " Every single physical volume is perfectly safe on the shelves.", "tokens": [51497, 2048, 2167, 4001, 5523, 307, 6239, 3273, 322, 264, 24349, 13, 51656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 22, "seek": 3000, "start": 55.82, "end": 57.120000000000005, "text": " Sounds ideal, honestly.", "tokens": [51656, 14576, 7157, 11, 6095, 13, 51721], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 23, "seek": 3000, "start": 57.44, "end": 57.66, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51737, 1779, 13, 51748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26575199624766477, "compression_ratio": 1.5444444444444445, "no_speech_prob": 6.875062043103231e-13}, {"id": 24, "seek": 5766, "start": 57.66, "end": 61.339999999999996, "text": " But overnight, the entire catalog system is permanently deleted.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 13935, 11, 264, 2302, 19746, 1185, 307, 24042, 22981, 13, 50549], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.203229064033145, "compression_ratio": 0.9864864864864865, "no_speech_prob": 1.4241486679181237e-12}, {"id": 25, "seek": 5766, "start": 61.339999999999996, "end": 62.22, "text": " Oh, wow.", "tokens": [50549, 876, 11, 6076, 13, 50593], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.203229064033145, "compression_ratio": 0.9864864864864865, "no_speech_prob": 1.4241486679181237e-12}, {"id": 26, "seek": 6222, "start": 62.22, "end": 62.5, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 13, 50379], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.24470038027376742, "compression_ratio": 1.3225806451612903, "no_speech_prob": 1.5489169192042795e-12}, {"id": 27, "seek": 6222, "start": 62.5, "end": 71.76, "text": " The call numbers on the spines of the books are completely scrambled, and the shelves are entirely rearranged at random, without any documentation whatsoever.", "tokens": [50379, 440, 818, 3547, 322, 264, 637, 1652, 295, 264, 3642, 366, 2584, 49127, 11, 293, 264, 24349, 366, 7696, 29875, 10296, 412, 4974, 11, 1553, 604, 14333, 17076, 13, 50842], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.24470038027376742, "compression_ratio": 1.3225806451612903, "no_speech_prob": 1.5489169192042795e-12}, {"id": 28, "seek": 7176, "start": 71.76, "end": 74.66000000000001, "text": " That is, that's a striking image.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 11, 300, 311, 257, 18559, 3256, 13, 50510], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1983309268951416, "compression_ratio": 1.42, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779834257502844e-12}, {"id": 29, "seek": 7176, "start": 74.66000000000001, "end": 84.44, "text": " And, you know, structurally, the outcome for you, the reader, walking through those doors, is exactly the same as if the building had burned to the ground.", "tokens": [50510, 400, 11, 291, 458, 11, 6594, 6512, 11, 264, 9700, 337, 291, 11, 264, 15149, 11, 4494, 807, 729, 8077, 11, 307, 2293, 264, 912, 382, 498, 264, 2390, 632, 13490, 281, 264, 2727, 13, 50999], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1983309268951416, "compression_ratio": 1.42, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779834257502844e-12}, {"id": 30, "seek": 7176, "start": 84.56, "end": 85.42, "text": " Totally the same.", "tokens": [51005, 22837, 264, 912, 13, 51048], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1983309268951416, "compression_ratio": 1.42, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779834257502844e-12}, {"id": 31, "seek": 7176, "start": 85.74000000000001, "end": 85.98, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51064, 865, 13, 51076], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1983309268951416, "compression_ratio": 1.42, "no_speech_prob": 1.4779834257502844e-12}, {"id": 32, "seek": 8598, "start": 85.98, "end": 94.58, "text": " I mean, you arrive with a reference in hand, you need a specific book to answer a specific question, and you absolutely cannot find it.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 291, 8881, 365, 257, 6408, 294, 1011, 11, 291, 643, 257, 2685, 1446, 281, 1867, 257, 2685, 1168, 11, 293, 291, 3122, 2644, 915, 309, 13, 50795], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07675595553416126, "compression_ratio": 1.4705882352941178, "no_speech_prob": 2.389941109598448e-12}, {"id": 33, "seek": 8598, "start": 94.66, "end": 101.24000000000001, "text": " The material exists, sure, but your ability to retrieve it has been entirely annihilated.", "tokens": [50799, 440, 2527, 8198, 11, 988, 11, 457, 428, 3485, 281, 30254, 309, 575, 668, 7696, 40430, 45678, 13, 51128], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07675595553416126, "compression_ratio": 1.4705882352941178, "no_speech_prob": 2.389941109598448e-12}, {"id": 34, "seek": 10124, "start": 101.24, "end": 101.75999999999999, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50391], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16235628816270337, "compression_ratio": 1.7049808429118773, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682267546530571e-12}, {"id": 35, "seek": 10124, "start": 102.82, "end": 106.28, "text": " The first library suffered a catastrophic loss of its collection.", "tokens": [50444, 440, 700, 6405, 12770, 257, 34915, 4470, 295, 1080, 5765, 13, 50617], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16235628816270337, "compression_ratio": 1.7049808429118773, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682267546530571e-12}, {"id": 36, "seek": 10124, "start": 107.02, "end": 116.96, "text": " But the second library, it perfectly preserved its collection while completely destroying the conditions under which that collection is actually useful to a human being.", "tokens": [50654, 583, 264, 1150, 6405, 11, 309, 6239, 22242, 1080, 5765, 1339, 2584, 19926, 264, 4487, 833, 597, 300, 5765, 307, 767, 4420, 281, 257, 1952, 885, 13, 51151], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16235628816270337, "compression_ratio": 1.7049808429118773, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682267546530571e-12}, {"id": 37, "seek": 10124, "start": 117.1, "end": 117.58, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51158, 7587, 13, 51182], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16235628816270337, "compression_ratio": 1.7049808429118773, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682267546530571e-12}, {"id": 38, "seek": 10124, "start": 117.94, "end": 127.66, "text": " And that paradox, the fact that something can be perfectly saved but completely lost at the exact same time, is the entire foundation of what we are unpacking today.", "tokens": [51200, 400, 300, 26221, 11, 264, 1186, 300, 746, 393, 312, 6239, 6624, 457, 2584, 2731, 412, 264, 1900, 912, 565, 11, 307, 264, 2302, 7030, 295, 437, 321, 366, 26699, 278, 965, 13, 51686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16235628816270337, "compression_ratio": 1.7049808429118773, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682267546530571e-12}, {"id": 39, "seek": 10124, "start": 128.22, "end": 130.44, "text": " Welcome to today's Deep Dive.", "tokens": [51714, 4027, 281, 965, 311, 14895, 413, 488, 13, 51825], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16235628816270337, "compression_ratio": 1.7049808429118773, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682267546530571e-12}, {"id": 40, "seek": 13044, "start": 130.44, "end": 131.34, "text": " Glad to be here.", "tokens": [50365, 28301, 281, 312, 510, 13, 50410], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 41, "seek": 13044, "start": 131.6, "end": 136.66, "text": " We are centering our conversation today on a truly fascinating 2026 paper.", "tokens": [50423, 492, 366, 1489, 1794, 527, 3761, 965, 322, 257, 4908, 10343, 945, 10880, 3035, 13, 50676], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 42, "seek": 13044, "start": 137.14, "end": 142.6, "text": " It's by an independent researcher named Flyxion, who operates under the handle Standard Galactic.", "tokens": [50700, 467, 311, 538, 364, 6695, 21751, 4926, 3235, 4105, 11, 567, 22577, 833, 264, 4813, 21298, 7336, 19892, 13, 50973], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 43, "seek": 13044, "start": 142.85999999999999, "end": 143.16, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50986, 1779, 13, 51001], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 44, "seek": 13044, "start": 143.26, "end": 149.74, "text": " The paper is titled, From Preservation to Reachability, Semantic Continuity in an Age of Drift.", "tokens": [51006, 440, 3035, 307, 19841, 11, 3358, 2718, 6864, 281, 35904, 2310, 11, 14421, 7128, 14674, 21757, 294, 364, 16280, 295, 2491, 2008, 13, 51330], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 45, "seek": 13044, "start": 150.16, "end": 150.98, "text": " That's the one.", "tokens": [51351, 663, 311, 264, 472, 13, 51392], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 46, "seek": 13044, "start": 151.12, "end": 151.36, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51399, 865, 13, 51411], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427199155434795, "compression_ratio": 1.40625, "no_speech_prob": 1.649058710764817e-12}, {"id": 47, "seek": 15136, "start": 151.36, "end": 163.04000000000002, "text": " And our mission today is to uncover why our modern, I mean, almost obsessive focus on saving and preserving information is fundamentally failing us.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 527, 4447, 965, 307, 281, 21694, 983, 527, 4363, 11, 286, 914, 11, 1920, 35803, 488, 1879, 322, 6816, 293, 33173, 1589, 307, 17879, 18223, 505, 13, 50949], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1039460583737022, "compression_ratio": 1.3278688524590163, "no_speech_prob": 1.861328582583588e-12}, {"id": 48, "seek": 15136, "start": 163.26000000000002, "end": 164.22000000000003, "text": " It really is.", "tokens": [50960, 467, 534, 307, 13, 51008], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1039460583737022, "compression_ratio": 1.3278688524590163, "no_speech_prob": 1.861328582583588e-12}, {"id": 49, "seek": 16422, "start": 164.22, "end": 169.34, "text": " We're going to look at what we actually need to be doing instead to stay truly well-informed.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 434, 516, 281, 574, 412, 437, 321, 767, 643, 281, 312, 884, 2602, 281, 1754, 4908, 731, 12, 259, 22892, 13, 50621], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15549509341900164, "compression_ratio": 1.1204819277108433, "no_speech_prob": 1.7078020855126885e-12}, {"id": 50, "seek": 16934, "start": 169.34, "end": 181.68, "text": " Because, as a learner trying to navigate the modern world, just hitting save on a PDF or bookmarking a web page is what's creating this massive, dangerous illusion of knowledge.", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 11, 382, 257, 33347, 1382, 281, 12350, 264, 4363, 1002, 11, 445, 8850, 3155, 322, 257, 17752, 420, 1446, 5638, 278, 257, 3670, 3028, 307, 437, 311, 4084, 341, 5994, 11, 5795, 18854, 295, 3601, 13, 50982], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08108093680405035, "compression_ratio": 1.2826086956521738, "no_speech_prob": 1.701405292695024e-12}, {"id": 51, "seek": 18168, "start": 181.68, "end": 182.58, "text": " It is.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 13, 50410], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09151681057818524, "compression_ratio": 1.5925925925925926, "no_speech_prob": 2.080206232962789e-12}, {"id": 52, "seek": 18168, "start": 182.58, "end": 189.04000000000002, "text": " And to really set the stakes for this, we have to look critically at the systems we rely on every single day.", "tokens": [50410, 400, 281, 534, 992, 264, 28429, 337, 341, 11, 321, 362, 281, 574, 22797, 412, 264, 3652, 321, 10687, 322, 633, 2167, 786, 13, 50733], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09151681057818524, "compression_ratio": 1.5925925925925926, "no_speech_prob": 2.080206232962789e-12}, {"id": 53, "seek": 18168, "start": 189.24, "end": 202.68, "text": " I mean, contemporary systems, our digital archives, our online encyclopedias, citation networks, the massive social platforms where we spend all our time, they are almost exclusively designed around the concept of preservation.", "tokens": [50743, 286, 914, 11, 14878, 3652, 11, 527, 4562, 25607, 11, 527, 2950, 465, 34080, 27277, 4609, 11, 45590, 9590, 11, 264, 5994, 2093, 9473, 689, 321, 3496, 439, 527, 565, 11, 436, 366, 1920, 20638, 4761, 926, 264, 3410, 295, 27257, 13, 51415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09151681057818524, "compression_ratio": 1.5925925925925926, "no_speech_prob": 2.080206232962789e-12}, {"id": 54, "seek": 20268, "start": 202.68, "end": 203.44, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 55, "seek": 20268, "start": 203.96, "end": 204.82, "text": " Just keeping the data.", "tokens": [50429, 1449, 5145, 264, 1412, 13, 50472], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 56, "seek": 20268, "start": 204.92000000000002, "end": 205.32, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50477, 7587, 13, 50497], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 57, "seek": 20268, "start": 205.84, "end": 213.66, "text": " Their primary engineering metric is ensuring that a document or a page or a user database is retained on a server somewhere.", "tokens": [50523, 6710, 6194, 7043, 20678, 307, 16882, 300, 257, 4166, 420, 257, 3028, 420, 257, 4195, 8149, 307, 33438, 322, 257, 7154, 4079, 13, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 58, "seek": 20268, "start": 213.88, "end": 220.70000000000002, "text": " But Flyxion's paper argues, quite forcefully, actually, that preservation is the completely wrong goal.", "tokens": [50925, 583, 3235, 4105, 311, 3035, 38218, 11, 1596, 3464, 2277, 11, 767, 11, 300, 27257, 307, 264, 2584, 2085, 3387, 13, 51266], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 59, "seek": 20268, "start": 220.96, "end": 221.86, "text": " The wrong goal.", "tokens": [51279, 440, 2085, 3387, 13, 51324], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 60, "seek": 20268, "start": 222.18, "end": 222.48000000000002, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51340, 865, 13, 51355], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 61, "seek": 20268, "start": 222.9, "end": 227.08, "text": " Or, to use the terminology from the paper, it's the wrong invariant.", "tokens": [51376, 1610, 11, 281, 764, 264, 27575, 490, 264, 3035, 11, 309, 311, 264, 2085, 33270, 394, 13, 51585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23461327654250125, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.7615466337282957e-12}, {"id": 62, "seek": 22708, "start": 227.08, "end": 235.18, "text": " The core thesis here is profoundly unsettling when you think about the terabytes of data we generate.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4965, 22288, 510, 307, 39954, 43964, 1688, 562, 291, 519, 466, 264, 1796, 24538, 295, 1412, 321, 8460, 13, 50770], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 63, "seek": 22708, "start": 235.98000000000002, "end": 242.34, "text": " The thesis is that a system can remember perfectly while being completely and utterly unable to recall.", "tokens": [50810, 440, 22288, 307, 300, 257, 1185, 393, 1604, 6239, 1339, 885, 2584, 293, 30251, 11299, 281, 9901, 13, 51128], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 64, "seek": 22708, "start": 242.56, "end": 243.12, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51139, 1033, 13, 51167], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 65, "seek": 22708, "start": 243.20000000000002, "end": 244.10000000000002, "text": " Let's unpack this.", "tokens": [51171, 961, 311, 26699, 341, 13, 51216], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 66, "seek": 22708, "start": 244.60000000000002, "end": 248.9, "text": " Because that phrasing is so specific and so counterintuitive.", "tokens": [51241, 1436, 300, 7636, 3349, 307, 370, 2685, 293, 370, 5682, 686, 48314, 13, 51456], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 67, "seek": 22708, "start": 249.68, "end": 252.4, "text": " Remembering perfectly but being unable to recall.", "tokens": [51495, 5459, 278, 6239, 457, 885, 11299, 281, 9901, 13, 51631], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 68, "seek": 22708, "start": 252.56, "end": 252.82000000000002, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51639, 1779, 13, 51652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21882389292997473, "compression_ratio": 1.5863636363636364, "no_speech_prob": 1.7214527329653673e-12}, {"id": 69, "seek": 25282, "start": 252.82, "end": 258.65999999999997, "text": " We treat those as synonyms in daily life, you know, like if I remember it, I could recall it.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 2387, 729, 382, 5451, 2526, 2592, 294, 5212, 993, 11, 291, 458, 11, 411, 498, 286, 1604, 309, 11, 286, 727, 9901, 309, 13, 50657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 70, "seek": 25282, "start": 259.08, "end": 270.12, "text": " To understand why our massive digital libraries are essentially losing their catalogs, we first need to define the hidden architecture of how we actually find things in the first place.", "tokens": [50678, 1407, 1223, 983, 527, 5994, 4562, 15148, 366, 4476, 7027, 641, 19746, 82, 11, 321, 700, 643, 281, 6964, 264, 7633, 9482, 295, 577, 321, 767, 915, 721, 294, 264, 700, 1081, 13, 51230], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 71, "seek": 25282, "start": 270.26, "end": 270.42, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51237, 1779, 13, 51245], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 72, "seek": 25282, "start": 270.5, "end": 271.56, "text": " The mechanics of it.", "tokens": [51249, 440, 12939, 295, 309, 13, 51302], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 73, "seek": 25282, "start": 271.64, "end": 271.82, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51306, 865, 13, 51315], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 74, "seek": 25282, "start": 272.52, "end": 275.7, "text": " And the paper doesn't just use metaphors like our library.", "tokens": [51350, 400, 264, 3035, 1177, 380, 445, 764, 30946, 830, 411, 527, 6405, 13, 51509], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 75, "seek": 25282, "start": 275.86, "end": 277.9, "text": " It uses formal mathematical structures.", "tokens": [51517, 467, 4960, 9860, 18894, 9227, 13, 51619], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 76, "seek": 25282, "start": 278.1, "end": 278.28, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51629, 1779, 13, 51638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 77, "seek": 25282, "start": 278.32, "end": 280.9, "text": " It introduces this idea of a directed graph.", "tokens": [51640, 467, 31472, 341, 1558, 295, 257, 12898, 4295, 13, 51769], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12836628286247578, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 2.334240222987005e-12}, {"id": 78, "seek": 28090, "start": 280.9, "end": 285.03999999999996, "text": " Now, I know that sounds like something from, I don't know, an advanced computer science seminar.", "tokens": [50365, 823, 11, 286, 458, 300, 3263, 411, 746, 490, 11, 286, 500, 380, 458, 11, 364, 7339, 3820, 3497, 29235, 13, 50572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 79, "seek": 28090, "start": 285.26, "end": 290.58, "text": " But it's actually incredibly intuitive once we break it down into its two basic parts.", "tokens": [50583, 583, 309, 311, 767, 6252, 21769, 1564, 321, 1821, 309, 760, 666, 1080, 732, 3875, 3166, 13, 50849], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 80, "seek": 28090, "start": 291.32, "end": 291.97999999999996, "text": " It really is.", "tokens": [50886, 467, 534, 307, 13, 50919], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 81, "seek": 28090, "start": 292.09999999999997, "end": 306.88, "text": " So, in the paper, a semantic system, which is just a broad term for any system of meaning from a physical library to the entirety of the internet itself, is described as a set of two fundamental things.", "tokens": [50925, 407, 11, 294, 264, 3035, 11, 257, 47982, 1185, 11, 597, 307, 445, 257, 4152, 1433, 337, 604, 1185, 295, 3620, 490, 257, 4001, 6405, 281, 264, 31557, 295, 264, 4705, 2564, 11, 307, 7619, 382, 257, 992, 295, 732, 8088, 721, 13, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 82, "seek": 28090, "start": 306.97999999999996, "end": 307.23999999999995, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51669, 1033, 13, 51682], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 83, "seek": 28090, "start": 307.52, "end": 307.9, "text": " What are they?", "tokens": [51696, 708, 366, 436, 30, 51715], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 84, "seek": 28090, "start": 308.23999999999995, "end": 310.28, "text": " First, there is a set of states.", "tokens": [51732, 2386, 11, 456, 307, 257, 992, 295, 4368, 13, 51834], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10474395751953125, "compression_ratio": 1.592982456140351, "no_speech_prob": 1.561059007754162e-12}, {"id": 85, "seek": 31028, "start": 310.28, "end": 312.79999999999995, "text": " You can think of these as the nodes in a network.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 393, 519, 295, 613, 382, 264, 13891, 294, 257, 3209, 13, 50491], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18711394995031222, "compression_ratio": 1.4702380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722625466505711e-12}, {"id": 86, "seek": 31028, "start": 313.38, "end": 315.97999999999996, "text": " A state is the actual semantic content.", "tokens": [50520, 316, 1785, 307, 264, 3539, 47982, 2701, 13, 50650], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18711394995031222, "compression_ratio": 1.4702380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722625466505711e-12}, {"id": 87, "seek": 31028, "start": 316.26, "end": 324.15999999999997, "text": " It's a specific web page, a digital file, a book, a photograph, or even just a specific human memory.", "tokens": [50664, 467, 311, 257, 2685, 3670, 3028, 11, 257, 4562, 3991, 11, 257, 1446, 11, 257, 8348, 11, 420, 754, 445, 257, 2685, 1952, 4675, 13, 51059], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18711394995031222, "compression_ratio": 1.4702380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722625466505711e-12}, {"id": 88, "seek": 31028, "start": 324.4, "end": 327.05999999999995, "text": " So, the state is the thing itself, the object.", "tokens": [51071, 407, 11, 264, 1785, 307, 264, 551, 2564, 11, 264, 2657, 13, 51204], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18711394995031222, "compression_ratio": 1.4702380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722625466505711e-12}, {"id": 89, "seek": 31028, "start": 327.28, "end": 327.7, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51215, 7587, 13, 51236], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18711394995031222, "compression_ratio": 1.4702380952380953, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722625466505711e-12}, {"id": 90, "seek": 32770, "start": 327.7, "end": 332.88, "text": " And second, and this is where it gets interesting, there is a set of transformations.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 1150, 11, 293, 341, 307, 689, 309, 2170, 1880, 11, 456, 307, 257, 992, 295, 34852, 13, 50624], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19277891565541752, "compression_ratio": 1.5870967741935484, "no_speech_prob": 1.4604565386905355e-12}, {"id": 91, "seek": 32770, "start": 333.18, "end": 334.8, "text": " These are the edges in the network.", "tokens": [50639, 1981, 366, 264, 8819, 294, 264, 3209, 13, 50720], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19277891565541752, "compression_ratio": 1.5870967741935484, "no_speech_prob": 1.4604565386905355e-12}, {"id": 92, "seek": 32770, "start": 335.32, "end": 341.44, "text": " A transformation is any valid action you can take to move from one state to another.", "tokens": [50746, 316, 9887, 307, 604, 7363, 3069, 291, 393, 747, 281, 1286, 490, 472, 1785, 281, 1071, 13, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19277891565541752, "compression_ratio": 1.5870967741935484, "no_speech_prob": 1.4604565386905355e-12}, {"id": 93, "seek": 32770, "start": 341.71999999999997, "end": 343.36, "text": " Give me an example of a transformation.", "tokens": [51066, 5303, 385, 364, 1365, 295, 257, 9887, 13, 51148], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19277891565541752, "compression_ratio": 1.5870967741935484, "no_speech_prob": 1.4604565386905355e-12}, {"id": 94, "seek": 34336, "start": 343.36, "end": 343.8, "text": " Sure.", "tokens": [50365, 4894, 13, 50387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21340721675327845, "compression_ratio": 1.5224719101123596, "no_speech_prob": 1.8606310069058107e-12}, {"id": 95, "seek": 34336, "start": 343.8, "end": 346.42, "text": " So, clicking a hyperlink is a transformation.", "tokens": [50387, 407, 11, 9697, 257, 9848, 22473, 307, 257, 9887, 13, 50518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21340721675327845, "compression_ratio": 1.5224719101123596, "no_speech_prob": 1.8606310069058107e-12}, {"id": 96, "seek": 34336, "start": 346.68, "end": 347.04, "text": " Oh, okay.", "tokens": [50531, 876, 11, 1392, 13, 50549], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21340721675327845, "compression_ratio": 1.5224719101123596, "no_speech_prob": 1.8606310069058107e-12}, {"id": 97, "seek": 34336, "start": 347.46000000000004, "end": 349.7, "text": " Querying a search index is a transformation.", "tokens": [50570, 2326, 2109, 278, 257, 3164, 8186, 307, 257, 9887, 13, 50682], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21340721675327845, "compression_ratio": 1.5224719101123596, "no_speech_prob": 1.8606310069058107e-12}, {"id": 98, "seek": 34336, "start": 350.06, "end": 359.96000000000004, "text": " Looking up a citation in a bibliography, translating a text from French to English, or even just the mental act of recalling something from a previous conversation.", "tokens": [50700, 11053, 493, 257, 45590, 294, 257, 34344, 5820, 11, 35030, 257, 2487, 490, 5522, 281, 3669, 11, 420, 754, 445, 264, 4973, 605, 295, 9901, 278, 746, 490, 257, 3894, 3761, 13, 51195], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21340721675327845, "compression_ratio": 1.5224719101123596, "no_speech_prob": 1.8606310069058107e-12}, {"id": 99, "seek": 35996, "start": 359.96, "end": 361.84, "text": " Those are all transformations.", "tokens": [50365, 3950, 366, 439, 34852, 13, 50459], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13896292828499002, "compression_ratio": 1.5765765765765767, "no_speech_prob": 1.244326907137716e-12}, {"id": 100, "seek": 35996, "start": 361.84, "end": 367.62, "text": " So, information isn't just a giant bucket of isolated files sitting in a vacuum waiting for us.", "tokens": [50459, 407, 11, 1589, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 7410, 13058, 295, 14621, 7098, 3798, 294, 257, 14224, 3806, 337, 505, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13896292828499002, "compression_ratio": 1.5765765765765767, "no_speech_prob": 1.244326907137716e-12}, {"id": 101, "seek": 35996, "start": 367.73999999999995, "end": 368.9, "text": " No, not at all.", "tokens": [50754, 883, 11, 406, 412, 439, 13, 50812], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13896292828499002, "compression_ratio": 1.5765765765765767, "no_speech_prob": 1.244326907137716e-12}, {"id": 102, "seek": 35996, "start": 369.26, "end": 370.47999999999996, "text": " It is a network, right?", "tokens": [50830, 467, 307, 257, 3209, 11, 558, 30, 50891], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13896292828499002, "compression_ratio": 1.5765765765765767, "no_speech_prob": 1.244326907137716e-12}, {"id": 103, "seek": 35996, "start": 370.58, "end": 383.28, "text": " A directed graph made of these nodes, the files or the states, and the edges, which are the literal paths we take to get from where we are to where the information is.", "tokens": [50896, 316, 12898, 4295, 1027, 295, 613, 13891, 11, 264, 7098, 420, 264, 4368, 11, 293, 264, 8819, 11, 597, 366, 264, 20411, 14518, 321, 747, 281, 483, 490, 689, 321, 366, 281, 689, 264, 1589, 307, 13, 51531], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13896292828499002, "compression_ratio": 1.5765765765765767, "no_speech_prob": 1.244326907137716e-12}, {"id": 104, "seek": 35996, "start": 383.32, "end": 383.91999999999996, "text": " That's spot on.", "tokens": [51533, 663, 311, 4008, 322, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13896292828499002, "compression_ratio": 1.5765765765765767, "no_speech_prob": 1.244326907137716e-12}, {"id": 105, "seek": 38392, "start": 383.92, "end": 387.38, "text": " Which brings us to the core distinction the author makes.", "tokens": [50365, 3013, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 4965, 16844, 264, 3793, 1669, 13, 50538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 106, "seek": 38392, "start": 388.06, "end": 392.64000000000004, "text": " And honestly, this is the pivot point for everything we are going to explore today.", "tokens": [50572, 400, 6095, 11, 341, 307, 264, 14538, 935, 337, 1203, 321, 366, 516, 281, 6839, 965, 13, 50801], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 107, "seek": 38392, "start": 392.86, "end": 396.58000000000004, "text": " The difference between preservation and reachability.", "tokens": [50812, 440, 2649, 1296, 27257, 293, 2524, 2310, 13, 50998], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 108, "seek": 38392, "start": 396.84000000000003, "end": 396.98, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51011, 1779, 13, 51018], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 109, "seek": 38392, "start": 397.18, "end": 403.66, "text": " So, preservation is simply the property that a state, a node, continues to exist over time.", "tokens": [51028, 407, 11, 27257, 307, 2935, 264, 4707, 300, 257, 1785, 11, 257, 9984, 11, 6515, 281, 2514, 670, 565, 13, 51352], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 110, "seek": 38392, "start": 403.78000000000003, "end": 404.66, "text": " It's still on the server.", "tokens": [51358, 467, 311, 920, 322, 264, 7154, 13, 51402], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 111, "seek": 38392, "start": 404.88, "end": 405.36, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51413, 7587, 13, 51437], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 112, "seek": 38392, "start": 405.8, "end": 407.88, "text": " It means the file is intact.", "tokens": [51459, 467, 1355, 264, 3991, 307, 23493, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 113, "seek": 38392, "start": 408.52000000000004, "end": 410.20000000000005, "text": " The database hasn't been corrupted.", "tokens": [51595, 440, 8149, 6132, 380, 668, 39480, 13, 51679], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1814496635210396, "compression_ratio": 1.5634920634920635, "no_speech_prob": 1.340799975386997e-12}, {"id": 114, "seek": 41020, "start": 410.2, "end": 414.52, "text": " The node is still physically or digitally somewhere in the graph.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 9984, 307, 920, 9762, 420, 36938, 4079, 294, 264, 4295, 13, 50581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10554753409491645, "compression_ratio": 1.584033613445378, "no_speech_prob": 1.3460513086094306e-12}, {"id": 115, "seek": 41020, "start": 415.58, "end": 424.88, "text": " Reachability, on the other hand, is the property that a state remains navigable from where you are right now using the transformations that are actually available to you.", "tokens": [50634, 35904, 2310, 11, 322, 264, 661, 1011, 11, 307, 264, 4707, 300, 257, 1785, 7023, 7407, 712, 490, 689, 291, 366, 558, 586, 1228, 264, 34852, 300, 366, 767, 2435, 281, 291, 13, 51099], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10554753409491645, "compression_ratio": 1.584033613445378, "no_speech_prob": 1.3460513086094306e-12}, {"id": 116, "seek": 41020, "start": 424.98, "end": 425.18, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51104, 1033, 13, 51114], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10554753409491645, "compression_ratio": 1.584033613445378, "no_speech_prob": 1.3460513086094306e-12}, {"id": 117, "seek": 41020, "start": 425.28, "end": 426.58, "text": " So, there's an unbroken path.", "tokens": [51119, 407, 11, 456, 311, 364, 517, 37947, 3100, 13, 51184], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10554753409491645, "compression_ratio": 1.584033613445378, "no_speech_prob": 1.3460513086094306e-12}, {"id": 118, "seek": 41020, "start": 426.71999999999997, "end": 427.03999999999996, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51191, 1079, 13, 51207], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10554753409491645, "compression_ratio": 1.584033613445378, "no_speech_prob": 1.3460513086094306e-12}, {"id": 119, "seek": 41020, "start": 427.52, "end": 435.06, "text": " It means there is a continuous directed path from your current state to that past semantic content.", "tokens": [51231, 467, 1355, 456, 307, 257, 10957, 12898, 3100, 490, 428, 2190, 1785, 281, 300, 1791, 47982, 2701, 13, 51608], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10554753409491645, "compression_ratio": 1.584033613445378, "no_speech_prob": 1.3460513086094306e-12}, {"id": 120, "seek": 43506, "start": 435.06, "end": 447.98, "text": " It's like assuming a town still exists, because you can see it clearly marked on a map, but failing to realize that the only bridge spanning the gorge to actually get there washed out 10 years ago.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 411, 11926, 257, 3954, 920, 8198, 11, 570, 291, 393, 536, 309, 4448, 12658, 322, 257, 4471, 11, 457, 18223, 281, 4325, 300, 264, 787, 7283, 47626, 264, 290, 4685, 281, 767, 483, 456, 16300, 484, 1266, 924, 2057, 13, 51011], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1941387714483799, "compression_ratio": 1.5148514851485149, "no_speech_prob": 2.218988231009189e-12}, {"id": 121, "seek": 43506, "start": 448.16, "end": 450.0, "text": " That is a perfect analogy.", "tokens": [51020, 663, 307, 257, 2176, 21663, 13, 51112], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1941387714483799, "compression_ratio": 1.5148514851485149, "no_speech_prob": 2.218988231009189e-12}, {"id": 122, "seek": 43506, "start": 450.52, "end": 451.72, "text": " The town is preserved.", "tokens": [51138, 440, 3954, 307, 22242, 13, 51198], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1941387714483799, "compression_ratio": 1.5148514851485149, "no_speech_prob": 2.218988231009189e-12}, {"id": 123, "seek": 43506, "start": 452.38, "end": 453.56, "text": " The buildings are there.", "tokens": [51231, 440, 7446, 366, 456, 13, 51290], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1941387714483799, "compression_ratio": 1.5148514851485149, "no_speech_prob": 2.218988231009189e-12}, {"id": 124, "seek": 43506, "start": 453.92, "end": 455.92, "text": " The coffee shop is fully stocked.", "tokens": [51308, 440, 4982, 3945, 307, 4498, 4127, 292, 13, 51408], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1941387714483799, "compression_ratio": 1.5148514851485149, "no_speech_prob": 2.218988231009189e-12}, {"id": 125, "seek": 45592, "start": 455.92, "end": 463.54, "text": " But for all practical intents and purposes, it is completely unreachable to anyone trying to drive there today.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 337, 439, 8496, 560, 791, 293, 9932, 11, 309, 307, 2584, 517, 16226, 712, 281, 2878, 1382, 281, 3332, 456, 965, 13, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13551292419433594, "compression_ratio": 1.5867158671586716, "no_speech_prob": 1.6165660390171643e-12}, {"id": 126, "seek": 45592, "start": 464.12, "end": 467.66, "text": " And that analogy touches on the exact mechanism at play here.", "tokens": [50775, 400, 300, 21663, 17431, 322, 264, 1900, 7513, 412, 862, 510, 13, 50952], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13551292419433594, "compression_ratio": 1.5867158671586716, "no_speech_prob": 1.6165660390171643e-12}, {"id": 127, "seek": 45592, "start": 468.44, "end": 473.62, "text": " The central claim of Flyxion's paper is that a system can absolutely preserve elements.", "tokens": [50991, 440, 5777, 3932, 295, 3235, 4105, 311, 3035, 307, 300, 257, 1185, 393, 3122, 15665, 4959, 13, 51250], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13551292419433594, "compression_ratio": 1.5867158671586716, "no_speech_prob": 1.6165660390171643e-12}, {"id": 128, "seek": 45592, "start": 474.18, "end": 480.56, "text": " It can keep those towns intact indefinitely while completely destroying the path structure of the graph.", "tokens": [51278, 467, 393, 1066, 729, 18104, 23493, 24162, 10925, 1339, 2584, 19926, 264, 3100, 3877, 295, 264, 4295, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13551292419433594, "compression_ratio": 1.5867158671586716, "no_speech_prob": 1.6165660390171643e-12}, {"id": 129, "seek": 45592, "start": 480.8, "end": 483.8, "text": " So, the towns are fine, but all the bridges are gone.", "tokens": [51609, 407, 11, 264, 18104, 366, 2489, 11, 457, 439, 264, 21114, 366, 2780, 13, 51759], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13551292419433594, "compression_ratio": 1.5867158671586716, "no_speech_prob": 1.6165660390171643e-12}, {"id": 130, "seek": 45592, "start": 484.20000000000005, "end": 484.8, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51779, 7587, 13, 51809], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13551292419433594, "compression_ratio": 1.5867158671586716, "no_speech_prob": 1.6165660390171643e-12}, {"id": 131, "seek": 48480, "start": 484.8, "end": 488.86, "text": " The preserved states become totally unreachable from the present.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 22242, 4368, 1813, 3879, 517, 16226, 712, 490, 264, 1974, 13, 50568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12020089076115535, "compression_ratio": 1.6007462686567164, "no_speech_prob": 1.5918460126440603e-12}, {"id": 132, "seek": 48480, "start": 489.62, "end": 493.92, "text": " And this isn't some theoretical paradox relegated to academic journals.", "tokens": [50606, 400, 341, 1943, 380, 512, 20864, 26221, 2951, 70, 770, 281, 7778, 29621, 13, 50821], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12020089076115535, "compression_ratio": 1.6007462686567164, "no_speech_prob": 1.5918460126440603e-12}, {"id": 133, "seek": 48480, "start": 494.26, "end": 502.66, "text": " It's a structural observation about how our modern digital ecosystems are actually engineered and how they are actively failing.", "tokens": [50838, 467, 311, 257, 15067, 14816, 466, 577, 527, 4363, 4562, 32647, 366, 767, 38648, 293, 577, 436, 366, 13022, 18223, 13, 51258], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12020089076115535, "compression_ratio": 1.6007462686567164, "no_speech_prob": 1.5918460126440603e-12}, {"id": 134, "seek": 48480, "start": 503.22, "end": 506.5, "text": " But wait, haven't information theorists figured this out already?", "tokens": [51286, 583, 1699, 11, 2378, 380, 1589, 27423, 1751, 8932, 341, 484, 1217, 30, 51450], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12020089076115535, "compression_ratio": 1.6007462686567164, "no_speech_prob": 1.5918460126440603e-12}, {"id": 135, "seek": 48480, "start": 506.96000000000004, "end": 511.72, "text": " I mean, a lot of people listening probably assume that the tech giants have already solved this.", "tokens": [51473, 286, 914, 11, 257, 688, 295, 561, 4764, 1391, 6552, 300, 264, 7553, 31894, 362, 1217, 13041, 341, 13, 51711], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12020089076115535, "compression_ratio": 1.6007462686567164, "no_speech_prob": 1.5918460126440603e-12}, {"id": 136, "seek": 51172, "start": 511.72, "end": 515.96, "text": " We think of Google or Amazon Web Services as having infallible memories.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 519, 295, 3329, 420, 6795, 9573, 12124, 382, 1419, 1536, 336, 964, 8495, 13, 50577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18330177507902445, "compression_ratio": 1.4193548387096775, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321960702089024e-12}, {"id": 137, "seek": 51172, "start": 516.5400000000001, "end": 517.88, "text": " Why is this a new problem?", "tokens": [50606, 1545, 307, 341, 257, 777, 1154, 30, 50673], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18330177507902445, "compression_ratio": 1.4193548387096775, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321960702089024e-12}, {"id": 138, "seek": 51172, "start": 518.32, "end": 519.72, "text": " You would certainly assume that.", "tokens": [50695, 509, 576, 3297, 6552, 300, 13, 50765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18330177507902445, "compression_ratio": 1.4193548387096775, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321960702089024e-12}, {"id": 139, "seek": 51172, "start": 520.3000000000001, "end": 529.86, "text": " But the theoretical foundations of information science actually have a massive historical blind spot regarding time and navigation.", "tokens": [50794, 583, 264, 20864, 22467, 295, 1589, 3497, 767, 362, 257, 5994, 8584, 6865, 4008, 8595, 565, 293, 17346, 13, 51272], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18330177507902445, "compression_ratio": 1.4193548387096775, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321960702089024e-12}, {"id": 140, "seek": 52986, "start": 529.86, "end": 530.34, "text": " Really?", "tokens": [50365, 4083, 30, 50389], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.27710299058394, "compression_ratio": 1.343915343915344, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980364155374296e-12}, {"id": 141, "seek": 52986, "start": 530.34, "end": 530.38, "text": " Really?", "tokens": [50389, 4083, 30, 50391], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.27710299058394, "compression_ratio": 1.343915343915344, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980364155374296e-12}, {"id": 142, "seek": 52986, "start": 530.6, "end": 531.0, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50402, 865, 13, 50422], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.27710299058394, "compression_ratio": 1.343915343915344, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980364155374296e-12}, {"id": 143, "seek": 52986, "start": 531.36, "end": 536.72, "text": " The paper brings up two giants in the field to illustrate why we build systems this way.", "tokens": [50440, 440, 3035, 5607, 493, 732, 31894, 294, 264, 2519, 281, 23221, 983, 321, 1322, 3652, 341, 636, 13, 50708], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.27710299058394, "compression_ratio": 1.343915343915344, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980364155374296e-12}, {"id": 144, "seek": 52986, "start": 537.32, "end": 539.38, "text": " First, there is Claude Shannon.", "tokens": [50738, 2386, 11, 456, 307, 12947, 2303, 28974, 13, 50841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.27710299058394, "compression_ratio": 1.343915343915344, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980364155374296e-12}, {"id": 145, "seek": 52986, "start": 540.1, "end": 548.36, "text": " In 1948, Shannon published his Mathematical Theory of Communication, which introduced the famous channel model.", "tokens": [50877, 682, 38833, 11, 28974, 6572, 702, 15776, 8615, 804, 29009, 295, 34930, 11, 597, 7268, 264, 4618, 2269, 2316, 13, 51290], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.27710299058394, "compression_ratio": 1.343915343915344, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980364155374296e-12}, {"id": 146, "seek": 54836, "start": 548.36, "end": 551.32, "text": " Right, the bedrock of modern digital communication.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 11, 264, 2901, 17799, 295, 4363, 4562, 6101, 13, 50513], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2035475404638993, "compression_ratio": 1.4207920792079207, "no_speech_prob": 1.635625662688156e-12}, {"id": 147, "seek": 54836, "start": 551.38, "end": 551.9, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50516, 7587, 13, 50542], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2035475404638993, "compression_ratio": 1.4207920792079207, "no_speech_prob": 1.635625662688156e-12}, {"id": 148, "seek": 54836, "start": 552.52, "end": 557.6800000000001, "text": " Every time you send a text message or stream a video, you are relying on Shannon's math.", "tokens": [50573, 2048, 565, 291, 2845, 257, 2487, 3636, 420, 4309, 257, 960, 11, 291, 366, 24140, 322, 28974, 311, 5221, 13, 50831], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2035475404638993, "compression_ratio": 1.4207920792079207, "no_speech_prob": 1.635625662688156e-12}, {"id": 149, "seek": 54836, "start": 558.48, "end": 561.5, "text": " But we have to look at what Shannon was actually trying to solve.", "tokens": [50871, 583, 321, 362, 281, 574, 412, 437, 28974, 390, 767, 1382, 281, 5039, 13, 51022], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2035475404638993, "compression_ratio": 1.4207920792079207, "no_speech_prob": 1.635625662688156e-12}, {"id": 150, "seek": 54836, "start": 561.64, "end": 565.86, "text": " He was working at Bell Labs and his concern was telephony.", "tokens": [51029, 634, 390, 1364, 412, 11485, 40047, 293, 702, 3136, 390, 4304, 28616, 13, 51240], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2035475404638993, "compression_ratio": 1.4207920792079207, "no_speech_prob": 1.635625662688156e-12}, {"id": 151, "seek": 54836, "start": 566.02, "end": 566.62, "text": " Phone lines.", "tokens": [51248, 30713, 3876, 13, 51278], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2035475404638993, "compression_ratio": 1.4207920792079207, "no_speech_prob": 1.635625662688156e-12}, {"id": 152, "seek": 56662, "start": 566.62, "end": 567.22, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13595110575358074, "compression_ratio": 1.5146443514644352, "no_speech_prob": 1.6298397093744699e-12}, {"id": 153, "seek": 56662, "start": 567.82, "end": 577.34, "text": " He needed to know, if I send a message from point A to point B right now over a noisy copper wire, does it arrive perfectly intact on the other end?", "tokens": [50425, 634, 2978, 281, 458, 11, 498, 286, 2845, 257, 3636, 490, 935, 316, 281, 935, 363, 558, 586, 670, 257, 24518, 15007, 6234, 11, 775, 309, 8881, 6239, 23493, 322, 264, 661, 917, 30, 50901], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13595110575358074, "compression_ratio": 1.5146443514644352, "no_speech_prob": 1.6298397093744699e-12}, {"id": 154, "seek": 56662, "start": 577.68, "end": 580.98, "text": " So he was totally focused on transmission fidelity.", "tokens": [50918, 407, 415, 390, 3879, 5178, 322, 11574, 46404, 13, 51083], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13595110575358074, "compression_ratio": 1.5146443514644352, "no_speech_prob": 1.6298397093744699e-12}, {"id": 155, "seek": 56662, "start": 581.18, "end": 584.24, "text": " Getting the signal through the noise in the present moment.", "tokens": [51093, 13674, 264, 6358, 807, 264, 5658, 294, 264, 1974, 1623, 13, 51246], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13595110575358074, "compression_ratio": 1.5146443514644352, "no_speech_prob": 1.6298397093744699e-12}, {"id": 156, "seek": 56662, "start": 584.98, "end": 588.58, "text": " He wasn't worried about whether someone could find that phone call 50 years later.", "tokens": [51283, 634, 2067, 380, 5804, 466, 1968, 1580, 727, 915, 300, 2593, 818, 2625, 924, 1780, 13, 51463], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13595110575358074, "compression_ratio": 1.5146443514644352, "no_speech_prob": 1.6298397093744699e-12}, {"id": 157, "seek": 56662, "start": 588.92, "end": 589.6, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [51480, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13595110575358074, "compression_ratio": 1.5146443514644352, "no_speech_prob": 1.6298397093744699e-12}, {"id": 158, "seek": 58960, "start": 589.6, "end": 596.1, "text": " He explicitly bracketed out the semantic meaning of the message and the temporal decay of paths.", "tokens": [50365, 634, 20803, 12305, 10993, 484, 264, 47982, 3620, 295, 264, 3636, 293, 264, 30881, 21039, 295, 14518, 13, 50690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16915761906167734, "compression_ratio": 1.6030534351145038, "no_speech_prob": 1.4497484159339824e-12}, {"id": 159, "seek": 58960, "start": 596.4200000000001, "end": 600.76, "text": " He just cared about the accurate transfer of bits across space.", "tokens": [50706, 634, 445, 19779, 466, 264, 8559, 5003, 295, 9239, 2108, 1901, 13, 50923], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16915761906167734, "compression_ratio": 1.6030534351145038, "no_speech_prob": 1.4497484159339824e-12}, {"id": 160, "seek": 58960, "start": 601.32, "end": 603.84, "text": " Okay, so that's Shannon, who's the second giant.", "tokens": [50951, 1033, 11, 370, 300, 311, 28974, 11, 567, 311, 264, 1150, 7410, 13, 51077], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16915761906167734, "compression_ratio": 1.6030534351145038, "no_speech_prob": 1.4497484159339824e-12}, {"id": 161, "seek": 58960, "start": 604.7, "end": 608.96, "text": " Then, on the other side of the spectrum, the paper mentions Luciana Flority,", "tokens": [51120, 1396, 11, 322, 264, 661, 1252, 295, 264, 11143, 11, 264, 3035, 23844, 37309, 2095, 8328, 507, 11, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16915761906167734, "compression_ratio": 1.6030534351145038, "no_speech_prob": 1.4497484159339824e-12}, {"id": 162, "seek": 58960, "start": 608.96, "end": 618.72, "text": " whose highly influential 2011 work on the philosophy of information treats information fundamentally as meaningful and truthful data.", "tokens": [51333, 6104, 5405, 22215, 10154, 589, 322, 264, 10675, 295, 1589, 19566, 1589, 17879, 382, 10995, 293, 44669, 1412, 13, 51821], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16915761906167734, "compression_ratio": 1.6030534351145038, "no_speech_prob": 1.4497484159339824e-12}, {"id": 163, "seek": 61872, "start": 618.72, "end": 622.26, "text": " So Flority actually cares about what the data means.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 8328, 507, 767, 12310, 466, 437, 264, 1412, 1355, 13, 50542], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 164, "seek": 61872, "start": 622.4, "end": 622.72, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50549, 1079, 13, 50565], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 165, "seek": 61872, "start": 623.4200000000001, "end": 628.52, "text": " Flority cares deeply about the semantic content, the actual meaning that Shannon ignored.", "tokens": [50600, 8328, 507, 12310, 8760, 466, 264, 47982, 2701, 11, 264, 3539, 3620, 300, 28974, 19735, 13, 50855], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 166, "seek": 61872, "start": 629.1, "end": 636.24, "text": " But, as Flyxion points out, in Flority's framework, the question of access to that information is largely treated as a given.", "tokens": [50884, 583, 11, 382, 3235, 970, 313, 2793, 484, 11, 294, 8328, 507, 311, 8388, 11, 264, 1168, 295, 2105, 281, 300, 1589, 307, 11611, 8668, 382, 257, 2212, 13, 51241], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 167, "seek": 61872, "start": 636.4, "end": 638.08, "text": " He just assumes you have the book in your hand.", "tokens": [51249, 634, 445, 37808, 291, 362, 264, 1446, 294, 428, 1011, 13, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 168, "seek": 61872, "start": 638.26, "end": 638.6800000000001, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51342, 7587, 13, 51363], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 169, "seek": 61872, "start": 638.86, "end": 641.58, "text": " It assumes you can already get to the document to read it.", "tokens": [51372, 467, 37808, 291, 393, 1217, 483, 281, 264, 4166, 281, 1401, 309, 13, 51508], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 170, "seek": 61872, "start": 641.58, "end": 647.0400000000001, "text": " What neither framework captures directly is the temporal and navigational dimension.", "tokens": [51508, 708, 9662, 8388, 27986, 3838, 307, 264, 30881, 293, 7407, 1478, 10139, 13, 51781], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 171, "seek": 61872, "start": 647.36, "end": 648.44, "text": " The element of time.", "tokens": [51797, 440, 4478, 295, 565, 13, 51851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16665884285918936, "compression_ratio": 1.706896551724138, "no_speech_prob": 1.7216053886312532e-12}, {"id": 172, "seek": 64872, "start": 648.72, "end": 651.94, "text": " The fact that the bridge can wash out?", "tokens": [50365, 440, 1186, 300, 264, 7283, 393, 5675, 484, 30, 50526], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 173, "seek": 64872, "start": 652.36, "end": 652.6800000000001, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50547, 1079, 13, 50563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 174, "seek": 64872, "start": 653.62, "end": 660.1, "text": " The critical question is whether a receiver in a future state, maybe 10 years from now, maybe 100,", "tokens": [50610, 440, 4924, 1168, 307, 1968, 257, 20086, 294, 257, 2027, 1785, 11, 1310, 1266, 924, 490, 586, 11, 1310, 2319, 11, 50934], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 175, "seek": 64872, "start": 660.46, "end": 665.1800000000001, "text": " can actually reconstruct the path back to a past message,", "tokens": [50952, 393, 767, 31499, 264, 3100, 646, 281, 257, 1791, 3636, 11, 51188], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 176, "seek": 64872, "start": 665.5, "end": 670.34, "text": " using only the transformations that are available to them at that future time.", "tokens": [51204, 1228, 787, 264, 34852, 300, 366, 2435, 281, 552, 412, 300, 2027, 565, 13, 51446], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 177, "seek": 64872, "start": 670.46, "end": 670.84, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [51452, 3153, 13, 51471], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 178, "seek": 64872, "start": 671.4, "end": 676.74, "text": " Reachability names this specific massive gap in our theories of knowledge.", "tokens": [51499, 35904, 2310, 5288, 341, 2685, 5994, 7417, 294, 527, 13667, 295, 3601, 13, 51766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.26305807720531116, "compression_ratio": 1.5276595744680852, "no_speech_prob": 2.2716342695794367e-12}, {"id": 179, "seek": 67674, "start": 676.74, "end": 684.52, "text": " We have optimized for storing bits accurately, and we have philosophized about what those bits mean.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 362, 26941, 337, 26085, 9239, 20095, 11, 293, 321, 362, 14529, 1602, 466, 437, 729, 9239, 914, 13, 50754], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17663588977995373, "compression_ratio": 1.3823529411764706, "no_speech_prob": 1.9201300705679047e-12}, {"id": 180, "seek": 67674, "start": 684.72, "end": 690.34, "text": " But we've completely ignored the fragile connective tissue that allows us to find them.", "tokens": [50764, 583, 321, 600, 2584, 19735, 264, 23847, 1745, 488, 12404, 300, 4045, 505, 281, 915, 552, 13, 51045], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17663588977995373, "compression_ratio": 1.3823529411764706, "no_speech_prob": 1.9201300705679047e-12}, {"id": 181, "seek": 69034, "start": 690.34, "end": 696.34, "text": " And because we haven't theoretically separated the concept of storage from the concept of navigation,", "tokens": [50365, 400, 570, 321, 2378, 380, 29400, 12005, 264, 3410, 295, 6725, 490, 264, 3410, 295, 17346, 11, 50665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14437330762545267, "compression_ratio": 1.6946564885496183, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308701572028238e-12}, {"id": 182, "seek": 69034, "start": 696.9, "end": 701.46, "text": " we build them separately, we fund them separately, and crucially, they fail separately.", "tokens": [50693, 321, 1322, 552, 14759, 11, 321, 2374, 552, 14759, 11, 293, 5140, 1909, 11, 436, 3061, 14759, 13, 50921], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14437330762545267, "compression_ratio": 1.6946564885496183, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308701572028238e-12}, {"id": 183, "seek": 69034, "start": 701.58, "end": 703.5, "text": " They absolutely fail separately.", "tokens": [50927, 814, 3122, 3061, 14759, 13, 51023], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14437330762545267, "compression_ratio": 1.6946564885496183, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308701572028238e-12}, {"id": 184, "seek": 70350, "start": 703.5, "end": 714.92, "text": " The paper points out that nodes, the storage and edges, the navigation, are maintained by entirely different engineering teams using completely different mechanisms.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3035, 2793, 484, 300, 13891, 11, 264, 6725, 293, 8819, 11, 264, 17346, 11, 366, 17578, 538, 7696, 819, 7043, 5491, 1228, 2584, 819, 15902, 13, 50936], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18221691419493477, "compression_ratio": 1.4825581395348837, "no_speech_prob": 1.8104611776773027e-12}, {"id": 185, "seek": 70350, "start": 715.24, "end": 715.34, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50952, 1779, 13, 50957], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18221691419493477, "compression_ratio": 1.4825581395348837, "no_speech_prob": 1.8104611776773027e-12}, {"id": 186, "seek": 70350, "start": 715.66, "end": 721.2, "text": " Preservation is handled by backup policies, archival standards, server redundancy.", "tokens": [50973, 2718, 6864, 307, 18033, 538, 14807, 7657, 11, 3912, 3576, 7787, 11, 7154, 27830, 6717, 13, 51250], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18221691419493477, "compression_ratio": 1.4825581395348837, "no_speech_prob": 1.8104611776773027e-12}, {"id": 187, "seek": 72120, "start": 721.2, "end": 724.0400000000001, "text": " If you want more preservation, you just throw money at it.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 291, 528, 544, 27257, 11, 291, 445, 3507, 1460, 412, 309, 13, 50507], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1144960948399135, "compression_ratio": 1.6115384615384616, "no_speech_prob": 1.7691755178905755e-12}, {"id": 188, "seek": 72120, "start": 724.12, "end": 727.38, "text": " You buy more hard drives, you build another server farm in a cooler climate.", "tokens": [50511, 509, 2256, 544, 1152, 11754, 11, 291, 1322, 1071, 7154, 5421, 294, 257, 15566, 5659, 13, 50674], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1144960948399135, "compression_ratio": 1.6115384615384616, "no_speech_prob": 1.7691755178905755e-12}, {"id": 189, "seek": 72120, "start": 727.5, "end": 728.7800000000001, "text": " Yeah, it's just a hardware problem.", "tokens": [50680, 865, 11, 309, 311, 445, 257, 8837, 1154, 13, 50744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1144960948399135, "compression_ratio": 1.6115384615384616, "no_speech_prob": 1.7691755178905755e-12}, {"id": 190, "seek": 72120, "start": 729.08, "end": 738.88, "text": " But reachability, reachability requires search indexing, citation linking, cross-referencing, naming consistency, algorithmic maintenance.", "tokens": [50759, 583, 2524, 2310, 11, 2524, 2310, 7029, 3164, 8186, 278, 11, 45590, 25775, 11, 3278, 12, 265, 612, 13644, 11, 25290, 14416, 11, 9284, 299, 11258, 13, 51249], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1144960948399135, "compression_ratio": 1.6115384615384616, "no_speech_prob": 1.7691755178905755e-12}, {"id": 191, "seek": 72120, "start": 739.44, "end": 746.7800000000001, "text": " Those are distinct engineering concerns, and they degrade in completely different, much more insidious ways.", "tokens": [51277, 3950, 366, 10644, 7043, 7389, 11, 293, 436, 368, 8692, 294, 2584, 819, 11, 709, 544, 1028, 327, 851, 2098, 13, 51644], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1144960948399135, "compression_ratio": 1.6115384615384616, "no_speech_prob": 1.7691755178905755e-12}, {"id": 192, "seek": 74678, "start": 746.78, "end": 761.0, "text": " And because they fail independently, we end up with these massive systemic breakdowns where everyone from the CEO of the platform down to the everyday user thinks the information is safe because the server uptime is 99.9%.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 570, 436, 3061, 21761, 11, 321, 917, 493, 365, 613, 5994, 23789, 18188, 82, 689, 1518, 490, 264, 9282, 295, 264, 3663, 760, 281, 264, 7429, 4195, 7309, 264, 1589, 307, 3273, 570, 264, 7154, 493, 3766, 307, 11803, 13, 24, 6856, 51076], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09743288159370422, "compression_ratio": 1.6194029850746268, "no_speech_prob": 1.868328842330458e-12}, {"id": 193, "seek": 74678, "start": 761.0, "end": 762.16, "text": " Right. The servers are fine.", "tokens": [51076, 1779, 13, 440, 15909, 366, 2489, 13, 51134], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09743288159370422, "compression_ratio": 1.6194029850746268, "no_speech_prob": 1.868328842330458e-12}, {"id": 194, "seek": 74678, "start": 762.3, "end": 763.5, "text": " The hard drives are humming.", "tokens": [51141, 440, 1152, 11754, 366, 34965, 13, 51201], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09743288159370422, "compression_ratio": 1.6194029850746268, "no_speech_prob": 1.868328842330458e-12}, {"id": 195, "seek": 74678, "start": 764.12, "end": 773.9599999999999, "text": " But the connections between the data points, the actual ways we traverse the graph to make sense of anything, are quietly rotting away in the background.", "tokens": [51232, 583, 264, 9271, 1296, 264, 1412, 2793, 11, 264, 3539, 2098, 321, 45674, 264, 4295, 281, 652, 2020, 295, 1340, 11, 366, 19141, 4297, 783, 1314, 294, 264, 3678, 13, 51724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09743288159370422, "compression_ratio": 1.6194029850746268, "no_speech_prob": 1.868328842330458e-12}, {"id": 196, "seek": 77396, "start": 773.96, "end": 778.5400000000001, "text": " So let's look at the specific failure modes happening right under our noses.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 718, 311, 574, 412, 264, 2685, 7763, 14068, 2737, 558, 833, 527, 3269, 279, 13, 50594], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956908915302542, "compression_ratio": 1.6931818181818181, "no_speech_prob": 2.4944781483460243e-12}, {"id": 197, "seek": 77396, "start": 778.9200000000001, "end": 784.46, "text": " Let's look at how human consensus and platform design actually weaponize this flaw.", "tokens": [50613, 961, 311, 574, 412, 577, 1952, 19115, 293, 3663, 1715, 767, 7463, 1125, 341, 13717, 13, 50890], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956908915302542, "compression_ratio": 1.6931818181818181, "no_speech_prob": 2.4944781483460243e-12}, {"id": 198, "seek": 77396, "start": 784.86, "end": 789.34, "text": " Let's move away from theory and look at the spaces we inhabit online every day.", "tokens": [50910, 961, 311, 1286, 1314, 490, 5261, 293, 574, 412, 264, 7673, 321, 21863, 2950, 633, 786, 13, 51134], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956908915302542, "compression_ratio": 1.6931818181818181, "no_speech_prob": 2.4944781483460243e-12}, {"id": 199, "seek": 77396, "start": 789.98, "end": 797.26, "text": " The paper lays out a taxonomy of failure modes where preservation technically succeeds, but reachability completely collapses.", "tokens": [51166, 440, 3035, 32714, 484, 257, 3366, 23423, 295, 7763, 14068, 689, 27257, 12120, 49263, 11, 457, 2524, 2310, 2584, 48765, 13, 51530], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956908915302542, "compression_ratio": 1.6931818181818181, "no_speech_prob": 2.4944781483460243e-12}, {"id": 200, "seek": 77396, "start": 797.5, "end": 798.26, "text": " Let's do it.", "tokens": [51542, 961, 311, 360, 309, 13, 51580], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956908915302542, "compression_ratio": 1.6931818181818181, "no_speech_prob": 2.4944781483460243e-12}, {"id": 201, "seek": 77396, "start": 798.32, "end": 801.48, "text": " Let's start by looking at social networks and community platforms.", "tokens": [51583, 961, 311, 722, 538, 1237, 412, 2093, 9590, 293, 1768, 9473, 13, 51741], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11956908915302542, "compression_ratio": 1.6931818181818181, "no_speech_prob": 2.4944781483460243e-12}, {"id": 202, "seek": 80148, "start": 801.48, "end": 805.8000000000001, "text": " The paper identifies a phenomenon it calls namespace laundering.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3035, 34597, 257, 14029, 309, 5498, 5288, 17940, 17245, 1794, 13, 50581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.25498627171371924, "compression_ratio": 1.4766839378238341, "no_speech_prob": 2.2536161305153346e-12}, {"id": 203, "seek": 80148, "start": 806.14, "end": 810.24, "text": " Namespace laundering is a brilliant and deeply concerning concept.", "tokens": [50598, 426, 1632, 17940, 17245, 1794, 307, 257, 10248, 293, 8760, 18087, 3410, 13, 50803], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.25498627171371924, "compression_ratio": 1.4766839378238341, "no_speech_prob": 2.2536161305153346e-12}, {"id": 204, "seek": 80148, "start": 810.76, "end": 814.78, "text": " It deals with identity drift combined with audience retention.", "tokens": [50829, 467, 11215, 365, 6575, 19699, 9354, 365, 4034, 22871, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.25498627171371924, "compression_ratio": 1.4766839378238341, "no_speech_prob": 2.2536161305153346e-12}, {"id": 205, "seek": 80148, "start": 815.08, "end": 816.24, "text": " Okay. Walk us through that.", "tokens": [51045, 1033, 13, 10818, 505, 807, 300, 13, 51103], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.25498627171371924, "compression_ratio": 1.4766839378238341, "no_speech_prob": 2.2536161305153346e-12}, {"id": 206, "seek": 80148, "start": 816.6800000000001, "end": 821.02, "text": " Think about large social platforms, Facebook, Reddit, Discord.", "tokens": [51125, 6557, 466, 2416, 2093, 9473, 11, 4384, 11, 32210, 11, 32623, 13, 51342], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.25498627171371924, "compression_ratio": 1.4766839378238341, "no_speech_prob": 2.2536161305153346e-12}, {"id": 207, "seek": 82102, "start": 821.02, "end": 830.9399999999999, "text": " Over time, named communities, whether they are groups, pages, subreddits, or channels, they accumulate massive audiences.", "tokens": [50365, 4886, 565, 11, 4926, 4456, 11, 1968, 436, 366, 3935, 11, 7183, 11, 1422, 986, 67, 1208, 11, 420, 9235, 11, 436, 33384, 5994, 15479, 13, 50861], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15376059214274088, "compression_ratio": 1.526829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 2.645002706441746e-12}, {"id": 208, "seek": 82102, "start": 831.66, "end": 837.4399999999999, "text": " Now, what is crucial to understand here is that this audience isn't just a list of passive subscribers.", "tokens": [50897, 823, 11, 437, 307, 11462, 281, 1223, 510, 307, 300, 341, 4034, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 1329, 295, 14975, 11092, 13, 51186], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15376059214274088, "compression_ratio": 1.526829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 2.645002706441746e-12}, {"id": 209, "seek": 82102, "start": 837.8, "end": 837.9, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51204, 1779, 13, 51209], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15376059214274088, "compression_ratio": 1.526829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 2.645002706441746e-12}, {"id": 210, "seek": 82102, "start": 838.4, "end": 842.72, "text": " In the graph model, the audience actually constitutes the social infrastructure.", "tokens": [51234, 682, 264, 4295, 2316, 11, 264, 4034, 767, 44204, 264, 2093, 6896, 13, 51450], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15376059214274088, "compression_ratio": 1.526829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 2.645002706441746e-12}, {"id": 211, "seek": 84272, "start": 842.72, "end": 850.88, "text": " They are the network through which content is distributed, and more importantly, they are how meaning is contextually stabilized.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 366, 264, 3209, 807, 597, 2701, 307, 12631, 11, 293, 544, 8906, 11, 436, 366, 577, 3620, 307, 4319, 671, 48384, 13, 50773], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15851097375574247, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604787407535463e-12}, {"id": 212, "seek": 84272, "start": 851.28, "end": 851.4, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50793, 1779, 13, 50799], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15851097375574247, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604787407535463e-12}, {"id": 213, "seek": 84272, "start": 851.48, "end": 858.12, "text": " Because if I join a group called Sustainable Local Farming, I have a very specific expectation of the semantic content.", "tokens": [50803, 1436, 498, 286, 3917, 257, 1594, 1219, 34407, 712, 22755, 9067, 2810, 11, 286, 362, 257, 588, 2685, 14334, 295, 264, 47982, 2701, 13, 51135], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15851097375574247, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604787407535463e-12}, {"id": 214, "seek": 84272, "start": 858.5400000000001, "end": 861.7, "text": " The community has a shared agreement on what that space means.", "tokens": [51156, 440, 1768, 575, 257, 5507, 8106, 322, 437, 300, 1901, 1355, 13, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15851097375574247, "compression_ratio": 1.45662100456621, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604787407535463e-12}, {"id": 215, "seek": 86170, "start": 861.7, "end": 865.4200000000001, "text": " We've all opted into a specific conversational contract.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 600, 439, 40768, 666, 257, 2685, 2615, 1478, 4364, 13, 50551], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 216, "seek": 86170, "start": 865.9000000000001, "end": 868.1, "text": " The name of the group is the signpost on the path.", "tokens": [50575, 440, 1315, 295, 264, 1594, 307, 264, 1465, 23744, 322, 264, 3100, 13, 50685], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 217, "seek": 86170, "start": 868.26, "end": 868.7, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50693, 7587, 13, 50715], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 218, "seek": 86170, "start": 869.0200000000001, "end": 871.0200000000001, "text": " But what happens when that community is renamed?", "tokens": [50731, 583, 437, 2314, 562, 300, 1768, 307, 40949, 30, 50831], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 219, "seek": 86170, "start": 871.5, "end": 875.1800000000001, "text": " Or its stated purpose is quietly changed by the administrators?", "tokens": [50855, 1610, 1080, 11323, 4334, 307, 19141, 3105, 538, 264, 27754, 30, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 220, "seek": 86170, "start": 875.82, "end": 878.4000000000001, "text": " Perhaps because a new moderation team takes over?", "tokens": [51071, 10517, 570, 257, 777, 49471, 1469, 2516, 670, 30, 51200], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 221, "seek": 86170, "start": 878.6600000000001, "end": 882.1400000000001, "text": " Or the original founder sells the page to a marketing firm?", "tokens": [51213, 1610, 264, 3380, 14917, 20897, 264, 3028, 281, 257, 6370, 6174, 30, 51387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 222, "seek": 86170, "start": 882.48, "end": 883.48, "text": " Oh, man.", "tokens": [51404, 876, 11, 587, 13, 51454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 223, "seek": 86170, "start": 883.6, "end": 885.76, "text": " I've seen that happen so many times.", "tokens": [51460, 286, 600, 1612, 300, 1051, 370, 867, 1413, 13, 51568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19976503372192383, "compression_ratio": 1.5524193548387097, "no_speech_prob": 1.629842419879901e-12}, {"id": 224, "seek": 88576, "start": 885.76, "end": 886.12, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50383], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 225, "seek": 88576, "start": 886.46, "end": 891.78, "text": " The paper points out that typically, the massive accumulated audience is retained.", "tokens": [50400, 440, 3035, 2793, 484, 300, 5850, 11, 264, 5994, 31346, 4034, 307, 33438, 13, 50666], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 226, "seek": 88576, "start": 892.4, "end": 901.04, "text": " The platform doesn't kick everyone out and make them resubscribe, but the semantic identity of the community is completely overwritten.", "tokens": [50697, 440, 3663, 1177, 380, 4437, 1518, 484, 293, 652, 552, 725, 9493, 11, 457, 264, 47982, 6575, 295, 264, 1768, 307, 2584, 670, 26859, 13, 51129], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 227, "seek": 88576, "start": 901.36, "end": 901.76, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [51145, 3153, 13, 51165], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 228, "seek": 88576, "start": 902.2, "end": 904.42, "text": " This is namespace laundering.", "tokens": [51187, 639, 307, 5288, 17940, 17245, 1794, 13, 51298], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 229, "seek": 88576, "start": 904.92, "end": 912.9, "text": " It severs the mapping between a name and its prior referent, but it forcefully conserves the distribution network.", "tokens": [51323, 467, 369, 840, 264, 18350, 1296, 257, 1315, 293, 1080, 4059, 2864, 317, 11, 457, 309, 3464, 2277, 1014, 9054, 264, 7316, 3209, 13, 51722], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 230, "seek": 88576, "start": 912.9, "end": 915.48, "text": " It's like buying a ticket for a train.", "tokens": [51722, 467, 311, 411, 6382, 257, 10550, 337, 257, 3847, 13, 51851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17840165802926727, "compression_ratio": 1.5862068965517242, "no_speech_prob": 1.6108501251638208e-12}, {"id": 231, "seek": 91576, "start": 915.76, "end": 919.76, "text": " That you are told is heading to a peaceful, philosophical retreat.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 291, 366, 1907, 307, 9864, 281, 257, 13962, 11, 25066, 15505, 13, 50565], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08954401849543006, "compression_ratio": 1.726923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 1.63621893811694e-12}, {"id": 232, "seek": 91576, "start": 920.3, "end": 934.56, "text": " You board the train, you fall asleep in your seat, and while you're sleeping, the train operators detach your specific passenger car and hook it up to a massive freight locomotive heading straight toward a giant corporate billboard.", "tokens": [50592, 509, 3150, 264, 3847, 11, 291, 2100, 11039, 294, 428, 6121, 11, 293, 1339, 291, 434, 8296, 11, 264, 3847, 19077, 43245, 428, 2685, 18707, 1032, 293, 6328, 309, 493, 281, 257, 5994, 37181, 36369, 22459, 9864, 2997, 7361, 257, 7410, 10896, 2961, 3787, 13, 51305], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08954401849543006, "compression_ratio": 1.726923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 1.63621893811694e-12}, {"id": 233, "seek": 91576, "start": 934.74, "end": 935.9, "text": " That's a great way to put it.", "tokens": [51314, 663, 311, 257, 869, 636, 281, 829, 309, 13, 51372], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08954401849543006, "compression_ratio": 1.726923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 1.63621893811694e-12}, {"id": 234, "seek": 91576, "start": 935.9, "end": 941.9399999999999, "text": " You wake up, you're still in the same seat, the car is perfectly preserved, your fellow passengers are all still there,", "tokens": [51372, 509, 6634, 493, 11, 291, 434, 920, 294, 264, 912, 6121, 11, 264, 1032, 307, 6239, 22242, 11, 428, 7177, 18436, 366, 439, 920, 456, 11, 51674], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08954401849543006, "compression_ratio": 1.726923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 1.63621893811694e-12}, {"id": 235, "seek": 94194, "start": 941.94, "end": 946.22, "text": " but your destination was silently overridden without your consent.", "tokens": [50365, 457, 428, 12236, 390, 40087, 670, 81, 6171, 1553, 428, 14546, 13, 50579], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18415918946266174, "compression_ratio": 1.0, "no_speech_prob": 1.7620025447376286e-12}, {"id": 236, "seek": 94622, "start": 946.22, "end": 957.4, "text": " The node, the social group isn't lost, the servers hold the data perfectly, but the edge label, the navigational path you took to get there is corrupted.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 9984, 11, 264, 2093, 1594, 1943, 380, 2731, 11, 264, 15909, 1797, 264, 1412, 6239, 11, 457, 264, 4691, 7645, 11, 264, 7407, 1478, 3100, 291, 1890, 281, 483, 456, 307, 39480, 13, 50924], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16196202474927146, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5983182659329298e-12}, {"id": 237, "seek": 94622, "start": 958.36, "end": 966.6800000000001, "text": " You, as an audience member who joined under one specific semantic contract, are now participating in a completely different one.", "tokens": [50972, 509, 11, 382, 364, 4034, 4006, 567, 6869, 833, 472, 2685, 47982, 4364, 11, 366, 586, 13950, 294, 257, 2584, 819, 472, 13, 51388], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16196202474927146, "compression_ratio": 1.4764397905759161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5983182659329298e-12}, {"id": 238, "seek": 96668, "start": 966.68, "end": 968.5799999999999, "text": " And what does that do to reachability?", "tokens": [50365, 400, 437, 775, 300, 360, 281, 2524, 2310, 30, 50460], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15766259395714963, "compression_ratio": 1.4734042553191489, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898028557336351e-12}, {"id": 239, "seek": 96668, "start": 969.14, "end": 971.4599999999999, "text": " Well, here is the truly damaging part.", "tokens": [50488, 1042, 11, 510, 307, 264, 4908, 25342, 644, 13, 50604], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15766259395714963, "compression_ratio": 1.4734042553191489, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898028557336351e-12}, {"id": 240, "seek": 96668, "start": 972.28, "end": 977.06, "text": " New members who join today encounter this community only in its present form.", "tokens": [50645, 1873, 2679, 567, 3917, 965, 8593, 341, 1768, 787, 294, 1080, 1974, 1254, 13, 50884], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15766259395714963, "compression_ratio": 1.4734042553191489, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898028557336351e-12}, {"id": 241, "seek": 96668, "start": 977.5, "end": 986.5, "text": " There is absolutely zero record right there on the front page that a prior form, a prior semantic contract, ever existed.", "tokens": [50906, 821, 307, 3122, 4018, 2136, 558, 456, 322, 264, 1868, 3028, 300, 257, 4059, 1254, 11, 257, 4059, 47982, 4364, 11, 1562, 13135, 13, 51356], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15766259395714963, "compression_ratio": 1.4734042553191489, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898028557336351e-12}, {"id": 242, "seek": 98650, "start": 986.5, "end": 992.58, "text": " Right. A prior meaning is not preserved. It is actively overwritten at the level of the identifier.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 316, 4059, 3620, 307, 406, 22242, 13, 467, 307, 13022, 670, 26859, 412, 264, 1496, 295, 264, 45690, 13, 50669], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1417141508782047, "compression_ratio": 1.688073394495413, "no_speech_prob": 1.8834341638379604e-12}, {"id": 243, "seek": 98650, "start": 993.38, "end": 1000.34, "text": " If you want to reach the past state of that community, what used to mean the discussions that used to happen, you can't.", "tokens": [50709, 759, 291, 528, 281, 2524, 264, 1791, 1785, 295, 300, 1768, 11, 437, 1143, 281, 914, 264, 11088, 300, 1143, 281, 1051, 11, 291, 393, 380, 13, 51057], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1417141508782047, "compression_ratio": 1.688073394495413, "no_speech_prob": 1.8834341638379604e-12}, {"id": 244, "seek": 98650, "start": 1000.58, "end": 1001.56, "text": " No, you can't.", "tokens": [51069, 883, 11, 291, 393, 380, 13, 51118], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1417141508782047, "compression_ratio": 1.688073394495413, "no_speech_prob": 1.8834341638379604e-12}, {"id": 245, "seek": 98650, "start": 1001.68, "end": 1008.84, "text": " The path from the present state to the community's prior meaning passes through a name that now points somewhere entirely different.", "tokens": [51124, 440, 3100, 490, 264, 1974, 1785, 281, 264, 1768, 311, 4059, 3620, 11335, 807, 257, 1315, 300, 586, 2793, 4079, 7696, 819, 13, 51482], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1417141508782047, "compression_ratio": 1.688073394495413, "no_speech_prob": 1.8834341638379604e-12}, {"id": 246, "seek": 100884, "start": 1008.84, "end": 1018.26, "text": " The preservation of the social group's database is 100% successful, but the reachability to its historical meaning is absolute zero.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 27257, 295, 264, 2093, 1594, 311, 8149, 307, 2319, 4, 4406, 11, 457, 264, 2524, 2310, 281, 1080, 8584, 3620, 307, 8236, 4018, 13, 50836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13147995346470884, "compression_ratio": 1.4366812227074235, "no_speech_prob": 1.478344465073722e-12}, {"id": 247, "seek": 100884, "start": 1018.74, "end": 1023.8000000000001, "text": " Exactly. But, you know, this isn't just malicious actors or corporate bait and switches.", "tokens": [50860, 7587, 13, 583, 11, 291, 458, 11, 341, 1943, 380, 445, 33496, 10037, 420, 10896, 16865, 293, 19458, 13, 51113], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13147995346470884, "compression_ratio": 1.4366812227074235, "no_speech_prob": 1.478344465073722e-12}, {"id": 248, "seek": 100884, "start": 1024.74, "end": 1029.6200000000001, "text": " It happens in the very places we trust the most to organize truth.", "tokens": [51160, 467, 2314, 294, 264, 588, 3190, 321, 3361, 264, 881, 281, 13859, 3494, 13, 51404], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13147995346470884, "compression_ratio": 1.4366812227074235, "no_speech_prob": 1.478344465073722e-12}, {"id": 249, "seek": 100884, "start": 1029.88, "end": 1031.78, "text": " Here's where it gets really interesting.", "tokens": [51417, 1692, 311, 689, 309, 2170, 534, 1880, 13, 51512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13147995346470884, "compression_ratio": 1.4366812227074235, "no_speech_prob": 1.478344465073722e-12}, {"id": 250, "seek": 103178, "start": 1031.78, "end": 1039.26, "text": " Right. This brings us to the next structural failure in the paper, which deals with reference systems like Wikipedia.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 639, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 958, 15067, 7763, 294, 264, 3035, 11, 597, 11215, 365, 6408, 3652, 411, 28999, 13, 50739], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20245115458965302, "compression_ratio": 1.6132596685082874, "no_speech_prob": 1.5552111464964269e-12}, {"id": 251, "seek": 103178, "start": 1040.44, "end": 1043.56, "text": " Flyxion calls this encyclopedic consolidation.", "tokens": [50798, 3235, 4105, 5498, 341, 465, 34080, 27277, 299, 39114, 13, 50954], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20245115458965302, "compression_ratio": 1.6132596685082874, "no_speech_prob": 1.5552111464964269e-12}, {"id": 252, "seek": 103178, "start": 1044.18, "end": 1045.86, "text": " Okay. Encyclopedic consolidation.", "tokens": [50985, 1033, 13, 2193, 34080, 27277, 299, 39114, 13, 51069], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20245115458965302, "compression_ratio": 1.6132596685082874, "no_speech_prob": 1.5552111464964269e-12}, {"id": 253, "seek": 103178, "start": 1046.54, "end": 1052.6399999999999, "text": " Reference systems stabilize meaning through a constant, relentless process of consolidation.", "tokens": [51103, 1300, 5158, 3652, 31870, 3620, 807, 257, 5754, 11, 46136, 1399, 295, 39114, 13, 51408], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20245115458965302, "compression_ratio": 1.6132596685082874, "no_speech_prob": 1.5552111464964269e-12}, {"id": 254, "seek": 105264, "start": 1052.64, "end": 1065.3400000000001, "text": " Articles are constantly being merged, disambiguated, or renamed as editors' debate, and eventually converge on what they consider to be the preferred framing of a topic.", "tokens": [50365, 5735, 5350, 366, 6460, 885, 36427, 11, 717, 2173, 16397, 770, 11, 420, 40949, 382, 31446, 6, 7958, 11, 293, 4728, 41881, 322, 437, 436, 1949, 281, 312, 264, 16494, 28971, 295, 257, 4829, 13, 51000], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871950785319011, "compression_ratio": 1.528301886792453, "no_speech_prob": 1.839362429728597e-12}, {"id": 255, "seek": 105264, "start": 1065.5400000000002, "end": 1073.24, "text": " Now, wait. As a learner trying to avoid information overload, my initial reaction is that consolidating information is a good thing.", "tokens": [51010, 823, 11, 1699, 13, 1018, 257, 33347, 1382, 281, 5042, 1589, 28777, 11, 452, 5883, 5480, 307, 300, 19045, 990, 1589, 307, 257, 665, 551, 13, 51395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871950785319011, "compression_ratio": 1.528301886792453, "no_speech_prob": 1.839362429728597e-12}, {"id": 256, "seek": 105264, "start": 1073.3200000000002, "end": 1074.24, "text": " Sure. It makes sense.", "tokens": [51399, 4894, 13, 467, 1669, 2020, 13, 51445], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871950785319011, "compression_ratio": 1.528301886792453, "no_speech_prob": 1.839362429728597e-12}, {"id": 257, "seek": 107424, "start": 1074.24, "end": 1080.02, "text": " I mean, I don't want to read 50 different disjointed, contradictory articles about the same historical event.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 286, 500, 380, 528, 281, 1401, 2625, 819, 717, 73, 33041, 11, 49555, 11290, 466, 264, 912, 8584, 2280, 13, 50654], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12232857830119583, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.1504152625251294e-12}, {"id": 258, "seek": 107424, "start": 1080.38, "end": 1083.9, "text": " I want one clean, consensus-driven page.", "tokens": [50672, 286, 528, 472, 2541, 11, 19115, 12, 25456, 3028, 13, 50848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12232857830119583, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.1504152625251294e-12}, {"id": 259, "seek": 107424, "start": 1083.9, "end": 1087.92, "text": " If I'm researching the French Revolution, I want the definitive summary.", "tokens": [50848, 759, 286, 478, 24176, 264, 5522, 16617, 11, 286, 528, 264, 28152, 12691, 13, 51049], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12232857830119583, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.1504152625251294e-12}, {"id": 260, "seek": 107424, "start": 1088.64, "end": 1091.54, "text": " Isn't this exactly what we want our encyclopedias to do?", "tokens": [51085, 6998, 380, 341, 2293, 437, 321, 528, 527, 465, 34080, 27277, 4609, 281, 360, 30, 51230], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12232857830119583, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.1504152625251294e-12}, {"id": 261, "seek": 107424, "start": 1091.98, "end": 1094.18, "text": " Sift through the noise and give us the signal.", "tokens": [51252, 318, 2008, 807, 264, 5658, 293, 976, 505, 264, 6358, 13, 51362], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12232857830119583, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.1504152625251294e-12}, {"id": 262, "seek": 107424, "start": 1094.56, "end": 1099.72, "text": " Yes. And for general navigability and rapid fact-checking, it is highly effective.", "tokens": [51381, 1079, 13, 400, 337, 2674, 7407, 2310, 293, 7558, 1186, 12, 15723, 278, 11, 309, 307, 5405, 4942, 13, 51639], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12232857830119583, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.1504152625251294e-12}, {"id": 263, "seek": 109972, "start": 1099.72, "end": 1107.8600000000001, "text": " It radically improves your ability to move from a state of ignorance toward canonical accepted content.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 35508, 24771, 428, 3485, 281, 1286, 490, 257, 1785, 295, 25390, 7361, 46491, 9035, 2701, 13, 50772], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21772888728550502, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.028037243348435e-12}, {"id": 264, "seek": 109972, "start": 1108.52, "end": 1115.66, "text": " But the paper provides a critical structural analysis of the unseen cost of this drive for consensus.", "tokens": [50805, 583, 264, 3035, 6417, 257, 4924, 15067, 5215, 295, 264, 40608, 2063, 295, 341, 3332, 337, 19115, 13, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21772888728550502, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.028037243348435e-12}, {"id": 265, "seek": 109972, "start": 1116.2, "end": 1120.48, "text": " It calls this process path compression with loss.", "tokens": [51189, 467, 5498, 341, 1399, 3100, 19355, 365, 4470, 13, 51403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21772888728550502, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.028037243348435e-12}, {"id": 266, "seek": 109972, "start": 1120.66, "end": 1122.32, "text": " Path compression with loss.", "tokens": [51412, 21914, 19355, 365, 4470, 13, 51495], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21772888728550502, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.028037243348435e-12}, {"id": 267, "seek": 109972, "start": 1122.38, "end": 1122.72, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51498, 1079, 13, 51515], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21772888728550502, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.028037243348435e-12}, {"id": 268, "seek": 112272, "start": 1122.72, "end": 1132.9, "text": " When a smaller, more nuanced article is merged into a massive mainstream article, intermediate nodes in the graph are completely eliminated.", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 257, 4356, 11, 544, 45115, 7222, 307, 36427, 666, 257, 5994, 15960, 7222, 11, 19376, 13891, 294, 264, 4295, 366, 2584, 20308, 13, 50874], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09690008624907463, "compression_ratio": 1.642156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.7482789304787416e-12}, {"id": 269, "seek": 112272, "start": 1133.66, "end": 1145.1000000000001, "text": " Those intermediate nodes often represented prior framings, minority perspectives, regional understandings, or earlier states of consensus that were highly relevant at the time they were written.", "tokens": [50912, 3950, 19376, 13891, 2049, 10379, 4059, 21405, 1109, 11, 16166, 16766, 11, 10964, 1223, 1109, 11, 420, 3071, 4368, 295, 19115, 300, 645, 5405, 7340, 412, 264, 565, 436, 645, 3720, 13, 51484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09690008624907463, "compression_ratio": 1.642156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.7482789304787416e-12}, {"id": 270, "seek": 114510, "start": 1145.1, "end": 1150.48, "text": " But I can hear people yelling at their audio players right now saying, wait, Wikipedia saves everything.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 286, 393, 1568, 561, 18381, 412, 641, 6278, 4150, 558, 586, 1566, 11, 1699, 11, 28999, 19155, 1203, 13, 50634], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 271, "seek": 114510, "start": 1150.58, "end": 1152.04, "text": " I can go look at the edit history.", "tokens": [50639, 286, 393, 352, 574, 412, 264, 8129, 2503, 13, 50712], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 272, "seek": 114510, "start": 1152.52, "end": 1153.9599999999998, "text": " Nothing is ever really deleted.", "tokens": [50736, 6693, 307, 1562, 534, 22981, 13, 50808], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 273, "seek": 114510, "start": 1154.56, "end": 1161.24, "text": " You can, but this is exactly where the distinction between preservation and reachability becomes razor sharp.", "tokens": [50838, 509, 393, 11, 457, 341, 307, 2293, 689, 264, 16844, 1296, 27257, 293, 2524, 2310, 3643, 30478, 8199, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 274, "seek": 114510, "start": 1161.36, "end": 1163.6999999999998, "text": " And why the graph model is so important.", "tokens": [51178, 400, 983, 264, 4295, 2316, 307, 370, 1021, 13, 51295], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 275, "seek": 114510, "start": 1164.28, "end": 1171.08, "text": " When that old article is merged, its prior existence is relegated solely to those internal edit histories.", "tokens": [51324, 1133, 300, 1331, 7222, 307, 36427, 11, 1080, 4059, 9123, 307, 2951, 70, 770, 23309, 281, 729, 6920, 8129, 30631, 13, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 276, "seek": 114510, "start": 1171.28, "end": 1172.1, "text": " Okay, so it's buried.", "tokens": [51674, 1033, 11, 370, 309, 311, 14101, 13, 51715], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 277, "seek": 114510, "start": 1172.4199999999998, "end": 1172.84, "text": " Buried.", "tokens": [51731, 7031, 1091, 13, 51752], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648260389055526, "compression_ratio": 1.6048951048951048, "no_speech_prob": 2.133676048343691e-12}, {"id": 278, "seek": 117284, "start": 1172.84, "end": 1177.8999999999999, "text": " And here's the crucial technical reality that affects billions of users.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 510, 311, 264, 11462, 6191, 4103, 300, 11807, 17375, 295, 5022, 13, 50618], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15448793646407455, "compression_ratio": 1.4798206278026906, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579882420267536e-12}, {"id": 279, "seek": 117284, "start": 1179.1, "end": 1183.98, "text": " Those edit histories are not indexed by external search engines.", "tokens": [50678, 3950, 8129, 30631, 366, 406, 8186, 292, 538, 8320, 3164, 12982, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15448793646407455, "compression_ratio": 1.4798206278026906, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579882420267536e-12}, {"id": 280, "seek": 117284, "start": 1184.36, "end": 1196.26, "text": " If a user arriving from Google or DuckDuckGo searches for a term that used to be a standalone article but is now just a merged paragraph in a larger page, they encounter the current consensus.", "tokens": [50941, 759, 257, 4195, 22436, 490, 3329, 420, 29266, 35, 1134, 12104, 26701, 337, 257, 1433, 300, 1143, 281, 312, 257, 37454, 7222, 457, 307, 586, 445, 257, 36427, 18865, 294, 257, 4833, 3028, 11, 436, 8593, 264, 2190, 19115, 13, 51536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15448793646407455, "compression_ratio": 1.4798206278026906, "no_speech_prob": 1.9579882420267536e-12}, {"id": 281, "seek": 119626, "start": 1196.26, "end": 1205.54, "text": " There is no visible, intuitive indication that a rich, distinct prior structure ever existed.", "tokens": [50365, 821, 307, 572, 8974, 11, 21769, 18877, 300, 257, 4593, 11, 10644, 4059, 3877, 1562, 13135, 13, 50829], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2154501832049826, "compression_ratio": 1.4179104477611941, "no_speech_prob": 1.4664869795941171e-12}, {"id": 282, "seek": 119626, "start": 1205.92, "end": 1206.04, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50848, 1779, 13, 50854], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2154501832049826, "compression_ratio": 1.4179104477611941, "no_speech_prob": 1.4664869795941171e-12}, {"id": 283, "seek": 119626, "start": 1206.24, "end": 1208.1, "text": " The prior structure is preserved.", "tokens": [50864, 440, 4059, 3877, 307, 22242, 13, 50957], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2154501832049826, "compression_ratio": 1.4179104477611941, "no_speech_prob": 1.4664869795941171e-12}, {"id": 284, "seek": 119626, "start": 1208.4, "end": 1210.96, "text": " It is technically sitting on a server farm in Virginia.", "tokens": [50972, 467, 307, 12120, 3798, 322, 257, 7154, 5421, 294, 10956, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2154501832049826, "compression_ratio": 1.4179104477611941, "no_speech_prob": 1.4664869795941171e-12}, {"id": 285, "seek": 121096, "start": 1210.96, "end": 1217.42, "text": " But it can only be reconstructed by an agent who already possesses highly specific navigational knowledge.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 309, 393, 787, 312, 31499, 292, 538, 364, 9461, 567, 1217, 17490, 279, 5405, 2685, 7407, 1478, 3601, 13, 50688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15724049116435804, "compression_ratio": 1.6117021276595744, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898030725740696e-12}, {"id": 286, "seek": 121096, "start": 1217.52, "end": 1218.0, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50693, 7587, 13, 50717], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15724049116435804, "compression_ratio": 1.6117021276595744, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898030725740696e-12}, {"id": 287, "seek": 121096, "start": 1218.1000000000001, "end": 1219.7, "text": " You have to know to click the history tab.", "tokens": [50722, 509, 362, 281, 458, 281, 2052, 264, 2503, 4421, 13, 50802], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15724049116435804, "compression_ratio": 1.6117021276595744, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898030725740696e-12}, {"id": 288, "seek": 121096, "start": 1219.78, "end": 1221.08, "text": " You have to know how to read the metadata.", "tokens": [50806, 509, 362, 281, 458, 577, 281, 1401, 264, 26603, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15724049116435804, "compression_ratio": 1.6117021276595744, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898030725740696e-12}, {"id": 289, "seek": 121096, "start": 1221.48, "end": 1227.22, "text": " And you have to know what specific timestamp you are looking for in thousands of lines of code diffs.", "tokens": [50891, 400, 291, 362, 281, 458, 437, 2685, 49108, 1215, 291, 366, 1237, 337, 294, 5383, 295, 3876, 295, 3089, 7593, 82, 13, 51178], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15724049116435804, "compression_ratio": 1.6117021276595744, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898030725740696e-12}, {"id": 290, "seek": 122722, "start": 1227.22, "end": 1238.08, "text": " And from the perspective of a general user, the available transformations, typing a natural language query into a search bar, will never lead them to those older merged perspectives.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 490, 264, 4585, 295, 257, 2674, 4195, 11, 264, 2435, 34852, 11, 18444, 257, 3303, 2856, 14581, 666, 257, 3164, 2159, 11, 486, 1128, 1477, 552, 281, 729, 4906, 36427, 16766, 13, 50908], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13610949387421478, "compression_ratio": 1.378787878787879, "no_speech_prob": 1.674412561727956e-12}, {"id": 291, "seek": 123808, "start": 1238.08, "end": 1249.1, "text": " The graph has been simplified and compressed for efficiency, but the path back to the messy historical debate is effectively destroyed for the average person.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4295, 575, 668, 26335, 293, 30353, 337, 10493, 11, 457, 264, 3100, 646, 281, 264, 16191, 8584, 7958, 307, 8659, 8937, 337, 264, 4274, 954, 13, 50916], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15318679809570312, "compression_ratio": 1.5871212121212122, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015473231796197e-12}, {"id": 292, "seek": 123808, "start": 1249.5, "end": 1252.6399999999999, "text": " The consensus hides the work of its own creation.", "tokens": [50936, 440, 19115, 35953, 264, 589, 295, 1080, 1065, 8016, 13, 51093], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15318679809570312, "compression_ratio": 1.5871212121212122, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015473231796197e-12}, {"id": 293, "seek": 123808, "start": 1253.04, "end": 1253.28, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [51113, 3153, 13, 51125], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15318679809570312, "compression_ratio": 1.5871212121212122, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015473231796197e-12}, {"id": 294, "seek": 123808, "start": 1253.48, "end": 1260.52, "text": " So namespace laundering and encyclopedic consolidation both involve active human choices that alter paths.", "tokens": [51135, 407, 5288, 17940, 17245, 1794, 293, 465, 34080, 27277, 299, 39114, 1293, 9494, 4967, 1952, 7994, 300, 11337, 14518, 13, 51487], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15318679809570312, "compression_ratio": 1.5871212121212122, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015473231796197e-12}, {"id": 295, "seek": 123808, "start": 1260.96, "end": 1267.32, "text": " But what happens when the infrastructure itself just passively rots or throws up artificial walls?", "tokens": [51509, 583, 437, 2314, 562, 264, 6896, 2564, 445, 1320, 3413, 367, 1971, 420, 19251, 493, 11677, 7920, 30, 51827], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15318679809570312, "compression_ratio": 1.5871212121212122, "no_speech_prob": 1.7015473231796197e-12}, {"id": 296, "seek": 126732, "start": 1267.32, "end": 1270.82, "text": " Well, that leads us to the second part of this taxonomy.", "tokens": [50365, 1042, 11, 300, 6689, 505, 281, 264, 1150, 644, 295, 341, 3366, 23423, 13, 50540], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 297, "seek": 126732, "start": 1271.5, "end": 1274.34, "text": " Gated paths, dead ends, and the hidden vault.", "tokens": [50574, 460, 770, 14518, 11, 3116, 5314, 11, 293, 264, 7633, 27134, 13, 50716], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 298, "seek": 126732, "start": 1274.5, "end": 1276.2, "text": " Let's talk about the artificial walls first.", "tokens": [50724, 961, 311, 751, 466, 264, 11677, 7920, 700, 13, 50809], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 299, "seek": 126732, "start": 1276.4199999999998, "end": 1277.04, "text": " Gated edges.", "tokens": [50820, 460, 770, 8819, 13, 50851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 300, "seek": 126732, "start": 1277.28, "end": 1277.48, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50863, 1779, 13, 50873], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 301, "seek": 126732, "start": 1277.6, "end": 1278.3799999999999, "text": " Access restriction.", "tokens": [50879, 17166, 29529, 13, 50918], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 302, "seek": 126732, "start": 1278.7, "end": 1283.1, "text": " This brings us directly into the realm of academic publishing and scientific research.", "tokens": [50934, 639, 5607, 505, 3838, 666, 264, 15355, 295, 7778, 17832, 293, 8134, 2132, 13, 51154], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 303, "seek": 126732, "start": 1283.1399999999999, "end": 1284.56, "text": " A system we all rely on.", "tokens": [51156, 316, 1185, 321, 439, 10687, 322, 13, 51227], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 304, "seek": 126732, "start": 1284.6399999999999, "end": 1285.12, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51231, 7587, 13, 51255], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 305, "seek": 126732, "start": 1285.6599999999999, "end": 1294.1399999999999, "text": " And academic publishing is a fascinating case study because in terms of sheer preservation, it actually does a relatively fantastic job.", "tokens": [51282, 400, 7778, 17832, 307, 257, 10343, 1389, 2979, 570, 294, 2115, 295, 23061, 27257, 11, 309, 767, 775, 257, 7226, 5456, 1691, 13, 51706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14594244956970215, "compression_ratio": 1.63003663003663, "no_speech_prob": 2.060544877086068e-12}, {"id": 306, "seek": 129414, "start": 1294.14, "end": 1297.4, "text": " The nodes, the research papers, exist perfectly.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 13891, 11, 264, 2132, 10577, 11, 2514, 6239, 13, 50528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15796942253635354, "compression_ratio": 1.4322916666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891269621014063e-12}, {"id": 307, "seek": 129414, "start": 1297.4, "end": 1303.3600000000001, "text": " The industry relies heavily on DOIs, or digital object identifiers.", "tokens": [50528, 440, 3518, 30910, 10950, 322, 10699, 6802, 11, 420, 4562, 2657, 2473, 23463, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15796942253635354, "compression_ratio": 1.4322916666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891269621014063e-12}, {"id": 308, "seek": 129414, "start": 1303.7, "end": 1306.88, "text": " If you've ever looked at a scholarly article, you've seen them.", "tokens": [50843, 759, 291, 600, 1562, 2956, 412, 257, 39589, 7222, 11, 291, 600, 1612, 552, 13, 51002], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15796942253635354, "compression_ratio": 1.4322916666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891269621014063e-12}, {"id": 309, "seek": 129414, "start": 1306.96, "end": 1310.42, "text": " It's a unique string of characters assigned permanently to a document.", "tokens": [51006, 467, 311, 257, 3845, 6798, 295, 4342, 13279, 24042, 281, 257, 4166, 13, 51179], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15796942253635354, "compression_ratio": 1.4322916666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891269621014063e-12}, {"id": 310, "seek": 129414, "start": 1310.5600000000002, "end": 1310.68, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51186, 1779, 13, 51192], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15796942253635354, "compression_ratio": 1.4322916666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891269621014063e-12}, {"id": 311, "seek": 129414, "start": 1310.74, "end": 1311.3200000000002, "text": " I've seen those.", "tokens": [51195, 286, 600, 1612, 729, 13, 51224], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15796942253635354, "compression_ratio": 1.4322916666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891269621014063e-12}, {"id": 312, "seek": 131132, "start": 1311.32, "end": 1316.1, "text": " The brilliant engineering behind DOIs is that they survive server changes.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 10248, 7043, 2261, 10699, 6802, 307, 300, 436, 7867, 7154, 2962, 13, 50604], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13055706024169922, "compression_ratio": 1.4433497536945812, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622708847753188e-12}, {"id": 313, "seek": 131132, "start": 1316.6399999999999, "end": 1329.22, "text": " If a journal gets bought out and moves its entire 50-year archive to a new domain structure, the DOI is updated in a central registry, and the link still points to the right place.", "tokens": [50631, 759, 257, 6708, 2170, 4243, 484, 293, 6067, 1080, 2302, 2625, 12, 5294, 23507, 281, 257, 777, 9274, 3877, 11, 264, 10699, 40, 307, 10588, 294, 257, 5777, 36468, 11, 293, 264, 2113, 920, 2793, 281, 264, 558, 1081, 13, 51260], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13055706024169922, "compression_ratio": 1.4433497536945812, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622708847753188e-12}, {"id": 314, "seek": 131132, "start": 1329.84, "end": 1332.1599999999999, "text": " The path, theoretically, is pristine.", "tokens": [51291, 440, 3100, 11, 29400, 11, 307, 582, 42745, 13, 51407], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13055706024169922, "compression_ratio": 1.4433497536945812, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622708847753188e-12}, {"id": 315, "seek": 133216, "start": 1332.16, "end": 1335.22, "text": " So the node is solidly present in the graph.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 264, 9984, 307, 5100, 356, 1974, 294, 264, 4295, 13, 50518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 316, "seek": 133216, "start": 1335.78, "end": 1339.52, "text": " The edge, the citation pointing to it, exists permanently.", "tokens": [50546, 440, 4691, 11, 264, 45590, 12166, 281, 309, 11, 8198, 24042, 13, 50733], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 317, "seek": 133216, "start": 1339.8000000000002, "end": 1340.1000000000001, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50747, 1079, 13, 50762], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 318, "seek": 133216, "start": 1340.3000000000002, "end": 1346.8000000000002, "text": " But I think anyone who has ever tried to research a medical condition or read a sociology paper knows exactly what comes next.", "tokens": [50772, 583, 286, 519, 2878, 567, 575, 1562, 3031, 281, 2132, 257, 4625, 4188, 420, 1401, 257, 41744, 3035, 3255, 2293, 437, 1487, 958, 13, 51097], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 319, "seek": 133216, "start": 1347.1000000000001, "end": 1349.52, "text": " You click the perfectly preserved DOI link.", "tokens": [51112, 509, 2052, 264, 6239, 22242, 10699, 40, 2113, 13, 51233], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 320, "seek": 133216, "start": 1350.1200000000001, "end": 1352.28, "text": " You follow the perfectly maintained path.", "tokens": [51263, 509, 1524, 264, 6239, 17578, 3100, 13, 51371], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 321, "seek": 133216, "start": 1352.7, "end": 1359.0400000000002, "text": " And you smash headfirst into a hard paywall, demanding $45 to read a six-page PDF.", "tokens": [51392, 400, 291, 17960, 1378, 29581, 666, 257, 1152, 1689, 16256, 11, 19960, 1848, 8465, 281, 1401, 257, 2309, 12, 15161, 17752, 13, 51709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 322, "seek": 133216, "start": 1359.52, "end": 1360.5400000000002, "text": " Every single time.", "tokens": [51733, 2048, 2167, 565, 13, 51784], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1724354630216546, "compression_ratio": 1.5437956204379562, "no_speech_prob": 1.5134024675816926e-12}, {"id": 323, "seek": 136054, "start": 1360.54, "end": 1369.0, "text": " Without institutional subscription credentials, typically provided by a wealthy university, that edge is gated.", "tokens": [50365, 9129, 18391, 17231, 27404, 11, 5850, 5649, 538, 257, 17707, 5454, 11, 300, 4691, 307, 290, 770, 13, 50788], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09599633864414545, "compression_ratio": 1.6015936254980079, "no_speech_prob": 2.020426144097587e-12}, {"id": 324, "seek": 136054, "start": 1369.58, "end": 1371.26, "text": " The preservation is flawless.", "tokens": [50817, 440, 27257, 307, 45693, 13, 50901], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09599633864414545, "compression_ratio": 1.6015936254980079, "no_speech_prob": 2.020426144097587e-12}, {"id": 325, "seek": 136054, "start": 1372.08, "end": 1375.26, "text": " The server is delivering the page exactly as requested.", "tokens": [50942, 440, 7154, 307, 14666, 264, 3028, 2293, 382, 16436, 13, 51101], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09599633864414545, "compression_ratio": 1.6015936254980079, "no_speech_prob": 2.020426144097587e-12}, {"id": 326, "seek": 136054, "start": 1375.8999999999999, "end": 1385.04, "text": " But reachability is restricted based on an external economic condition that has absolutely nothing to do with the semantic content of the document itself.", "tokens": [51133, 583, 2524, 2310, 307, 20608, 2361, 322, 364, 8320, 4836, 4188, 300, 575, 3122, 1825, 281, 360, 365, 264, 47982, 2701, 295, 264, 4166, 2564, 13, 51590], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09599633864414545, "compression_ratio": 1.6015936254980079, "no_speech_prob": 2.020426144097587e-12}, {"id": 327, "seek": 136054, "start": 1385.34, "end": 1387.72, "text": " It doesn't matter what the scientific paper says.", "tokens": [51605, 467, 1177, 380, 1871, 437, 264, 8134, 3035, 1619, 13, 51724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09599633864414545, "compression_ratio": 1.6015936254980079, "no_speech_prob": 2.020426144097587e-12}, {"id": 328, "seek": 138772, "start": 1387.72, "end": 1393.48, "text": " It matters if your university paid Elsevier a massive subscription fee this year.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 7001, 498, 428, 5454, 4835, 45472, 85, 811, 257, 5994, 17231, 12054, 341, 1064, 13, 50653], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12643417630876813, "compression_ratio": 1.5495495495495495, "no_speech_prob": 1.769336305072755e-12}, {"id": 329, "seek": 138772, "start": 1394.14, "end": 1402.72, "text": " From the perspective of an independent researcher, a journalist, or just a curious citizen, the state is preserved but completely unreachable.", "tokens": [50686, 3358, 264, 4585, 295, 364, 6695, 21751, 11, 257, 17277, 11, 420, 445, 257, 6369, 13326, 11, 264, 1785, 307, 22242, 457, 2584, 517, 16226, 712, 13, 51115], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12643417630876813, "compression_ratio": 1.5495495495495495, "no_speech_prob": 1.769336305072755e-12}, {"id": 330, "seek": 138772, "start": 1404.0, "end": 1410.5, "text": " The citation points to an object that cannot be accessed through the transformations available to that specific person.", "tokens": [51179, 440, 45590, 2793, 281, 364, 2657, 300, 2644, 312, 34211, 807, 264, 34852, 2435, 281, 300, 2685, 954, 13, 51504], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12643417630876813, "compression_ratio": 1.5495495495495495, "no_speech_prob": 1.769336305072755e-12}, {"id": 331, "seek": 141050, "start": 1410.5, "end": 1415.32, "text": " It highlights that reachability isn't a universal truth, right?", "tokens": [50365, 467, 14254, 300, 2524, 2310, 1943, 380, 257, 11455, 3494, 11, 558, 30, 50606], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18444311207738415, "compression_ratio": 1.16, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970869576113603e-12}, {"id": 332, "seek": 141050, "start": 1415.46, "end": 1418.66, "text": " It is deeply subjective based on your access rights.", "tokens": [50613, 467, 307, 8760, 25972, 2361, 322, 428, 2105, 4601, 13, 50773], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18444311207738415, "compression_ratio": 1.16, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970869576113603e-12}, {"id": 333, "seek": 141866, "start": 1418.66, "end": 1421.5400000000002, "text": " It creates a bifurcated semantic landscape.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 7829, 257, 272, 351, 374, 66, 770, 47982, 9661, 13, 50509], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1952319201301126, "compression_ratio": 1.4734513274336283, "no_speech_prob": 1.810853008342439e-12}, {"id": 334, "seek": 141866, "start": 1422.16, "end": 1426.0400000000002, "text": " The graph looks completely different depending on your institutional affiliation.", "tokens": [50540, 440, 4295, 1542, 2584, 819, 5413, 322, 428, 18391, 14863, 399, 13, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1952319201301126, "compression_ratio": 1.4734513274336283, "no_speech_prob": 1.810853008342439e-12}, {"id": 335, "seek": 141866, "start": 1426.22, "end": 1429.1000000000001, "text": " But paywalls are, at least, artificial constraints.", "tokens": [50743, 583, 1689, 16256, 82, 366, 11, 412, 1935, 11, 11677, 18491, 13, 50887], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1952319201301126, "compression_ratio": 1.4734513274336283, "no_speech_prob": 1.810853008342439e-12}, {"id": 336, "seek": 141866, "start": 1429.76, "end": 1431.96, "text": " They can be removed by a policy change.", "tokens": [50920, 814, 393, 312, 7261, 538, 257, 3897, 1319, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1952319201301126, "compression_ratio": 1.4734513274336283, "no_speech_prob": 1.810853008342439e-12}, {"id": 337, "seek": 141866, "start": 1432.52, "end": 1436.4, "text": " The next failure mode, Flyxion Details, is much more final.", "tokens": [51058, 440, 958, 7763, 4391, 11, 3235, 970, 952, 42811, 11, 307, 709, 544, 2572, 13, 51252], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1952319201301126, "compression_ratio": 1.4734513274336283, "no_speech_prob": 1.810853008342439e-12}, {"id": 338, "seek": 141866, "start": 1436.9, "end": 1439.42, "text": " And it deals with the physical decay of the web itself.", "tokens": [51277, 400, 309, 11215, 365, 264, 4001, 21039, 295, 264, 3670, 2564, 13, 51403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1952319201301126, "compression_ratio": 1.4734513274336283, "no_speech_prob": 1.810853008342439e-12}, {"id": 339, "seek": 143942, "start": 1439.42, "end": 1442.94, "text": " What happens when the path just crumbles into the ocean?", "tokens": [50365, 708, 2314, 562, 264, 3100, 445, 941, 12255, 666, 264, 7810, 30, 50541], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 340, "seek": 143942, "start": 1443.16, "end": 1443.46, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50552, 7587, 13, 50567], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 341, "seek": 143942, "start": 1443.8600000000001, "end": 1447.38, "text": " This is link rot, or literal edge deletion.", "tokens": [50587, 639, 307, 2113, 4297, 11, 420, 20411, 4691, 1103, 302, 313, 13, 50763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 342, "seek": 143942, "start": 1447.5800000000002, "end": 1449.8400000000001, "text": " We all know the visceral frustration of this.", "tokens": [50773, 492, 439, 458, 264, 1452, 47879, 20491, 295, 341, 13, 50886], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 343, "seek": 143942, "start": 1449.94, "end": 1452.96, "text": " You're reading a fascinating article that makes a bold claim.", "tokens": [50891, 509, 434, 3760, 257, 10343, 7222, 300, 1669, 257, 11928, 3932, 13, 51042], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 344, "seek": 143942, "start": 1453.24, "end": 1459.94, "text": " You click the source link to verify it, and you get a blank white screen with bold black text.", "tokens": [51056, 509, 2052, 264, 4009, 2113, 281, 16888, 309, 11, 293, 291, 483, 257, 8247, 2418, 2568, 365, 11928, 2211, 2487, 13, 51391], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 345, "seek": 143942, "start": 1460.8400000000001, "end": 1461.9, "text": " 404 error.", "tokens": [51436, 3356, 19, 6713, 13, 51489], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 346, "seek": 143942, "start": 1462.8200000000002, "end": 1463.8000000000002, "text": " Page not found.", "tokens": [51535, 21217, 406, 1352, 13, 51584], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 347, "seek": 143942, "start": 1464.02, "end": 1464.9, "text": " So painful.", "tokens": [51595, 407, 11697, 13, 51639], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19206825256347657, "compression_ratio": 1.4747899159663866, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253695418194107e-12}, {"id": 348, "seek": 146490, "start": 1464.9, "end": 1467.3400000000001, "text": " It is the digital equivalent of a dead end.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 264, 4562, 10344, 295, 257, 3116, 917, 13, 50487], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13921941594874604, "compression_ratio": 1.5851851851851853, "no_speech_prob": 3.759084189758344e-12}, {"id": 349, "seek": 146490, "start": 1467.96, "end": 1476.2, "text": " But the paper brings in some truly stark data to quantify just how catastrophic this is for human knowledge.", "tokens": [50518, 583, 264, 3035, 5607, 294, 512, 4908, 17417, 1412, 281, 40421, 445, 577, 34915, 341, 307, 337, 1952, 3601, 13, 50930], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13921941594874604, "compression_ratio": 1.5851851851851853, "no_speech_prob": 3.759084189758344e-12}, {"id": 350, "seek": 146490, "start": 1476.7, "end": 1482.0, "text": " It references a massive 2014 study published in the journal PLOS1.", "tokens": [50955, 467, 15400, 257, 5994, 8227, 2979, 6572, 294, 264, 6708, 6999, 4367, 16, 13, 51220], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13921941594874604, "compression_ratio": 1.5851851851851853, "no_speech_prob": 3.759084189758344e-12}, {"id": 351, "seek": 146490, "start": 1482.8400000000001, "end": 1487.5400000000002, "text": " The researchers look specifically at the scholarly context papers relying on other papers,", "tokens": [51262, 440, 10309, 574, 4682, 412, 264, 39589, 4319, 10577, 24140, 322, 661, 10577, 11, 51497], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13921941594874604, "compression_ratio": 1.5851851851851853, "no_speech_prob": 3.759084189758344e-12}, {"id": 352, "seek": 146490, "start": 1488.1200000000001, "end": 1490.0400000000002, "text": " data sets relying on other data sets.", "tokens": [51526, 1412, 6352, 24140, 322, 661, 1412, 6352, 13, 51622], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13921941594874604, "compression_ratio": 1.5851851851851853, "no_speech_prob": 3.759084189758344e-12}, {"id": 353, "seek": 146490, "start": 1490.0400000000002, "end": 1494.4, "text": " They found that one in five articles suffers from what they call reference rot.", "tokens": [51622, 814, 1352, 300, 472, 294, 1732, 11290, 33776, 490, 437, 436, 818, 6408, 4297, 13, 51840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13921941594874604, "compression_ratio": 1.5851851851851853, "no_speech_prob": 3.759084189758344e-12}, {"id": 354, "seek": 149490, "start": 1494.9, "end": 1495.7, "text": " One in five.", "tokens": [50365, 1485, 294, 1732, 13, 50405], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 355, "seek": 149490, "start": 1496.0, "end": 1496.8600000000001, "text": " Twenty percent.", "tokens": [50420, 28789, 3043, 13, 50463], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 356, "seek": 149490, "start": 1497.24, "end": 1504.2800000000002, "text": " Over a period of just a few years, a fifth of the foundational evidence supporting modern scientific literature simply evaporates.", "tokens": [50482, 4886, 257, 2896, 295, 445, 257, 1326, 924, 11, 257, 9266, 295, 264, 32195, 4467, 7231, 4363, 8134, 10394, 2935, 26315, 1024, 13, 50834], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 357, "seek": 149490, "start": 1504.3400000000001, "end": 1504.98, "text": " That's wild.", "tokens": [50837, 663, 311, 4868, 13, 50869], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 358, "seek": 149490, "start": 1505.3400000000001, "end": 1510.18, "text": " This is a staggering rate of decay for systems we trust to build airplanes and cure diseases.", "tokens": [50887, 639, 307, 257, 42974, 3314, 295, 21039, 337, 3652, 321, 3361, 281, 1322, 32947, 293, 13698, 11044, 13, 51129], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 359, "seek": 149490, "start": 1510.7800000000002, "end": 1514.26, "text": " Web infrastructure links are the literal edges of our digital graph,", "tokens": [51159, 9573, 6896, 6123, 366, 264, 20411, 8819, 295, 527, 4562, 4295, 11, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 360, "seek": 149490, "start": 1514.5400000000002, "end": 1518.3600000000001, "text": " and those edges degrade rapidly due to pure administrative entropy.", "tokens": [51347, 293, 729, 8819, 368, 8692, 12910, 3462, 281, 6075, 17900, 30867, 13, 51538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16116721733756686, "compression_ratio": 1.5866141732283465, "no_speech_prob": 1.4899735091555844e-12}, {"id": 361, "seek": 151836, "start": 1518.36, "end": 1521.4199999999998, "text": " I want to paint a picture of how this actually plays out.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 528, 281, 4225, 257, 3036, 295, 577, 341, 767, 5749, 484, 13, 50518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18551489114761352, "compression_ratio": 1.5665236051502145, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362795651041043e-12}, {"id": 362, "seek": 151836, "start": 1522.3799999999999, "end": 1527.6, "text": " Imagine a medical researcher trying to replicate a crucial study on a new cancer treatment.", "tokens": [50566, 11739, 257, 4625, 21751, 1382, 281, 25356, 257, 11462, 2979, 322, 257, 777, 5592, 5032, 13, 50827], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18551489114761352, "compression_ratio": 1.5665236051502145, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362795651041043e-12}, {"id": 363, "seek": 151836, "start": 1527.9799999999998, "end": 1533.1799999999998, "text": " The original paper from 2018 references a massive data set of patient responses.", "tokens": [50846, 440, 3380, 3035, 490, 6096, 15400, 257, 5994, 1412, 992, 295, 4537, 13019, 13, 51106], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18551489114761352, "compression_ratio": 1.5665236051502145, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362795651041043e-12}, {"id": 364, "seek": 151836, "start": 1534.24, "end": 1537.1599999999999, "text": " The researcher clicks the link to download the data set.", "tokens": [51159, 440, 21751, 18521, 264, 2113, 281, 5484, 264, 1412, 992, 13, 51305], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18551489114761352, "compression_ratio": 1.5665236051502145, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362795651041043e-12}, {"id": 365, "seek": 151836, "start": 1537.6, "end": 1542.58, "text": " But the domain registration lapsed because the original lab lost its funding,", "tokens": [51327, 583, 264, 9274, 16847, 24971, 292, 570, 264, 3380, 2715, 2731, 1080, 6137, 11, 51576], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18551489114761352, "compression_ratio": 1.5665236051502145, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362795651041043e-12}, {"id": 366, "seek": 154258, "start": 1542.58, "end": 1546.84, "text": " and the admin forgot to renew the $20 GoDaddy fee.", "tokens": [50365, 293, 264, 24236, 5298, 281, 10162, 264, 1848, 2009, 1037, 14599, 3173, 12054, 13, 50578], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22965116086213486, "compression_ratio": 1.3475609756097562, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182127895297051e-12}, {"id": 367, "seek": 154258, "start": 1547.36, "end": 1547.6399999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50604, 1779, 13, 50618], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22965116086213486, "compression_ratio": 1.3475609756097562, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182127895297051e-12}, {"id": 368, "seek": 154258, "start": 1547.78, "end": 1548.72, "text": " A $20 fee.", "tokens": [50625, 316, 1848, 2009, 12054, 13, 50672], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22965116086213486, "compression_ratio": 1.3475609756097562, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182127895297051e-12}, {"id": 369, "seek": 154258, "start": 1549.26, "end": 1554.0, "text": " The URL now redirects to a park page selling herbal supplements.", "tokens": [50699, 440, 12905, 586, 29066, 82, 281, 257, 3884, 3028, 6511, 44255, 26645, 13, 50936], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22965116086213486, "compression_ratio": 1.3475609756097562, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182127895297051e-12}, {"id": 370, "seek": 154258, "start": 1554.0, "end": 1559.74, "text": " And the tragedy is that the node, the actual data set, might still exist.", "tokens": [50936, 400, 264, 18563, 307, 300, 264, 9984, 11, 264, 3539, 1412, 992, 11, 1062, 920, 2514, 13, 51223], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22965116086213486, "compression_ratio": 1.3475609756097562, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182127895297051e-12}, {"id": 371, "seek": 154258, "start": 1560.1399999999999, "end": 1560.84, "text": " Wait, really?", "tokens": [51243, 3802, 11, 534, 30, 51278], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22965116086213486, "compression_ratio": 1.3475609756097562, "no_speech_prob": 1.8182127895297051e-12}, {"id": 372, "seek": 156084, "start": 1560.84, "end": 1561.26, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 13, 50386], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 373, "seek": 156084, "start": 1561.52, "end": 1566.76, "text": " It might be sitting on a hard drive in a desk drawer in that original researcher's office,", "tokens": [50399, 467, 1062, 312, 3798, 322, 257, 1152, 3332, 294, 257, 10026, 24039, 294, 300, 3380, 21751, 311, 3398, 11, 50661], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 374, "seek": 156084, "start": 1567.08, "end": 1572.8999999999999, "text": " or it might have been migrated to a new university server under a different folder structure.", "tokens": [50677, 420, 309, 1062, 362, 668, 48329, 281, 257, 777, 5454, 7154, 833, 257, 819, 10820, 3877, 13, 50968], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 375, "seek": 156084, "start": 1573.54, "end": 1576.56, "text": " The preservation of the data might be perfectly fine.", "tokens": [51000, 440, 27257, 295, 264, 1412, 1062, 312, 6239, 2489, 13, 51151], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 376, "seek": 156084, "start": 1576.6399999999999, "end": 1577.72, "text": " But you can't get to it.", "tokens": [51155, 583, 291, 393, 380, 483, 281, 309, 13, 51209], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 377, "seek": 156084, "start": 1577.98, "end": 1580.82, "text": " Because the literal edge, the URL, is deleted,", "tokens": [51222, 1436, 264, 20411, 4691, 11, 264, 12905, 11, 307, 22981, 11, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 378, "seek": 156084, "start": 1581.1799999999998, "end": 1584.98, "text": " there is absolutely no path from the present state to that node.", "tokens": [51382, 456, 307, 3122, 572, 3100, 490, 264, 1974, 1785, 281, 300, 9984, 13, 51572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 379, "seek": 156084, "start": 1585.4199999999998, "end": 1588.3999999999999, "text": " The failure isn't a lack of a backup policy.", "tokens": [51594, 440, 7763, 1943, 380, 257, 5011, 295, 257, 14807, 3897, 13, 51743], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1766537482585382, "compression_ratio": 1.6015037593984962, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013990043224236e-12}, {"id": 380, "seek": 158840, "start": 1588.4, "end": 1592.02, "text": " It's a failure of ongoing infrastructure maintenance.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 257, 7763, 295, 10452, 6896, 11258, 13, 50546], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 381, "seek": 158840, "start": 1592.76, "end": 1596.64, "text": " The transformation that existed yesterday simply does not exist today.", "tokens": [50583, 440, 9887, 300, 13135, 5186, 2935, 775, 406, 2514, 965, 13, 50777], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 382, "seek": 158840, "start": 1596.9, "end": 1601.5, "text": " It is a citation without an object, a pointer aiming at a void.", "tokens": [50790, 467, 307, 257, 45590, 1553, 364, 2657, 11, 257, 23918, 20253, 412, 257, 22009, 13, 51020], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 383, "seek": 158840, "start": 1601.7, "end": 1608.3600000000001, "text": " Okay, so we've looked at paths being overwritten, compressed, paywalled, and literally rotting away.", "tokens": [51030, 1033, 11, 370, 321, 600, 2956, 412, 14518, 885, 670, 26859, 11, 30353, 11, 1689, 86, 8907, 11, 293, 3736, 4297, 783, 1314, 13, 51363], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 384, "seek": 158840, "start": 1609.22, "end": 1613.52, "text": " But what if the preservation is perfect, there's no paywall, the link isn't broken,", "tokens": [51406, 583, 437, 498, 264, 27257, 307, 2176, 11, 456, 311, 572, 1689, 16256, 11, 264, 2113, 1943, 380, 5463, 11, 51621], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 385, "seek": 158840, "start": 1613.64, "end": 1616.6200000000001, "text": " but the map itself is written in a language you don't speak?", "tokens": [51627, 457, 264, 4471, 2564, 307, 3720, 294, 257, 2856, 291, 500, 380, 1710, 30, 51776], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 386, "seek": 158840, "start": 1616.72, "end": 1617.02, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51781, 1779, 13, 51796], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16871060551823797, "compression_ratio": 1.5806451612903225, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582686167085583e-12}, {"id": 387, "seek": 161702, "start": 1617.02, "end": 1621.86, "text": " This brings us to the fifth failure mode, archival isolation.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 9266, 7763, 4391, 11, 3912, 3576, 16001, 13, 50607], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 388, "seek": 161702, "start": 1622.1399999999999, "end": 1624.16, "text": " This is what happens when you have node preservation,", "tokens": [50621, 639, 307, 437, 2314, 562, 291, 362, 9984, 27257, 11, 50722], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 389, "seek": 161702, "start": 1624.76, "end": 1629.3, "text": " but immense path loss due to the mismatch between the archive and the user.", "tokens": [50752, 457, 22920, 3100, 4470, 3462, 281, 264, 23220, 852, 1296, 264, 23507, 293, 264, 4195, 13, 50979], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 390, "seek": 161702, "start": 1630.22, "end": 1636.22, "text": " The paper uses a very powerful and sobering example, the September 11th Digital Archive.", "tokens": [51025, 440, 3035, 4960, 257, 588, 4005, 293, 26212, 278, 1365, 11, 264, 7216, 2975, 392, 15522, 10984, 488, 13, 51325], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 391, "seek": 161702, "start": 1636.32, "end": 1636.54, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51330, 1779, 13, 51341], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 392, "seek": 161702, "start": 1636.8, "end": 1641.54, "text": " This archive is maintained by the Roy Rosenzweig Center for History and New Media,", "tokens": [51354, 639, 23507, 307, 17578, 538, 264, 8751, 33630, 89, 826, 328, 5169, 337, 12486, 293, 1873, 14741, 11, 51591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 393, "seek": 161702, "start": 1641.84, "end": 1644.76, "text": " and it is held in partnership with the Library of Congress.", "tokens": [51606, 293, 309, 307, 5167, 294, 9982, 365, 264, 12806, 295, 6426, 13, 51752], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15578775585822338, "compression_ratio": 1.5808823529411764, "no_speech_prob": 1.6363638959474014e-12}, {"id": 394, "seek": 164476, "start": 1644.76, "end": 1649.0, "text": " By all technical metrics, it is a masterpiece of digital preservation.", "tokens": [50365, 3146, 439, 6191, 16367, 11, 309, 307, 257, 32208, 295, 4562, 27257, 13, 50577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18195424360387466, "compression_ratio": 1.0, "no_speech_prob": 1.846560231111294e-12}, {"id": 395, "seek": 164900, "start": 1649.0, "end": 1650.92, "text": " It's beautifully maintained.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 16525, 17578, 13, 50461], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19241563735469694, "compression_ratio": 1.4791666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 2.108825050348151e-12}, {"id": 396, "seek": 164900, "start": 1650.92, "end": 1657.82, "text": " It holds a substantial, vital record of firsthand accounts, emails, digital photographs, and artifacts,", "tokens": [50461, 467, 9190, 257, 16726, 11, 11707, 2136, 295, 38599, 9402, 11, 12524, 11, 4562, 17649, 11, 293, 24617, 11, 50806], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19241563735469694, "compression_ratio": 1.4791666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 2.108825050348151e-12}, {"id": 397, "seek": 164900, "start": 1658.28, "end": 1662.66, "text": " all capturing the raw, immediate human experience of 2001.", "tokens": [50829, 439, 23384, 264, 8936, 11, 11629, 1952, 1752, 295, 16382, 13, 51048], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19241563735469694, "compression_ratio": 1.4791666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 2.108825050348151e-12}, {"id": 398, "seek": 164900, "start": 1663.28, "end": 1670.46, "text": " It is a deliberate, serious, highly funded attempt to maintain digital states against decay.", "tokens": [51079, 467, 307, 257, 30515, 11, 3156, 11, 5405, 14385, 5217, 281, 6909, 4562, 4368, 1970, 21039, 13, 51438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19241563735469694, "compression_ratio": 1.4791666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 2.108825050348151e-12}, {"id": 399, "seek": 167046, "start": 1670.46, "end": 1673.74, "text": " The nodes are preserved with the utmost care.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 13891, 366, 22242, 365, 264, 42777, 1127, 13, 50529], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22305028669295773, "compression_ratio": 1.4602272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.83219932281542e-12}, {"id": 400, "seek": 167046, "start": 1673.74, "end": 1675.68, "text": " But the reachability fails.", "tokens": [50529, 583, 264, 2524, 2310, 18199, 13, 50626], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22305028669295773, "compression_ratio": 1.4602272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.83219932281542e-12}, {"id": 401, "seek": 167046, "start": 1675.8400000000001, "end": 1676.1000000000001, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50634, 865, 13, 50647], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22305028669295773, "compression_ratio": 1.4602272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.83219932281542e-12}, {"id": 402, "seek": 167046, "start": 1676.32, "end": 1679.78, "text": " And it fails not because of rot, but because of isolation.", "tokens": [50658, 400, 309, 18199, 406, 570, 295, 4297, 11, 457, 570, 295, 16001, 13, 50831], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22305028669295773, "compression_ratio": 1.4602272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.83219932281542e-12}, {"id": 403, "seek": 167046, "start": 1680.92, "end": 1689.44, "text": " Flyxion points out that this incredible, historically vital archive is not indexed by major commercial search engines", "tokens": [50888, 3235, 4105, 2793, 484, 300, 341, 4651, 11, 16180, 11707, 23507, 307, 406, 8186, 292, 538, 2563, 6841, 3164, 12982, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22305028669295773, "compression_ratio": 1.4602272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 1.83219932281542e-12}, {"id": 404, "seek": 168944, "start": 1689.44, "end": 1692.8200000000002, "text": " in ways that surface it for relevant general queries.", "tokens": [50365, 294, 2098, 300, 3753, 309, 337, 7340, 2674, 24109, 13, 50534], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 405, "seek": 168944, "start": 1693.06, "end": 1693.3400000000001, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50546, 1779, 13, 50560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 406, "seek": 168944, "start": 1693.3400000000001, "end": 1697.1200000000001, "text": " If a high school student today types a natural language question like,", "tokens": [50560, 759, 257, 1090, 1395, 3107, 965, 3467, 257, 3303, 2856, 1168, 411, 11, 50749], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 407, "seek": 168944, "start": 1697.6200000000001, "end": 1700.88, "text": " what was it like to be New York on 9-11 into Google or Bing,", "tokens": [50774, 437, 390, 309, 411, 281, 312, 1873, 3609, 322, 1722, 12, 5348, 666, 3329, 420, 30755, 11, 50937], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 408, "seek": 168944, "start": 1701.44, "end": 1705.5800000000002, "text": " they are directed to Wikipedia articles, news summaries, and history blogs.", "tokens": [50965, 436, 366, 12898, 281, 28999, 11290, 11, 2583, 8367, 4889, 11, 293, 2503, 31038, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 409, "seek": 168944, "start": 1705.74, "end": 1706.04, "text": " Mm-hmm.", "tokens": [51180, 8266, 12, 10250, 13, 51195], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 410, "seek": 168944, "start": 1706.14, "end": 1708.88, "text": " They're almost never directed to this primary source archive.", "tokens": [51200, 814, 434, 1920, 1128, 12898, 281, 341, 6194, 4009, 23507, 13, 51337], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17318218404596503, "compression_ratio": 1.4382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619922669006137e-12}, {"id": 411, "seek": 170888, "start": 1708.88, "end": 1715.22, "text": " Because users who don't already know this specific archive exists typically only discover it through secondary references,", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 5022, 567, 500, 380, 1217, 458, 341, 2685, 23507, 8198, 5850, 787, 4411, 309, 807, 11396, 15400, 11, 50682], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 412, "seek": 170888, "start": 1715.8400000000001, "end": 1719.0600000000002, "text": " maybe a citation in an academic paper they happen to read,", "tokens": [50713, 1310, 257, 45590, 294, 364, 7778, 3035, 436, 1051, 281, 1401, 11, 50874], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 413, "seek": 170888, "start": 1719.2800000000002, "end": 1722.1200000000001, "text": " or digging through specialized library portals.", "tokens": [50885, 420, 17343, 807, 19813, 6405, 2436, 1124, 13, 51027], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 414, "seek": 170888, "start": 1722.3200000000002, "end": 1728.24, "text": " And what's fascinating here is that it allows Flyxion to introduce a crucial mathematical concept.", "tokens": [51037, 400, 437, 311, 10343, 510, 307, 300, 309, 4045, 3235, 4105, 281, 5366, 257, 11462, 18894, 3410, 13, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 415, "seek": 170888, "start": 1729.1000000000001, "end": 1732.5400000000002, "text": " Reachability is not just a binary property of a system.", "tokens": [51376, 35904, 2310, 307, 406, 445, 257, 17434, 4707, 295, 257, 1185, 13, 51548], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 416, "seek": 170888, "start": 1732.92, "end": 1734.18, "text": " It's not just a yes or no.", "tokens": [51567, 467, 311, 406, 445, 257, 2086, 420, 572, 13, 51630], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 417, "seek": 170888, "start": 1734.2600000000002, "end": 1737.9, "text": " No, it's not a simple checklist of is it reachable, yes or no.", "tokens": [51634, 883, 11, 309, 311, 406, 257, 2199, 30357, 295, 307, 309, 2524, 712, 11, 2086, 420, 572, 13, 51816], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15001145430973598, "compression_ratio": 1.621160409556314, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508335918905217e-12}, {"id": 418, "seek": 173790, "start": 1737.9, "end": 1742.64, "text": " Reachability is mathematically defined as a function of two distinctive variables.", "tokens": [50365, 35904, 2310, 307, 44003, 7642, 382, 257, 2445, 295, 732, 27766, 9102, 13, 50602], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 419, "seek": 173790, "start": 1743.48, "end": 1748.68, "text": " The graph, which they call G, and the agent's capabilities, which they call A.", "tokens": [50644, 440, 4295, 11, 597, 436, 818, 460, 11, 293, 264, 9461, 311, 10862, 11, 597, 436, 818, 316, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 420, "seek": 173790, "start": 1749.0400000000002, "end": 1752.3200000000002, "text": " So the formula is G, A.", "tokens": [50922, 407, 264, 8513, 307, 460, 11, 316, 13, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 421, "seek": 173790, "start": 1752.5400000000002, "end": 1754.14, "text": " Wait, so it's a literal formula.", "tokens": [51097, 3802, 11, 370, 309, 311, 257, 20411, 8513, 13, 51177], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 422, "seek": 173790, "start": 1754.46, "end": 1755.68, "text": " The graph and the agent.", "tokens": [51193, 440, 4295, 293, 264, 9461, 13, 51254], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 423, "seek": 173790, "start": 1755.8600000000001, "end": 1756.18, "text": " Mm-hmm.", "tokens": [51263, 8266, 12, 10250, 13, 51279], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 424, "seek": 173790, "start": 1756.3400000000001, "end": 1758.0, "text": " The landscape and the map reader.", "tokens": [51287, 440, 9661, 293, 264, 4471, 15149, 13, 51370], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 425, "seek": 173790, "start": 1758.24, "end": 1758.8000000000002, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51382, 7587, 13, 51410], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 426, "seek": 173790, "start": 1759.2, "end": 1761.18, "text": " This is a massive paradigm shift.", "tokens": [51430, 639, 307, 257, 5994, 24709, 5513, 13, 51529], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21037832561292147, "compression_ratio": 1.6157635467980296, "no_speech_prob": 2.740069022372227e-12}, {"id": 427, "seek": 176118, "start": 1761.18, "end": 1770.54, "text": " It means two people inhabiting the exact same internet actually inhabit completely different effective graphs based on their A value.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1355, 732, 561, 16934, 1748, 264, 1900, 912, 4705, 767, 21863, 2584, 819, 4942, 24877, 2361, 322, 641, 316, 2158, 13, 50833], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1501122686598036, "compression_ratio": 1.5880149812734083, "no_speech_prob": 1.4496141917050287e-12}, {"id": 428, "seek": 176118, "start": 1770.76, "end": 1771.1000000000001, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50844, 1079, 13, 50861], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1501122686598036, "compression_ratio": 1.5880149812734083, "no_speech_prob": 1.4496141917050287e-12}, {"id": 429, "seek": 176118, "start": 1771.68, "end": 1773.9, "text": " The available transformations aren't universal.", "tokens": [50890, 440, 2435, 34852, 3212, 380, 11455, 13, 51001], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1501122686598036, "compression_ratio": 1.5880149812734083, "no_speech_prob": 1.4496141917050287e-12}, {"id": 430, "seek": 176118, "start": 1774.54, "end": 1778.52, "text": " A credentialed, highly trained archivist knows the Boolean search operators,", "tokens": [51033, 316, 22034, 292, 11, 5405, 8895, 3912, 592, 468, 3255, 264, 23351, 28499, 3164, 19077, 11, 51232], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1501122686598036, "compression_ratio": 1.5880149812734083, "no_speech_prob": 1.4496141917050287e-12}, {"id": 431, "seek": 176118, "start": 1779.04, "end": 1784.26, "text": " knows the specific institutional URLs, and understands the metadata taxonomy.", "tokens": [51258, 3255, 264, 2685, 18391, 43267, 11, 293, 15146, 264, 26603, 3366, 23423, 13, 51519], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1501122686598036, "compression_ratio": 1.5880149812734083, "no_speech_prob": 1.4496141917050287e-12}, {"id": 432, "seek": 176118, "start": 1784.8, "end": 1789.5600000000002, "text": " Their A value allows them to traverse the graph and find the 911 emails instantly.", "tokens": [51546, 6710, 316, 2158, 4045, 552, 281, 45674, 264, 4295, 293, 915, 264, 26901, 12524, 13518, 13, 51784], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1501122686598036, "compression_ratio": 1.5880149812734083, "no_speech_prob": 1.4496141917050287e-12}, {"id": 433, "seek": 178956, "start": 1789.56, "end": 1796.94, "text": " But to a general learner who relies entirely on commercial search algorithms parsing natural language,", "tokens": [50365, 583, 281, 257, 2674, 33347, 567, 30910, 7696, 322, 6841, 3164, 14642, 21156, 278, 3303, 2856, 11, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12353627093426593, "compression_ratio": 1.5650224215246638, "no_speech_prob": 1.6232330150162122e-12}, {"id": 434, "seek": 178956, "start": 1797.58, "end": 1799.3799999999999, "text": " their A value is different.", "tokens": [50766, 641, 316, 2158, 307, 819, 13, 50856], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12353627093426593, "compression_ratio": 1.5650224215246638, "no_speech_prob": 1.6232330150162122e-12}, {"id": 435, "seek": 178956, "start": 1800.06, "end": 1802.2, "text": " To them, the archive is invisible.", "tokens": [50890, 1407, 552, 11, 264, 23507, 307, 14603, 13, 50997], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12353627093426593, "compression_ratio": 1.5650224215246638, "no_speech_prob": 1.6232330150162122e-12}, {"id": 436, "seek": 178956, "start": 1802.8799999999999, "end": 1811.0, "text": " An archive reachable only by specialists is not reachable in the sense that matters for broad societal semantic continuity.", "tokens": [51031, 1107, 23507, 2524, 712, 787, 538, 25476, 307, 406, 2524, 712, 294, 264, 2020, 300, 7001, 337, 4152, 33472, 47982, 23807, 13, 51437], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12353627093426593, "compression_ratio": 1.5650224215246638, "no_speech_prob": 1.6232330150162122e-12}, {"id": 437, "seek": 178956, "start": 1811.32, "end": 1813.8999999999999, "text": " We fall right back to the library with a scrambled catalog.", "tokens": [51453, 492, 2100, 558, 646, 281, 264, 6405, 365, 257, 49127, 19746, 13, 51582], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12353627093426593, "compression_ratio": 1.5650224215246638, "no_speech_prob": 1.6232330150162122e-12}, {"id": 438, "seek": 181390, "start": 1813.9, "end": 1819.4, "text": " It's perfectly safe, but practically invisible to the person walking in off the street.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 6239, 3273, 11, 457, 15667, 14603, 281, 264, 954, 4494, 294, 766, 264, 4838, 13, 50640], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13422733017160923, "compression_ratio": 1.4656862745098038, "no_speech_prob": 2.092736357470204e-12}, {"id": 439, "seek": 181390, "start": 1819.76, "end": 1821.66, "text": " So what does this all mean?", "tokens": [50658, 407, 437, 775, 341, 439, 914, 30, 50753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13422733017160923, "compression_ratio": 1.4656862745098038, "no_speech_prob": 2.092736357470204e-12}, {"id": 440, "seek": 181390, "start": 1822.3000000000002, "end": 1830.92, "text": " When we look at this entire taxonomy, namespace laundering, encyclopedic consolidation, gated edges, link rot, and archival isolation,", "tokens": [50785, 1133, 321, 574, 412, 341, 2302, 3366, 23423, 11, 5288, 17940, 17245, 1794, 11, 465, 34080, 27277, 299, 39114, 11, 290, 770, 8819, 11, 2113, 4297, 11, 293, 3912, 3576, 16001, 11, 51216], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13422733017160923, "compression_ratio": 1.4656862745098038, "no_speech_prob": 2.092736357470204e-12}, {"id": 441, "seek": 181390, "start": 1831.48, "end": 1833.26, "text": " it paints a pretty grim picture.", "tokens": [51244, 309, 28076, 257, 1238, 36010, 3036, 13, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13422733017160923, "compression_ratio": 1.4656862745098038, "no_speech_prob": 2.092736357470204e-12}, {"id": 442, "seek": 181390, "start": 1833.52, "end": 1834.22, "text": " It really does.", "tokens": [51346, 467, 534, 775, 13, 51381], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13422733017160923, "compression_ratio": 1.4656862745098038, "no_speech_prob": 2.092736357470204e-12}, {"id": 443, "seek": 183422, "start": 1834.22, "end": 1838.98, "text": " It means that preservation is actually a deeply relative, almost comforting fiction.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1355, 300, 27257, 307, 767, 257, 8760, 4972, 11, 1920, 38439, 13266, 13, 50603], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12817288459615506, "compression_ratio": 1.7478632478632479, "no_speech_prob": 1.8253350220209796e-12}, {"id": 444, "seek": 183422, "start": 1839.52, "end": 1845.3600000000001, "text": " You can have the most heavily fortified, perfectly backed up, climate-controlled digital vault in human history.", "tokens": [50630, 509, 393, 362, 264, 881, 10950, 5009, 2587, 11, 6239, 20391, 493, 11, 5659, 12, 49344, 4562, 27134, 294, 1952, 2503, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12817288459615506, "compression_ratio": 1.7478632478632479, "no_speech_prob": 1.8253350220209796e-12}, {"id": 445, "seek": 183422, "start": 1845.64, "end": 1852.66, "text": " But if you don't have the map, or you don't have the institutional keys, or you don't have the specialized training to navigate the interface,", "tokens": [50936, 583, 498, 291, 500, 380, 362, 264, 4471, 11, 420, 291, 500, 380, 362, 264, 18391, 9317, 11, 420, 291, 500, 380, 362, 264, 19813, 3097, 281, 12350, 264, 9226, 11, 51287], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12817288459615506, "compression_ratio": 1.7478632478632479, "no_speech_prob": 1.8253350220209796e-12}, {"id": 446, "seek": 183422, "start": 1853.38, "end": 1855.88, "text": " that knowledge is functionally dead to you.", "tokens": [51323, 300, 3601, 307, 2445, 379, 3116, 281, 291, 13, 51448], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12817288459615506, "compression_ratio": 1.7478632478632479, "no_speech_prob": 1.8253350220209796e-12}, {"id": 447, "seek": 183422, "start": 1856.16, "end": 1857.6000000000001, "text": " It is functionally dead.", "tokens": [51462, 467, 307, 2445, 379, 3116, 13, 51534], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12817288459615506, "compression_ratio": 1.7478632478632479, "no_speech_prob": 1.8253350220209796e-12}, {"id": 448, "seek": 185760, "start": 1857.6, "end": 1861.56, "text": " And these aren't edge cases or temporary glitches.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 613, 3212, 380, 4691, 3331, 420, 13413, 23552, 279, 13, 50563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15401266135421454, "compression_ratio": 1.4817073170731707, "no_speech_prob": 1.617155628158562e-12}, {"id": 449, "seek": 185760, "start": 1862.04, "end": 1866.9599999999998, "text": " These five modes are the normal operating conditions of our digital infrastructure.", "tokens": [50587, 1981, 1732, 14068, 366, 264, 2710, 7447, 4487, 295, 527, 4562, 6896, 13, 50833], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15401266135421454, "compression_ratio": 1.4817073170731707, "no_speech_prob": 1.617155628158562e-12}, {"id": 450, "seek": 185760, "start": 1867.62, "end": 1875.06, "text": " They all demonstrate how preserving the object completely fails to preserve the meaning if the path is lost.", "tokens": [50866, 814, 439, 11698, 577, 33173, 264, 2657, 2584, 18199, 281, 15665, 264, 3620, 498, 264, 3100, 307, 2731, 13, 51238], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15401266135421454, "compression_ratio": 1.4817073170731707, "no_speech_prob": 1.617155628158562e-12}, {"id": 451, "seek": 187506, "start": 1875.06, "end": 1882.44, "text": " If our massive digital archives and server farms are functionally isolating information and allowing paths to rot,", "tokens": [50365, 759, 527, 5994, 4562, 25607, 293, 7154, 20366, 366, 2445, 379, 48912, 1589, 293, 8293, 14518, 281, 4297, 11, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 452, "seek": 187506, "start": 1883.5, "end": 1885.72, "text": " we have to ask a massive question.", "tokens": [50787, 321, 362, 281, 1029, 257, 5994, 1168, 13, 50898], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 453, "seek": 187506, "start": 1886.6399999999999, "end": 1890.94, "text": " Did humanity ever solve this before server farms existed?", "tokens": [50944, 2589, 10243, 1562, 5039, 341, 949, 7154, 20366, 13135, 30, 51159], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 454, "seek": 187506, "start": 1891.1599999999999, "end": 1891.3999999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51170, 1779, 13, 51182], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 455, "seek": 187506, "start": 1891.6599999999999, "end": 1894.62, "text": " Is there any system that actually gets this right?", "tokens": [51195, 1119, 456, 604, 1185, 300, 767, 2170, 341, 558, 30, 51343], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 456, "seek": 187506, "start": 1894.72, "end": 1899.3799999999999, "text": " Because if we want to figure out how to fix our current mess, we need a success mode.", "tokens": [51348, 1436, 498, 321, 528, 281, 2573, 484, 577, 281, 3191, 527, 2190, 2082, 11, 321, 643, 257, 2245, 4391, 13, 51581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 457, "seek": 187506, "start": 1899.72, "end": 1904.1599999999999, "text": " And this is where Flishan's paper takes a brilliant, unexpected turn.", "tokens": [51598, 400, 341, 307, 689, 3235, 742, 282, 311, 3035, 2516, 257, 10248, 11, 13106, 1261, 13, 51820], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18213186264038086, "compression_ratio": 1.588679245283019, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108450936665799e-12}, {"id": 458, "seek": 190506, "start": 1905.06, "end": 1910.6599999999999, "text": " To find a system that succeeds at reachability, we have to look completely away from the digital realm.", "tokens": [50365, 1407, 915, 257, 1185, 300, 49263, 412, 2524, 2310, 11, 321, 362, 281, 574, 2584, 1314, 490, 264, 4562, 15355, 13, 50645], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 459, "seek": 190506, "start": 1910.84, "end": 1911.12, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50654, 1079, 13, 50668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 460, "seek": 190506, "start": 1911.54, "end": 1917.46, "text": " We have to look at ancient oral traditions, at local villages, craft guilds, and the breadth of human voices.", "tokens": [50689, 492, 362, 281, 574, 412, 7832, 19338, 15643, 11, 412, 2654, 20444, 11, 8448, 37435, 82, 11, 293, 264, 35862, 295, 1952, 9802, 13, 50985], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 461, "seek": 190506, "start": 1917.78, "end": 1919.98, "text": " A village, the voice, and generational time.", "tokens": [51001, 316, 7288, 11, 264, 3177, 11, 293, 48320, 565, 13, 51111], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 462, "seek": 190506, "start": 1920.2, "end": 1923.6599999999999, "text": " The paper's sixth case completely inverts the pattern we've been discussing.", "tokens": [51122, 440, 3035, 311, 15102, 1389, 2584, 28653, 1373, 264, 5102, 321, 600, 668, 10850, 13, 51295], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 463, "seek": 190506, "start": 1924.1799999999998, "end": 1927.44, "text": " It examines a system where reachability is effectively guaranteed,", "tokens": [51321, 467, 1139, 1652, 257, 1185, 689, 2524, 2310, 307, 8659, 18031, 11, 51484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 464, "seek": 190506, "start": 1927.84, "end": 1932.56, "text": " but it achieves this with almost zero formal archival infrastructure.", "tokens": [51504, 457, 309, 3538, 977, 341, 365, 1920, 4018, 9860, 3912, 3576, 6896, 13, 51740], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 465, "seek": 190506, "start": 1932.78, "end": 1933.5, "text": " Zero infrastructure.", "tokens": [51751, 17182, 6896, 13, 51787], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13582557742878543, "compression_ratio": 1.6996587030716723, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112864723709987e-12}, {"id": 466, "seek": 193350, "start": 1933.5, "end": 1934.02, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50391], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2094742255874827, "compression_ratio": 1.4832535885167464, "no_speech_prob": 1.875913703888732e-12}, {"id": 467, "seek": 193350, "start": 1934.28, "end": 1937.76, "text": " It's guaranteed by what the author calls path density.", "tokens": [50404, 467, 311, 18031, 538, 437, 264, 3793, 5498, 3100, 10305, 13, 50578], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2094742255874827, "compression_ratio": 1.4832535885167464, "no_speech_prob": 1.875913703888732e-12}, {"id": 468, "seek": 193350, "start": 1938.56, "end": 1940.82, "text": " Consider a dense local system.", "tokens": [50618, 17416, 257, 18011, 2654, 1185, 13, 50731], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2094742255874827, "compression_ratio": 1.4832535885167464, "no_speech_prob": 1.875913703888732e-12}, {"id": 469, "seek": 193350, "start": 1941.12, "end": 1945.02, "text": " This could be a traditional craft guild passing down masonry techniques,", "tokens": [50746, 639, 727, 312, 257, 5164, 8448, 37435, 8437, 760, 275, 1258, 627, 7512, 11, 50941], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2094742255874827, "compression_ratio": 1.4832535885167464, "no_speech_prob": 1.875913703888732e-12}, {"id": 470, "seek": 193350, "start": 1945.48, "end": 1949.52, "text": " a tight-knit neighborhood with deep roots, a religious congregation,", "tokens": [50964, 257, 4524, 12, 5457, 270, 7630, 365, 2452, 10669, 11, 257, 7185, 34782, 11, 51166], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2094742255874827, "compression_ratio": 1.4832535885167464, "no_speech_prob": 1.875913703888732e-12}, {"id": 471, "seek": 193350, "start": 1949.92, "end": 1954.72, "text": " or a multi-generational family that has farmed the same land for a century.", "tokens": [51186, 420, 257, 4825, 12, 21848, 1478, 1605, 300, 575, 1400, 1912, 264, 912, 2117, 337, 257, 4901, 13, 51426], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2094742255874827, "compression_ratio": 1.4832535885167464, "no_speech_prob": 1.875913703888732e-12}, {"id": 472, "seek": 195472, "start": 1954.72, "end": 1960.24, "text": " But if you look at these groups through the lens of a modern data scientist or archivist,", "tokens": [50365, 583, 498, 291, 574, 412, 613, 3935, 807, 264, 6765, 295, 257, 4363, 1412, 12662, 420, 3912, 592, 468, 11, 50641], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1893307367960612, "compression_ratio": 1.5367965367965368, "no_speech_prob": 2.4260381030483114e-12}, {"id": 473, "seek": 195472, "start": 1960.4, "end": 1962.34, "text": " they are an absolute nightmare.", "tokens": [50649, 436, 366, 364, 8236, 18724, 13, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1893307367960612, "compression_ratio": 1.5367965367965368, "no_speech_prob": 2.4260381030483114e-12}, {"id": 474, "seek": 195472, "start": 1962.56, "end": 1963.4, "text": " Oh, completely.", "tokens": [50757, 876, 11, 2584, 13, 50799], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1893307367960612, "compression_ratio": 1.5367965367965368, "no_speech_prob": 2.4260381030483114e-12}, {"id": 475, "seek": 195472, "start": 1963.64, "end": 1969.24, "text": " They have terrible formal archival storage, no indexed records or digitized vaults.", "tokens": [50811, 814, 362, 6237, 9860, 3912, 3576, 6725, 11, 572, 8186, 292, 7724, 420, 14293, 1602, 27134, 82, 13, 51091], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1893307367960612, "compression_ratio": 1.5367965367965368, "no_speech_prob": 2.4260381030483114e-12}, {"id": 476, "seek": 195472, "start": 1969.98, "end": 1975.42, "text": " There is no off-site climate-controlled server backup for the guild's techniques.", "tokens": [51128, 821, 307, 572, 766, 12, 30417, 5659, 12, 49344, 7154, 14807, 337, 264, 37435, 311, 7512, 13, 51400], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1893307367960612, "compression_ratio": 1.5367965367965368, "no_speech_prob": 2.4260381030483114e-12}, {"id": 477, "seek": 195472, "start": 1975.78, "end": 1978.92, "text": " To a technologist, they are doing everything wrong.", "tokens": [51418, 1407, 257, 1537, 9201, 11, 436, 366, 884, 1203, 2085, 13, 51575], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1893307367960612, "compression_ratio": 1.5367965367965368, "no_speech_prob": 2.4260381030483114e-12}, {"id": 478, "seek": 197892, "start": 1978.92, "end": 1981.68, "text": " They have almost no formal storage capacity.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 362, 1920, 572, 9860, 6725, 6042, 13, 50503], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17503796683417427, "compression_ratio": 1.5302325581395348, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011404221042858e-12}, {"id": 479, "seek": 197892, "start": 1982.4, "end": 1988.68, "text": " And yet, their semantic continuity, their ability to maintain and transmit complex meaning,", "tokens": [50539, 400, 1939, 11, 641, 47982, 23807, 11, 641, 3485, 281, 6909, 293, 17831, 3997, 3620, 11, 50853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17503796683417427, "compression_ratio": 1.5302325581395348, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011404221042858e-12}, {"id": 480, "seek": 197892, "start": 1989.22, "end": 1995.7, "text": " nuanced skills, and historical identity over vast stretches of time, is incredibly robust.", "tokens": [50880, 45115, 3942, 11, 293, 8584, 6575, 670, 8369, 29058, 295, 565, 11, 307, 6252, 13956, 13, 51204], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17503796683417427, "compression_ratio": 1.5302325581395348, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011404221042858e-12}, {"id": 481, "seek": 197892, "start": 1995.8600000000001, "end": 1996.6000000000001, "text": " Why is that?", "tokens": [51212, 1545, 307, 300, 30, 51249], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17503796683417427, "compression_ratio": 1.5302325581395348, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011404221042858e-12}, {"id": 482, "seek": 197892, "start": 1996.8600000000001, "end": 2001.52, "text": " Because the structure of their reachability graph is what the paper calls locally dense.", "tokens": [51262, 1436, 264, 3877, 295, 641, 2524, 2310, 4295, 307, 437, 264, 3035, 5498, 16143, 18011, 13, 51495], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17503796683417427, "compression_ratio": 1.5302325581395348, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011404221042858e-12}, {"id": 483, "seek": 200152, "start": 2001.52, "end": 2008.02, "text": " Every present state is connected to past states through multiple overlapping redundant paths.", "tokens": [50365, 2048, 1974, 1785, 307, 4582, 281, 1791, 4368, 807, 3866, 33535, 40997, 14518, 13, 50690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 484, "seek": 200152, "start": 2008.36, "end": 2011.18, "text": " What does a redundant path look like in a physical village?", "tokens": [50707, 708, 775, 257, 40997, 3100, 574, 411, 294, 257, 4001, 7288, 30, 50848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 485, "seek": 200152, "start": 2011.32, "end": 2012.3, "text": " It's not a backup server.", "tokens": [50855, 467, 311, 406, 257, 14807, 7154, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 486, "seek": 200152, "start": 2012.74, "end": 2013.02, "text": " No.", "tokens": [50926, 883, 13, 50940], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 487, "seek": 200152, "start": 2013.3799999999999, "end": 2017.5, "text": " A redundant path looks like overlapping memories among community members.", "tokens": [50958, 316, 40997, 3100, 1542, 411, 33535, 8495, 3654, 1768, 2679, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 488, "seek": 200152, "start": 2018.16, "end": 2022.58, "text": " It looks like repeated narratives, gossip, and storytelling around a dinner table.", "tokens": [51197, 467, 1542, 411, 10477, 28016, 11, 31788, 11, 293, 21479, 926, 257, 6148, 3199, 13, 51418], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 489, "seek": 200152, "start": 2023.28, "end": 2026.86, "text": " It is ritual reenactment, shared material culture,", "tokens": [51453, 467, 307, 13792, 319, 268, 578, 518, 11, 5507, 2527, 3713, 11, 51632], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1664864400799355, "compression_ratio": 1.649789029535865, "no_speech_prob": 2.1009272880428975e-12}, {"id": 490, "seek": 202686, "start": 2026.86, "end": 2034.6799999999998, "text": " the layout of the architecture, and the direct living presence of elders who participated in prior events.", "tokens": [50365, 264, 13333, 295, 264, 9482, 11, 293, 264, 2047, 2647, 6814, 295, 22737, 567, 17978, 294, 4059, 3931, 13, 50756], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12748829730145342, "compression_ratio": 1.599056603773585, "no_speech_prob": 2.1588219493301475e-12}, {"id": 491, "seek": 202686, "start": 2034.6799999999998, "end": 2039.56, "text": " It's the difference between saving a document in one folder on your computer", "tokens": [50756, 467, 311, 264, 2649, 1296, 6816, 257, 4166, 294, 472, 10820, 322, 428, 3820, 51000], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12748829730145342, "compression_ratio": 1.599056603773585, "no_speech_prob": 2.1588219493301475e-12}, {"id": 492, "seek": 202686, "start": 2039.56, "end": 2042.74, "text": " versus teaching a song to 50 different people.", "tokens": [51000, 5717, 4571, 257, 2153, 281, 2625, 819, 561, 13, 51159], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12748829730145342, "compression_ratio": 1.599056603773585, "no_speech_prob": 2.1588219493301475e-12}, {"id": 493, "seek": 202686, "start": 2043.56, "end": 2047.9599999999998, "text": " If you save the document and the hard drive crashes, the path is instantly destroyed.", "tokens": [51200, 759, 291, 3155, 264, 4166, 293, 264, 1152, 3332, 28642, 11, 264, 3100, 307, 13518, 8937, 13, 51420], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12748829730145342, "compression_ratio": 1.599056603773585, "no_speech_prob": 2.1588219493301475e-12}, {"id": 494, "seek": 202686, "start": 2048.44, "end": 2049.64, "text": " The link rot is total.", "tokens": [51444, 440, 2113, 4297, 307, 3217, 13, 51504], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12748829730145342, "compression_ratio": 1.599056603773585, "no_speech_prob": 2.1588219493301475e-12}, {"id": 495, "seek": 204964, "start": 2049.64, "end": 2055.7999999999997, "text": " But in the village, if one path degrades, say, an elder tragically passes away,", "tokens": [50365, 583, 294, 264, 7288, 11, 498, 472, 3100, 368, 22626, 11, 584, 11, 364, 12995, 38282, 984, 11335, 1314, 11, 50673], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 496, "seek": 204964, "start": 2056.48, "end": 2061.08, "text": " the knowledge isn't lost because 10 other redundant paths still connect to that meaning", "tokens": [50707, 264, 3601, 1943, 380, 2731, 570, 1266, 661, 40997, 14518, 920, 1745, 281, 300, 3620, 50937], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 497, "seek": 204964, "start": 2061.08, "end": 2065.0, "text": " through other community members, shared practices, and daily habits.", "tokens": [50937, 807, 661, 1768, 2679, 11, 5507, 7525, 11, 293, 5212, 14100, 13, 51133], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 498, "seek": 204964, "start": 2065.44, "end": 2068.72, "text": " The system doesn't need a formal, isolated archive", "tokens": [51155, 440, 1185, 1177, 380, 643, 257, 9860, 11, 14621, 23507, 51319], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 499, "seek": 204964, "start": 2068.72, "end": 2072.3799999999997, "text": " because it is continuously traversing its own history.", "tokens": [51319, 570, 309, 307, 15684, 23149, 278, 1080, 1065, 2503, 13, 51502], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 500, "seek": 204964, "start": 2073.2599999999998, "end": 2074.74, "text": " Storage isn't the invariant.", "tokens": [51546, 36308, 1943, 380, 264, 33270, 394, 13, 51620], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 501, "seek": 204964, "start": 2074.94, "end": 2076.58, "text": " Continuous traversal is.", "tokens": [51630, 14674, 12549, 23149, 304, 307, 13, 51712], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 502, "seek": 204964, "start": 2076.8599999999997, "end": 2077.96, "text": " Continuous traversal.", "tokens": [51726, 14674, 12549, 23149, 304, 13, 51781], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 503, "seek": 204964, "start": 2077.96, "end": 2078.3599999999997, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51781, 1079, 13, 51801], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19678982173171, "compression_ratio": 1.6459143968871595, "no_speech_prob": 1.7013945590935164e-12}, {"id": 504, "seek": 207836, "start": 2078.36, "end": 2085.08, "text": " That is such a profound shift in perspective for anyone involved in knowledge management.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 1270, 257, 14382, 5513, 294, 4585, 337, 2878, 3288, 294, 3601, 4592, 13, 50701], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14376574502864353, "compression_ratio": 1.5324074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.227367379079026e-12}, {"id": 505, "seek": 207836, "start": 2085.6200000000003, "end": 2089.82, "text": " A system with minimal storage but maximum path density", "tokens": [50728, 316, 1185, 365, 13206, 6725, 457, 6674, 3100, 10305, 50938], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14376574502864353, "compression_ratio": 1.5324074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.227367379079026e-12}, {"id": 506, "seek": 207836, "start": 2089.82, "end": 2096.1400000000003, "text": " can sustain knowledge far better than a system with comprehensive petabyte digital archives", "tokens": [50938, 393, 6769, 3601, 1400, 1101, 813, 257, 1185, 365, 13914, 3817, 34529, 4562, 25607, 51254], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14376574502864353, "compression_ratio": 1.5324074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.227367379079026e-12}, {"id": 507, "seek": 207836, "start": 2096.1400000000003, "end": 2098.76, "text": " but fragile, degrading navigation.", "tokens": [51254, 457, 23847, 11, 24740, 278, 17346, 13, 51385], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14376574502864353, "compression_ratio": 1.5324074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.227367379079026e-12}, {"id": 508, "seek": 207836, "start": 2099.32, "end": 2102.2200000000003, "text": " It's not about how securely you lock the book in the vault.", "tokens": [51413, 467, 311, 406, 466, 577, 38348, 291, 4017, 264, 1446, 294, 264, 27134, 13, 51558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14376574502864353, "compression_ratio": 1.5324074074074074, "no_speech_prob": 2.227367379079026e-12}, {"id": 509, "seek": 210222, "start": 2102.22, "end": 2108.64, "text": " It's about how many people are walking the path to read it, discuss it, and apply it every single day.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 466, 577, 867, 561, 366, 4494, 264, 3100, 281, 1401, 309, 11, 2248, 309, 11, 293, 3079, 309, 633, 2167, 786, 13, 50686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07240580660956246, "compression_ratio": 1.1333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 2.0968387616504547e-12}, {"id": 510, "seek": 210864, "start": 2108.64, "end": 2114.56, "text": " And when information systems scale up to a global level, when we move from the village to the internet,", "tokens": [50365, 400, 562, 1589, 3652, 4373, 493, 281, 257, 4338, 1496, 11, 562, 321, 1286, 490, 264, 7288, 281, 264, 4705, 11, 50661], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 511, "seek": 210864, "start": 2115.06, "end": 2117.1, "text": " what they lose isn't storage capacity.", "tokens": [50686, 437, 436, 3624, 1943, 380, 6725, 6042, 13, 50788], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 512, "seek": 210864, "start": 2117.2599999999998, "end": 2118.74, "text": " They have virtually infinite storage.", "tokens": [50796, 814, 362, 14103, 13785, 6725, 13, 50870], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 513, "seek": 210864, "start": 2119.1, "end": 2122.3399999999997, "text": " What they lose is the local redundancy of paths.", "tokens": [50888, 708, 436, 3624, 307, 264, 2654, 27830, 6717, 295, 14518, 13, 51050], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 514, "seek": 210864, "start": 2122.48, "end": 2122.7599999999998, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51057, 1779, 13, 51071], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 515, "seek": 210864, "start": 2122.98, "end": 2124.7999999999997, "text": " They lose the human overlapping of memory.", "tokens": [51082, 814, 3624, 264, 1952, 33535, 295, 4675, 13, 51173], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 516, "seek": 210864, "start": 2124.98, "end": 2130.3399999999997, "text": " They rely on single, brittle hyperlinks instead of 50 overlapping conversations.", "tokens": [51182, 814, 10687, 322, 2167, 11, 49325, 9848, 75, 16431, 2602, 295, 2625, 33535, 7315, 13, 51450], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19768653518852147, "compression_ratio": 1.6143497757847534, "no_speech_prob": 2.1253654218511553e-12}, {"id": 517, "seek": 213034, "start": 2130.34, "end": 2134.1400000000003, "text": " Which brings us to the most mind-bending scale of the paper.", "tokens": [50365, 3013, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 881, 1575, 12, 65, 2029, 4373, 295, 264, 3035, 13, 50555], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.191528709567323, "compression_ratio": 1.352, "no_speech_prob": 2.1928429124601356e-12}, {"id": 518, "seek": 213034, "start": 2134.46, "end": 2140.1000000000004, "text": " We've been talking about timescales maybe a few years for link rot or a few decades for a village elder.", "tokens": [50571, 492, 600, 668, 1417, 466, 1413, 66, 4229, 1310, 257, 1326, 924, 337, 2113, 4297, 420, 257, 1326, 7878, 337, 257, 7288, 12995, 13, 50853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.191528709567323, "compression_ratio": 1.352, "no_speech_prob": 2.1928429124601356e-12}, {"id": 519, "seek": 213034, "start": 2140.3, "end": 2140.56, "text": " No.", "tokens": [50863, 883, 13, 50876], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.191528709567323, "compression_ratio": 1.352, "no_speech_prob": 2.1928429124601356e-12}, {"id": 520, "seek": 214056, "start": 2140.56, "end": 2143.7799999999997, "text": " But Flyxion expands the timeline dramatically.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 3235, 970, 952, 33706, 264, 12933, 17548, 13, 50526], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 521, "seek": 214056, "start": 2144.02, "end": 2145.16, "text": " Generational time.", "tokens": [50538, 15409, 1478, 565, 13, 50595], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 522, "seek": 214056, "start": 2145.56, "end": 2145.84, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50615, 1079, 13, 50629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 523, "seek": 214056, "start": 2146.6, "end": 2151.08, "text": " If digital systems rot in years, languages shift over generations.", "tokens": [50667, 759, 4562, 3652, 4297, 294, 924, 11, 8650, 5513, 670, 10593, 13, 50891], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 524, "seek": 214056, "start": 2151.64, "end": 2156.2799999999997, "text": " And the paper argues that natural human language is not just a medium of communication.", "tokens": [50919, 400, 264, 3035, 38218, 300, 3303, 1952, 2856, 307, 406, 445, 257, 6399, 295, 6101, 13, 51151], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 525, "seek": 214056, "start": 2156.7799999999997, "end": 2164.02, "text": " It is literally a massive, long timescale navigation system for an inherited semantic field.", "tokens": [51176, 467, 307, 3736, 257, 5994, 11, 938, 1413, 37088, 17346, 1185, 337, 364, 27091, 47982, 2519, 13, 51538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 526, "seek": 214056, "start": 2164.36, "end": 2168.52, "text": " This is a beautiful application of the graph theory we established at the beginning.", "tokens": [51555, 639, 307, 257, 2238, 3861, 295, 264, 4295, 5261, 321, 7545, 412, 264, 2863, 13, 51763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19955035618373326, "compression_ratio": 1.57421875, "no_speech_prob": 2.3342001075066232e-12}, {"id": 527, "seek": 216852, "start": 2168.52, "end": 2175.5, "text": " Think of a language not just as a dictionary of words, but as a vast, complex network of transformations.", "tokens": [50365, 6557, 295, 257, 2856, 406, 445, 382, 257, 25890, 295, 2283, 11, 457, 382, 257, 8369, 11, 3997, 3209, 295, 34852, 13, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12577530772415632, "compression_ratio": 1.6561264822134387, "no_speech_prob": 2.109316193932287e-12}, {"id": 528, "seek": 216852, "start": 2175.96, "end": 2176.22, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50737, 1033, 13, 50750], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12577530772415632, "compression_ratio": 1.6561264822134387, "no_speech_prob": 2.109316193932287e-12}, {"id": 529, "seek": 216852, "start": 2176.66, "end": 2181.78, "text": " A speaker of a language inherits access to a specific subgraph of human meaning.", "tokens": [50772, 316, 8145, 295, 257, 2856, 9484, 1208, 2105, 281, 257, 2685, 1422, 34091, 295, 1952, 3620, 13, 51028], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12577530772415632, "compression_ratio": 1.6561264822134387, "no_speech_prob": 2.109316193932287e-12}, {"id": 530, "seek": 216852, "start": 2182.06, "end": 2189.34, "text": " All the texts, the oral traditions, the idioms, the conceptual frameworks encoded in that language's specific history.", "tokens": [51042, 1057, 264, 15765, 11, 264, 19338, 15643, 11, 264, 18014, 4785, 11, 264, 24106, 29834, 2058, 12340, 294, 300, 2856, 311, 2685, 2503, 13, 51406], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12577530772415632, "compression_ratio": 1.6561264822134387, "no_speech_prob": 2.109316193932287e-12}, {"id": 531, "seek": 216852, "start": 2190.1, "end": 2196.5, "text": " Therefore, a language shift, whether it is a voluntary assimilation or a violently imposed colonial policy,", "tokens": [51444, 7504, 11, 257, 2856, 5513, 11, 1968, 309, 307, 257, 28563, 8249, 16067, 420, 257, 46728, 26491, 19066, 3897, 11, 51764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12577530772415632, "compression_ratio": 1.6561264822134387, "no_speech_prob": 2.109316193932287e-12}, {"id": 532, "seek": 219650, "start": 2196.5, "end": 2199.68, "text": " is not just a change in how people express their thoughts.", "tokens": [50365, 307, 406, 445, 257, 1319, 294, 577, 561, 5109, 641, 4598, 13, 50524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19964699591359786, "compression_ratio": 1.4450867052023122, "no_speech_prob": 2.5341605983802973e-12}, {"id": 533, "seek": 219650, "start": 2199.88, "end": 2200.64, "text": " What is it, then?", "tokens": [50534, 708, 307, 309, 11, 550, 30, 50572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19964699591359786, "compression_ratio": 1.4450867052023122, "no_speech_prob": 2.5341605983802973e-12}, {"id": 534, "seek": 219650, "start": 2200.7, "end": 2205.76, "text": " It is a catastrophic restructuring of the entire available reachability graph.", "tokens": [50575, 467, 307, 257, 34915, 1472, 1757, 1345, 295, 264, 2302, 2435, 2524, 2310, 4295, 13, 50828], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19964699591359786, "compression_ratio": 1.4450867052023122, "no_speech_prob": 2.5341605983802973e-12}, {"id": 535, "seek": 219650, "start": 2205.98, "end": 2206.34, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [50839, 3153, 13, 50857], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19964699591359786, "compression_ratio": 1.4450867052023122, "no_speech_prob": 2.5341605983802973e-12}, {"id": 536, "seek": 219650, "start": 2206.98, "end": 2212.18, "text": " The paper looks at language displacement as a primary example of this structural failure.", "tokens": [50889, 440, 3035, 1542, 412, 2856, 21899, 382, 257, 6194, 1365, 295, 341, 15067, 7763, 13, 51149], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19964699591359786, "compression_ratio": 1.4450867052023122, "no_speech_prob": 2.5341605983802973e-12}, {"id": 537, "seek": 221218, "start": 2212.18, "end": 2222.54, "text": " It mentions French displacing regional dialects like Breton or Occitan in France, English reorganizing the semantic landscape of its colonial territories,", "tokens": [50365, 467, 23844, 5522, 14996, 5615, 10964, 24652, 82, 411, 42000, 266, 420, 26191, 9670, 294, 6190, 11, 3669, 41203, 3319, 264, 47982, 9661, 295, 1080, 19066, 25195, 11, 50883], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16772605632913523, "compression_ratio": 1.3837209302325582, "no_speech_prob": 2.307041927288034e-12}, {"id": 538, "seek": 221218, "start": 2222.8199999999997, "end": 2228.2799999999997, "text": " or Spanish restructuring the prior Mesoamerican systems of the Aztec and Maya.", "tokens": [50897, 420, 8058, 1472, 1757, 1345, 264, 4059, 17485, 78, 13530, 8914, 3652, 295, 264, 7607, 975, 66, 293, 21695, 13, 51170], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16772605632913523, "compression_ratio": 1.3837209302325582, "no_speech_prob": 2.307041927288034e-12}, {"id": 539, "seek": 221218, "start": 2228.3999999999996, "end": 2229.14, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51176, 1079, 13, 51213], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16772605632913523, "compression_ratio": 1.3837209302325582, "no_speech_prob": 2.307041927288034e-12}, {"id": 540, "seek": 222914, "start": 2229.14, "end": 2238.7999999999997, "text": " When these massive linguistic displacements happen, the prior states, the indigenous oral traditions, the untranslated botanical knowledge,", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 613, 5994, 43002, 14996, 41140, 1051, 11, 264, 4059, 4368, 11, 264, 15511, 19338, 15643, 11, 264, 1701, 25392, 38539, 10592, 282, 804, 3601, 11, 50848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16636143869428494, "compression_ratio": 1.5507246376811594, "no_speech_prob": 2.1170779972851106e-12}, {"id": 541, "seek": 222914, "start": 2239.3199999999997, "end": 2242.92, "text": " the deep contextual worldview embedded in the grammar itself,", "tokens": [50874, 264, 2452, 35526, 41141, 16741, 294, 264, 22317, 2564, 11, 51054], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16636143869428494, "compression_ratio": 1.5507246376811594, "no_speech_prob": 2.1170779972851106e-12}, {"id": 542, "seek": 222914, "start": 2243.3199999999997, "end": 2246.7999999999997, "text": " they aren't magically destroyed the instant the new language takes over.", "tokens": [51074, 436, 3212, 380, 39763, 8937, 264, 9836, 264, 777, 2856, 2516, 670, 13, 51248], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16636143869428494, "compression_ratio": 1.5507246376811594, "no_speech_prob": 2.1170779972851106e-12}, {"id": 543, "seek": 222914, "start": 2247.52, "end": 2249.72, "text": " The physical artifacts and the elders survive.", "tokens": [51284, 440, 4001, 24617, 293, 264, 22737, 7867, 13, 51394], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16636143869428494, "compression_ratio": 1.5507246376811594, "no_speech_prob": 2.1170779972851106e-12}, {"id": 544, "seek": 224972, "start": 2249.72, "end": 2257.4199999999996, "text": " The nodes still exist, the grandmother still holds the memories, the physical ruins, and the untranslated codices remain.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 13891, 920, 2514, 11, 264, 14317, 920, 9190, 264, 8495, 11, 264, 4001, 24747, 11, 293, 264, 1701, 25392, 38539, 17656, 1473, 6222, 13, 50750], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16860150655110678, "compression_ratio": 1.591743119266055, "no_speech_prob": 2.7832135467836805e-12}, {"id": 545, "seek": 224972, "start": 2258.18, "end": 2263.5, "text": " But they become entirely unreachable by the paths available to the subsequent generations.", "tokens": [50788, 583, 436, 1813, 7696, 517, 16226, 712, 538, 264, 14518, 2435, 281, 264, 19962, 10593, 13, 51054], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16860150655110678, "compression_ratio": 1.591743119266055, "no_speech_prob": 2.7832135467836805e-12}, {"id": 546, "seek": 224972, "start": 2263.54, "end": 2264.8999999999996, "text": " Because they don't speak the language.", "tokens": [51056, 1436, 436, 500, 380, 1710, 264, 2856, 13, 51124], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16860150655110678, "compression_ratio": 1.591743119266055, "no_speech_prob": 2.7832135467836805e-12}, {"id": 547, "seek": 224972, "start": 2265.4399999999996, "end": 2265.9399999999996, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51151, 7587, 13, 51176], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16860150655110678, "compression_ratio": 1.591743119266055, "no_speech_prob": 2.7832135467836805e-12}, {"id": 548, "seek": 224972, "start": 2266.22, "end": 2270.58, "text": " The children and grandchildren inherit the new linguistic navigational infrastructure.", "tokens": [51190, 440, 2227, 293, 28112, 21389, 264, 777, 43002, 7407, 1478, 6896, 13, 51408], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16860150655110678, "compression_ratio": 1.591743119266055, "no_speech_prob": 2.7832135467836805e-12}, {"id": 549, "seek": 227058, "start": 2270.58, "end": 2278.02, "text": " Because they lack the transformations, the specific vocabulary, the syntax, the cultural context of the old language,", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 436, 5011, 264, 34852, 11, 264, 2685, 19864, 11, 264, 28431, 11, 264, 6988, 4319, 295, 264, 1331, 2856, 11, 50737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13491856070125804, "compression_ratio": 1.5823293172690762, "no_speech_prob": 2.5042515804096777e-12}, {"id": 550, "seek": 227058, "start": 2278.46, "end": 2281.2999999999997, "text": " the historical meaning is severed from them.", "tokens": [50759, 264, 8584, 3620, 307, 2802, 292, 490, 552, 13, 50901], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13491856070125804, "compression_ratio": 1.5823293172690762, "no_speech_prob": 2.5042515804096777e-12}, {"id": 551, "seek": 227058, "start": 2281.2999999999997, "end": 2288.14, "text": " It is exactly the same structural failure as the rotting URL or the paywalled academic paper", "tokens": [50901, 467, 307, 2293, 264, 912, 15067, 7763, 382, 264, 4297, 783, 12905, 420, 264, 1689, 86, 8907, 7778, 3035, 51243], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13491856070125804, "compression_ratio": 1.5823293172690762, "no_speech_prob": 2.5042515804096777e-12}, {"id": 552, "seek": 227058, "start": 2288.14, "end": 2293.9, "text": " just playing out devastatingly across human generations instead of server cycles.", "tokens": [51243, 445, 2433, 484, 21280, 356, 2108, 1952, 10593, 2602, 295, 7154, 17796, 13, 51531], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13491856070125804, "compression_ratio": 1.5823293172690762, "no_speech_prob": 2.5042515804096777e-12}, {"id": 553, "seek": 227058, "start": 2294.12, "end": 2297.8199999999997, "text": " The map has changed, so the territory becomes invisible.", "tokens": [51542, 440, 4471, 575, 3105, 11, 370, 264, 11360, 3643, 14603, 13, 51727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13491856070125804, "compression_ratio": 1.5823293172690762, "no_speech_prob": 2.5042515804096777e-12}, {"id": 554, "seek": 229782, "start": 2297.82, "end": 2306.4, "text": " But there are counterexamples where language acts as the ultimate unbroken path across unimaginable gulfs of time.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 456, 366, 1207, 323, 87, 335, 2622, 689, 2856, 10672, 382, 264, 9705, 517, 37947, 3100, 2108, 517, 44976, 712, 290, 5757, 82, 295, 565, 13, 50794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 555, "seek": 229782, "start": 2306.6600000000003, "end": 2308.6400000000003, "text": " I want to highlight what the paper says about Arabic.", "tokens": [50807, 286, 528, 281, 5078, 437, 264, 3035, 1619, 466, 19938, 13, 50906], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 556, "seek": 229782, "start": 2308.98, "end": 2311.2000000000003, "text": " Oh, the Arabic counterexample is stunning.", "tokens": [50923, 876, 11, 264, 19938, 1207, 323, 87, 335, 781, 307, 18550, 13, 51034], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 557, "seek": 229782, "start": 2311.5, "end": 2313.1200000000003, "text": " The analysis here is just incredible.", "tokens": [51049, 440, 5215, 510, 307, 445, 4651, 13, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 558, "seek": 229782, "start": 2313.6600000000003, "end": 2316.96, "text": " Arabic has maintained reachability over 14 centuries.", "tokens": [51157, 19938, 575, 17578, 2524, 2310, 670, 3499, 13926, 13, 51322], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 559, "seek": 229782, "start": 2317.7400000000002, "end": 2319.0800000000004, "text": " Think about that timescale.", "tokens": [51361, 6557, 466, 300, 1413, 37088, 13, 51428], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 560, "seek": 229782, "start": 2319.96, "end": 2323.56, "text": " Despite massive geographical dispersal across continents,", "tokens": [51472, 11334, 5994, 39872, 24631, 304, 2108, 38598, 11, 51652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1552471121152242, "compression_ratio": 1.58130081300813, "no_speech_prob": 2.38065686955502e-12}, {"id": 561, "seek": 232356, "start": 2323.56, "end": 2328.6, "text": " despite immense political transformations, the rise and fall of empires,", "tokens": [50365, 7228, 22920, 3905, 34852, 11, 264, 6272, 293, 2100, 295, 4012, 3145, 11, 50617], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14956432435570693, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.456220990487701e-12}, {"id": 562, "seek": 232356, "start": 2328.7799999999997, "end": 2331.38, "text": " and the shift from parchment to the digital age,", "tokens": [50626, 293, 264, 5513, 490, 37208, 281, 264, 4562, 3205, 11, 50756], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14956432435570693, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.456220990487701e-12}, {"id": 563, "seek": 232356, "start": 2332.16, "end": 2338.66, "text": " classical Arabic has remained a functional navigational system connecting the present to the 7th century.", "tokens": [50795, 13735, 19938, 575, 12780, 257, 11745, 7407, 1478, 1185, 11015, 264, 1974, 281, 264, 1614, 392, 4901, 13, 51120], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14956432435570693, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.456220990487701e-12}, {"id": 564, "seek": 232356, "start": 2338.98, "end": 2341.22, "text": " And we have to ask how it achieved that.", "tokens": [51136, 400, 321, 362, 281, 1029, 577, 309, 11042, 300, 13, 51248], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14956432435570693, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.456220990487701e-12}, {"id": 565, "seek": 232356, "start": 2341.68, "end": 2346.2, "text": " It certainly wasn't through passive preservation locking texts away in a dark room.", "tokens": [51271, 467, 3297, 2067, 380, 807, 14975, 27257, 23954, 15765, 1314, 294, 257, 2877, 1808, 13, 51497], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14956432435570693, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.456220990487701e-12}, {"id": 566, "seek": 232356, "start": 2346.34, "end": 2346.48, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51504, 1779, 13, 51511], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14956432435570693, "compression_ratio": 1.5608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 2.456220990487701e-12}, {"id": 567, "seek": 234648, "start": 2346.48, "end": 2352.52, "text": " The paper emphasizes that Arabic survived via intense, active path maintenance.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3035, 48856, 300, 19938, 14433, 5766, 9447, 11, 4967, 3100, 11258, 13, 50667], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21161387516902044, "compression_ratio": 1.5265486725663717, "no_speech_prob": 2.175774534499131e-12}, {"id": 568, "seek": 234648, "start": 2353.58, "end": 2359.28, "text": " It maintained its reachability through continuous, relentless traversal by millions of agents.", "tokens": [50720, 467, 17578, 1080, 2524, 2310, 807, 10957, 11, 46136, 23149, 304, 538, 6803, 295, 12554, 13, 51005], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21161387516902044, "compression_ratio": 1.5265486725663717, "no_speech_prob": 2.175774534499131e-12}, {"id": 569, "seek": 234648, "start": 2360.0, "end": 2366.12, "text": " This includes daily liturgical practice, the unbroken tradition of Quranic recitation,", "tokens": [51041, 639, 5974, 5212, 7997, 46736, 3124, 11, 264, 517, 37947, 6994, 295, 19375, 299, 850, 4614, 11, 51347], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21161387516902044, "compression_ratio": 1.5265486725663717, "no_speech_prob": 2.175774534499131e-12}, {"id": 570, "seek": 234648, "start": 2366.46, "end": 2369.72, "text": " where the text is literally memorized and spoken aloud.", "tokens": [51364, 689, 264, 2487, 307, 3736, 46677, 293, 10759, 43888, 13, 51527], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21161387516902044, "compression_ratio": 1.5265486725663717, "no_speech_prob": 2.175774534499131e-12}, {"id": 571, "seek": 234648, "start": 2369.82, "end": 2370.82, "text": " Spoken aloud.", "tokens": [51532, 1738, 8406, 43888, 13, 51582], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21161387516902044, "compression_ratio": 1.5265486725663717, "no_speech_prob": 2.175774534499131e-12}, {"id": 572, "seek": 234648, "start": 2371.0, "end": 2371.72, "text": " Continuously.", "tokens": [51591, 14674, 84, 5098, 13, 51627], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21161387516902044, "compression_ratio": 1.5265486725663717, "no_speech_prob": 2.175774534499131e-12}, {"id": 573, "seek": 237172, "start": 2371.72, "end": 2378.3599999999997, "text": " Yes, classical literary education and a relentless, continuous tradition of commentary, debate,", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 11, 13735, 24194, 3309, 293, 257, 46136, 11, 10957, 6994, 295, 23527, 11, 7958, 11, 50697], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14558397455418365, "compression_ratio": 1.6209677419354838, "no_speech_prob": 2.236425237708839e-12}, {"id": 574, "seek": 237172, "start": 2378.72, "end": 2381.7799999999997, "text": " and cross-referencing by scholars across generations.", "tokens": [50715, 293, 3278, 12, 265, 612, 13644, 538, 8553, 2108, 10593, 13, 50868], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14558397455418365, "compression_ratio": 1.6209677419354838, "no_speech_prob": 2.236425237708839e-12}, {"id": 575, "seek": 237172, "start": 2382.3399999999997, "end": 2386.66, "text": " It's the village model scaled up to a global religion and culture.", "tokens": [50896, 467, 311, 264, 7288, 2316, 36039, 493, 281, 257, 4338, 7561, 293, 3713, 13, 51112], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14558397455418365, "compression_ratio": 1.6209677419354838, "no_speech_prob": 2.236425237708839e-12}, {"id": 576, "seek": 237172, "start": 2387.2, "end": 2390.8399999999997, "text": " It's the difference between an abandoned, overgrown trail in the woods", "tokens": [51139, 467, 311, 264, 2649, 1296, 364, 13732, 11, 670, 38413, 9924, 294, 264, 15296, 51321], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14558397455418365, "compression_ratio": 1.6209677419354838, "no_speech_prob": 2.236425237708839e-12}, {"id": 577, "seek": 237172, "start": 2390.8399999999997, "end": 2394.3399999999997, "text": " and a path that is walked every single day by millions of people.", "tokens": [51321, 293, 257, 3100, 300, 307, 7628, 633, 2167, 786, 538, 6803, 295, 561, 13, 51496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14558397455418365, "compression_ratio": 1.6209677419354838, "no_speech_prob": 2.236425237708839e-12}, {"id": 578, "seek": 237172, "start": 2394.74, "end": 2396.9199999999996, "text": " The classical texts weren't just put in a vault.", "tokens": [51516, 440, 13735, 15765, 4999, 380, 445, 829, 294, 257, 27134, 13, 51625], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14558397455418365, "compression_ratio": 1.6209677419354838, "no_speech_prob": 2.236425237708839e-12}, {"id": 579, "seek": 239692, "start": 2396.92, "end": 2401.8, "text": " They were continuously reached, repeatedly, by a massive population of agents", "tokens": [50365, 814, 645, 15684, 6488, 11, 18227, 11, 538, 257, 5994, 4415, 295, 12554, 50609], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 580, "seek": 239692, "start": 2401.8, "end": 2405.4, "text": " who actively maintained the transformations that made them accessible.", "tokens": [50609, 567, 13022, 17578, 264, 34852, 300, 1027, 552, 9515, 13, 50789], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 581, "seek": 239692, "start": 2406.04, "end": 2409.2000000000003, "text": " The edges were never allowed to rot because they were used daily.", "tokens": [50821, 440, 8819, 645, 1128, 4350, 281, 4297, 570, 436, 645, 1143, 5212, 13, 50979], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 582, "seek": 239692, "start": 2409.7200000000003, "end": 2411.26, "text": " That is active path maintenance.", "tokens": [51005, 663, 307, 4967, 3100, 11258, 13, 51082], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 583, "seek": 239692, "start": 2411.8, "end": 2416.14, "text": " And this structural understanding of language as a reachability graph", "tokens": [51109, 400, 341, 15067, 3701, 295, 2856, 382, 257, 2524, 2310, 4295, 51326], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 584, "seek": 239692, "start": 2416.14, "end": 2421.56, "text": " allows us to look at modern institutional policies in a completely new light.", "tokens": [51326, 4045, 505, 281, 574, 412, 4363, 18391, 7657, 294, 257, 2584, 777, 1442, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 585, "seek": 239692, "start": 2422.46, "end": 2426.6, "text": " Flyxion brings up a specific, fascinating, modern example.", "tokens": [51642, 479, 697, 32167, 5607, 493, 257, 2685, 11, 10343, 11, 4363, 1365, 13, 51849], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17344323794047037, "compression_ratio": 1.6214285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 2.0283590345532287e-12}, {"id": 586, "seek": 242660, "start": 2427.38, "end": 2433.98, "text": " Quebec's 1977 chart de la langue fran\u00e7aise, or the charter of the French language.", "tokens": [50404, 38903, 311, 35092, 6927, 368, 635, 40318, 43832, 11, 420, 264, 27472, 295, 264, 5522, 2856, 13, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21547913551330566, "compression_ratio": 1.5303643724696356, "no_speech_prob": 3.092799020359971e-12}, {"id": 587, "seek": 242660, "start": 2434.2, "end": 2438.48, "text": " Now, normally when people talk about language laws like the one in Quebec,", "tokens": [50745, 823, 11, 5646, 562, 561, 751, 466, 2856, 6064, 411, 264, 472, 294, 38903, 11, 50959], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21547913551330566, "compression_ratio": 1.5303643724696356, "no_speech_prob": 3.092799020359971e-12}, {"id": 588, "seek": 242660, "start": 2438.86, "end": 2442.36, "text": " the conversation immediately becomes highly politicized.", "tokens": [50978, 264, 3761, 4258, 3643, 5405, 48044, 1602, 13, 51153], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21547913551330566, "compression_ratio": 1.5303643724696356, "no_speech_prob": 3.092799020359971e-12}, {"id": 589, "seek": 242660, "start": 2442.48, "end": 2442.88, "text": " Oh, yeah.", "tokens": [51159, 876, 11, 1338, 13, 51179], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21547913551330566, "compression_ratio": 1.5303643724696356, "no_speech_prob": 3.092799020359971e-12}, {"id": 590, "seek": 242660, "start": 2443.04, "end": 2447.92, "text": " It's framed as identity politics or cultural protectionism or nationalism.", "tokens": [51187, 467, 311, 30420, 382, 6575, 7341, 420, 6988, 6334, 1434, 420, 39186, 13, 51431], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21547913551330566, "compression_ratio": 1.5303643724696356, "no_speech_prob": 3.092799020359971e-12}, {"id": 591, "seek": 242660, "start": 2448.38, "end": 2453.02, "text": " But Flyxion strips all the politics away and looks at it purely structurally.", "tokens": [51454, 583, 479, 697, 32167, 19842, 439, 264, 7341, 1314, 293, 1542, 412, 309, 17491, 6594, 6512, 13, 51686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21547913551330566, "compression_ratio": 1.5303643724696356, "no_speech_prob": 3.092799020359971e-12}, {"id": 592, "seek": 245302, "start": 2453.02, "end": 2458.24, "text": " And just to be clear to everyone listening, we aren't taking a political side on this policy.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 445, 281, 312, 1850, 281, 1518, 4764, 11, 321, 3212, 380, 1940, 257, 3905, 1252, 322, 341, 3897, 13, 50626], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1420392014763572, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.4042467235835252e-12}, {"id": 593, "seek": 245302, "start": 2458.94, "end": 2465.94, "text": " We are impartially reporting the paper's incredibly unique structural analysis of it as an information system.", "tokens": [50661, 492, 366, 32177, 2270, 10031, 264, 3035, 311, 6252, 3845, 15067, 5215, 295, 309, 382, 364, 1589, 1185, 13, 51011], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1420392014763572, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.4042467235835252e-12}, {"id": 594, "seek": 245302, "start": 2466.32, "end": 2466.48, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51030, 1779, 13, 51038], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1420392014763572, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.4042467235835252e-12}, {"id": 595, "seek": 245302, "start": 2466.8, "end": 2472.48, "text": " Purely from an information theory perspective, the paper argues that the Quebec policy is best understood", "tokens": [51054, 29474, 356, 490, 364, 1589, 5261, 4585, 11, 264, 3035, 38218, 300, 264, 38903, 3897, 307, 1151, 7320, 51338], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1420392014763572, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.4042467235835252e-12}, {"id": 596, "seek": 245302, "start": 2472.48, "end": 2476.0, "text": " as a literal boundary condition on a reachability graph.", "tokens": [51338, 382, 257, 20411, 12866, 4188, 322, 257, 2524, 2310, 4295, 13, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1420392014763572, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.4042467235835252e-12}, {"id": 597, "seek": 245302, "start": 2476.12, "end": 2477.18, "text": " A boundary condition.", "tokens": [51520, 316, 12866, 4188, 13, 51573], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1420392014763572, "compression_ratio": 1.6363636363636365, "no_speech_prob": 2.4042467235835252e-12}, {"id": 598, "seek": 247718, "start": 2477.18, "end": 2477.7, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50391], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18884546106511896, "compression_ratio": 1.4375, "no_speech_prob": 2.5636580532062414e-12}, {"id": 599, "seek": 247718, "start": 2478.46, "end": 2484.24, "text": " What the law does is legally enforce the maintenance of edges in the francophone semantic graph", "tokens": [50429, 708, 264, 2101, 775, 307, 21106, 24825, 264, 11258, 295, 8819, 294, 264, 30514, 32561, 47982, 4295, 50718], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18884546106511896, "compression_ratio": 1.4375, "no_speech_prob": 2.5636580532062414e-12}, {"id": 600, "seek": 247718, "start": 2484.24, "end": 2491.6, "text": " against the overwhelming dominant pressure of the English language commercial infrastructure surrounding it in North America.", "tokens": [50718, 1970, 264, 13373, 15657, 3321, 295, 264, 3669, 2856, 6841, 6896, 11498, 309, 294, 4067, 3374, 13, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18884546106511896, "compression_ratio": 1.4375, "no_speech_prob": 2.5636580532062414e-12}, {"id": 601, "seek": 249160, "start": 2491.6, "end": 2494.66, "text": " But how does a law actually do that mechanically?", "tokens": [50365, 583, 577, 775, 257, 2101, 767, 360, 300, 4236, 984, 30, 50518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22895377022879465, "compression_ratio": 1.3125, "no_speech_prob": 2.702471276275209e-12}, {"id": 602, "seek": 249160, "start": 2495.66, "end": 2501.8199999999997, "text": " How does a legal constraint alter a reachability graph for a normal person?", "tokens": [50568, 1012, 775, 257, 5089, 25534, 11337, 257, 2524, 2310, 4295, 337, 257, 2710, 954, 30, 50876], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22895377022879465, "compression_ratio": 1.3125, "no_speech_prob": 2.702471276275209e-12}, {"id": 603, "seek": 249160, "start": 2502.8199999999997, "end": 2504.9, "text": " Think about a teenager living in Montreal.", "tokens": [50926, 6557, 466, 257, 21440, 2647, 294, 34180, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.22895377022879465, "compression_ratio": 1.3125, "no_speech_prob": 2.702471276275209e-12}, {"id": 604, "seek": 250490, "start": 2504.9, "end": 2513.84, "text": " When the law mandates that commercial signs must be predominantly in French or that large businesses must operate internally in French", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 264, 2101, 48662, 300, 6841, 7880, 1633, 312, 29893, 294, 5522, 420, 300, 2416, 6011, 1633, 9651, 19501, 294, 5522, 50812], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18600044610365382, "compression_ratio": 1.6144578313253013, "no_speech_prob": 3.1764766598302296e-12}, {"id": 605, "seek": 250490, "start": 2513.84, "end": 2517.48, "text": " or that children of immigrants must attend French schools,", "tokens": [50812, 420, 300, 2227, 295, 16598, 1633, 6888, 5522, 4656, 11, 50994], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18600044610365382, "compression_ratio": 1.6144578313253013, "no_speech_prob": 3.1764766598302296e-12}, {"id": 606, "seek": 250490, "start": 2517.7000000000003, "end": 2523.92, "text": " it is forcing the daily mechanical traversal of the French semantic graph.", "tokens": [51005, 309, 307, 19030, 264, 5212, 12070, 23149, 304, 295, 264, 5522, 47982, 4295, 13, 51316], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18600044610365382, "compression_ratio": 1.6144578313253013, "no_speech_prob": 3.1764766598302296e-12}, {"id": 607, "seek": 252392, "start": 2523.92, "end": 2534.94, "text": " It is ensuring that the transformations, the vocabulary needed to buy groceries, apply for a job, or read a street sign, remain actively used and redundant.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 16882, 300, 264, 34852, 11, 264, 19864, 2978, 281, 2256, 31391, 11, 3079, 337, 257, 1691, 11, 420, 1401, 257, 4838, 1465, 11, 6222, 13022, 1143, 293, 40997, 13, 50916], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13454863845661122, "compression_ratio": 1.5934065934065933, "no_speech_prob": 2.0764559776481617e-12}, {"id": 608, "seek": 252392, "start": 2535.42, "end": 2537.6800000000003, "text": " It acts as a structural constraint on the environment.", "tokens": [50940, 467, 10672, 382, 257, 15067, 25534, 322, 264, 2823, 13, 51053], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13454863845661122, "compression_ratio": 1.5934065934065933, "no_speech_prob": 2.0764559776481617e-12}, {"id": 609, "seek": 252392, "start": 2538.06, "end": 2541.66, "text": " It doesn't necessarily restore historical paths that are already lost,", "tokens": [51072, 467, 1177, 380, 4725, 15227, 8584, 14518, 300, 366, 1217, 2731, 11, 51252], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13454863845661122, "compression_ratio": 1.5934065934065933, "no_speech_prob": 2.0764559776481617e-12}, {"id": 610, "seek": 252392, "start": 2541.8, "end": 2548.28, "text": " but it prevents certain linguistic transitions from defaulting to English simply because it's commercially cheaper.", "tokens": [51259, 457, 309, 22367, 1629, 43002, 23767, 490, 7576, 278, 281, 3669, 2935, 570, 309, 311, 41751, 12284, 13, 51583], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13454863845661122, "compression_ratio": 1.5934065934065933, "no_speech_prob": 2.0764559776481617e-12}, {"id": 611, "seek": 252392, "start": 2548.52, "end": 2548.8, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51595, 1779, 13, 51609], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13454863845661122, "compression_ratio": 1.5934065934065933, "no_speech_prob": 2.0764559776481617e-12}, {"id": 612, "seek": 252392, "start": 2548.9, "end": 2550.14, "text": " The path of least resistance.", "tokens": [51614, 440, 3100, 295, 1935, 7335, 13, 51676], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13454863845661122, "compression_ratio": 1.5934065934065933, "no_speech_prob": 2.0764559776481617e-12}, {"id": 613, "seek": 255014, "start": 2550.14, "end": 2550.74, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 614, "seek": 255014, "start": 2551.02, "end": 2559.2, "text": " It maintains connectivity to prior francophone semantic states, the literature, the history, the cultural context of the region,", "tokens": [50409, 467, 33385, 21095, 281, 4059, 30514, 32561, 47982, 4368, 11, 264, 10394, 11, 264, 2503, 11, 264, 6988, 4319, 295, 264, 4458, 11, 50818], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 615, "seek": 255014, "start": 2559.48, "end": 2563.9, "text": " that would otherwise become completely unreachable within a single generation", "tokens": [50832, 300, 576, 5911, 1813, 2584, 517, 16226, 712, 1951, 257, 2167, 5125, 51053], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 616, "seek": 255014, "start": 2563.9, "end": 2568.04, "text": " if the commercial infrastructure simply overwrote the navigational paths.", "tokens": [51053, 498, 264, 6841, 6896, 2935, 670, 7449, 1370, 264, 7407, 1478, 14518, 13, 51260], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 617, "seek": 255014, "start": 2568.5, "end": 2571.2, "text": " It is forcing the daily maintenance of the bridge.", "tokens": [51283, 467, 307, 19030, 264, 5212, 11258, 295, 264, 7283, 13, 51418], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 618, "seek": 255014, "start": 2572.04, "end": 2574.3199999999997, "text": " The author insists this is not a metaphor.", "tokens": [51460, 440, 3793, 50137, 341, 307, 406, 257, 19157, 13, 51574], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 619, "seek": 255014, "start": 2575.0, "end": 2579.2999999999997, "text": " This is the exact same mathematical mechanism operating through a different medium.", "tokens": [51608, 639, 307, 264, 1900, 912, 18894, 7513, 7447, 807, 257, 819, 6399, 13, 51823], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1702789189864178, "compression_ratio": 1.6501766784452296, "no_speech_prob": 2.1011139876569995e-12}, {"id": 620, "seek": 257930, "start": 2579.3, "end": 2584.84, "text": " The reachability graph of a language is damaged by the exact same structural operations,", "tokens": [50365, 440, 2524, 2310, 4295, 295, 257, 2856, 307, 14080, 538, 264, 1900, 912, 15067, 7705, 11, 50642], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17149178574724896, "compression_ratio": 1.6186046511627907, "no_speech_prob": 1.4437462727071027e-12}, {"id": 621, "seek": 257930, "start": 2585.48, "end": 2589.2000000000003, "text": " edge deletion, path compression, audience redirection,", "tokens": [50674, 4691, 1103, 302, 313, 11, 3100, 19355, 11, 4034, 2182, 621, 882, 11, 50860], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17149178574724896, "compression_ratio": 1.6186046511627907, "no_speech_prob": 1.4437462727071027e-12}, {"id": 622, "seek": 257930, "start": 2589.4, "end": 2594.3, "text": " that damage the reachability graphs of Wikipedia or social media platforms.", "tokens": [50870, 300, 4344, 264, 2524, 2310, 24877, 295, 28999, 420, 2093, 3021, 9473, 13, 51115], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17149178574724896, "compression_ratio": 1.6186046511627907, "no_speech_prob": 1.4437462727071027e-12}, {"id": 623, "seek": 257930, "start": 2594.44, "end": 2595.5, "text": " It's all the same math.", "tokens": [51122, 467, 311, 439, 264, 912, 5221, 13, 51175], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17149178574724896, "compression_ratio": 1.6186046511627907, "no_speech_prob": 1.4437462727071027e-12}, {"id": 624, "seek": 257930, "start": 2595.9, "end": 2599.1600000000003, "text": " The timescales are different, centuries versus server cycles,", "tokens": [51195, 440, 1413, 66, 4229, 366, 819, 11, 13926, 5717, 7154, 17796, 11, 51358], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17149178574724896, "compression_ratio": 1.6186046511627907, "no_speech_prob": 1.4437462727071027e-12}, {"id": 625, "seek": 257930, "start": 2599.4, "end": 2602.1200000000003, "text": " but the underlying structure is identical.", "tokens": [51370, 457, 264, 14217, 3877, 307, 14800, 13, 51506], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17149178574724896, "compression_ratio": 1.6186046511627907, "no_speech_prob": 1.4437462727071027e-12}, {"id": 626, "seek": 260212, "start": 2602.12, "end": 2606.92, "text": " Whether it's a broken link to a cancer study or the loss of a grandmother's dialect,", "tokens": [50365, 8503, 309, 311, 257, 5463, 2113, 281, 257, 5592, 2979, 420, 264, 4470, 295, 257, 14317, 311, 24652, 11, 50605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15298074629248642, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 2.4847975239883358e-12}, {"id": 627, "seek": 260212, "start": 2607.64, "end": 2609.7799999999997, "text": " it is the failure to maintain the path.", "tokens": [50641, 309, 307, 264, 7763, 281, 6909, 264, 3100, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15298074629248642, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 2.4847975239883358e-12}, {"id": 628, "seek": 260212, "start": 2609.7799999999997, "end": 2614.7999999999997, "text": " It is genuinely awe-inspiring to realize the universality of this math.", "tokens": [50748, 467, 307, 17839, 30912, 12, 31637, 5057, 281, 4325, 264, 5950, 1860, 295, 341, 5221, 13, 50999], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15298074629248642, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 2.4847975239883358e-12}, {"id": 629, "seek": 260212, "start": 2615.18, "end": 2618.42, "text": " Which brings us to the ultimate, final question of the paper.", "tokens": [51018, 3013, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 9705, 11, 2572, 1168, 295, 264, 3035, 13, 51180], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15298074629248642, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 2.4847975239883358e-12}, {"id": 630, "seek": 260212, "start": 2618.64, "end": 2618.9, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51191, 1779, 13, 51204], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15298074629248642, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 2.4847975239883358e-12}, {"id": 631, "seek": 260212, "start": 2619.02, "end": 2621.48, "text": " How do we actually build systems that survive?", "tokens": [51210, 1012, 360, 321, 767, 1322, 3652, 300, 7867, 30, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15298074629248642, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 2.4847975239883358e-12}, {"id": 632, "seek": 262148, "start": 2621.48, "end": 2625.2400000000002, "text": " If everything is rotting, if encyclopedias compress history,", "tokens": [50365, 759, 1203, 307, 4297, 783, 11, 498, 465, 34080, 27277, 4609, 14778, 2503, 11, 50553], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092470012299002, "compression_ratio": 1.5076923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604845954452777e-12}, {"id": 633, "seek": 262148, "start": 2625.48, "end": 2627.52, "text": " if social media launders identities,", "tokens": [50565, 498, 2093, 3021, 17245, 433, 24239, 11, 50667], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092470012299002, "compression_ratio": 1.5076923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604845954452777e-12}, {"id": 634, "seek": 262148, "start": 2627.94, "end": 2630.84, "text": " and if passive preservation is a dangerous illusion,", "tokens": [50688, 293, 498, 14975, 27257, 307, 257, 5795, 18854, 11, 50833], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092470012299002, "compression_ratio": 1.5076923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604845954452777e-12}, {"id": 635, "seek": 262148, "start": 2631.48, "end": 2634.44, "text": " how do we fix this at an engineering level?", "tokens": [50865, 577, 360, 321, 3191, 341, 412, 364, 7043, 1496, 30, 51013], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092470012299002, "compression_ratio": 1.5076923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604845954452777e-12}, {"id": 636, "seek": 262148, "start": 2634.82, "end": 2637.02, "text": " This brings us to the final section of the paper,", "tokens": [51032, 639, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 2572, 3541, 295, 264, 3035, 11, 51142], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092470012299002, "compression_ratio": 1.5076923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604845954452777e-12}, {"id": 637, "seek": 262148, "start": 2637.62, "end": 2640.12, "text": " what Flyxion calls the constructive requirement.", "tokens": [51172, 437, 3235, 4105, 5498, 264, 30223, 11695, 13, 51297], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092470012299002, "compression_ratio": 1.5076923076923077, "no_speech_prob": 2.0604845954452777e-12}, {"id": 638, "seek": 264012, "start": 2640.12, "end": 2645.72, "text": " If the true goal of a memory system isn't just hoarding data,", "tokens": [50365, 759, 264, 2074, 3387, 295, 257, 4675, 1185, 1943, 380, 445, 45940, 278, 1412, 11, 50645], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 639, "seek": 264012, "start": 2646.2, "end": 2648.14, "text": " but ensuring semantic continuity,", "tokens": [50669, 457, 16882, 47982, 23807, 11, 50766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 640, "seek": 264012, "start": 2648.7999999999997, "end": 2651.88, "text": " which is the ability of future agents to reach past meaning", "tokens": [50799, 597, 307, 264, 3485, 295, 2027, 12554, 281, 2524, 1791, 3620, 50953], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 641, "seek": 264012, "start": 2651.88, "end": 2653.44, "text": " through available transformations,", "tokens": [50953, 807, 2435, 34852, 11, 51031], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 642, "seek": 264012, "start": 2654.12, "end": 2658.52, "text": " then we have to fundamentally change the question we ask our engineers and ourselves.", "tokens": [51065, 550, 321, 362, 281, 17879, 1319, 264, 1168, 321, 1029, 527, 11955, 293, 4175, 13, 51285], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 643, "seek": 264012, "start": 2658.7, "end": 2659.4, "text": " We do.", "tokens": [51294, 492, 360, 13, 51329], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 644, "seek": 264012, "start": 2659.7999999999997, "end": 2661.8599999999997, "text": " The design question can no longer be,", "tokens": [51349, 440, 1715, 1168, 393, 572, 2854, 312, 11, 51452], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 645, "seek": 264012, "start": 2662.2799999999997, "end": 2665.48, "text": " how do we safely store this information on a hard drive?", "tokens": [51473, 577, 360, 321, 11750, 3531, 341, 1589, 322, 257, 1152, 3332, 30, 51633], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 646, "seek": 264012, "start": 2665.8199999999997, "end": 2667.5, "text": " The question must shift to,", "tokens": [51650, 440, 1168, 1633, 5513, 281, 11, 51734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20525269556527187, "compression_ratio": 1.592156862745098, "no_speech_prob": 1.9430453340046894e-12}, {"id": 647, "seek": 266750, "start": 2667.5, "end": 2671.28, "text": " how do we ensure that future states can reach past states?", "tokens": [50365, 577, 360, 321, 5586, 300, 2027, 4368, 393, 2524, 1791, 4368, 30, 50554], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 648, "seek": 266750, "start": 2671.66, "end": 2672.66, "text": " And to achieve that,", "tokens": [50573, 400, 281, 4584, 300, 11, 50623], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 649, "seek": 266750, "start": 2672.8, "end": 2676.76, "text": " the paper outlines three non-negotiable pillars of continuity.", "tokens": [50630, 264, 3035, 40125, 1045, 2107, 12, 28561, 8206, 712, 26729, 295, 23807, 13, 50828], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 650, "seek": 266750, "start": 2677.56, "end": 2680.46, "text": " Three things a system must attend to simultaneously,", "tokens": [50868, 6244, 721, 257, 1185, 1633, 6888, 281, 16561, 11, 51013], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 651, "seek": 266750, "start": 2681.08, "end": 2683.18, "text": " or it will inevitably fail.", "tokens": [51044, 420, 309, 486, 28171, 3061, 13, 51149], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 652, "seek": 266750, "start": 2684.04, "end": 2685.34, "text": " Okay, what are the three pillars?", "tokens": [51192, 1033, 11, 437, 366, 264, 1045, 26729, 30, 51257], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 653, "seek": 266750, "start": 2685.52, "end": 2687.84, "text": " Pillar number one is what we are already very good at,", "tokens": [51266, 430, 30635, 1230, 472, 307, 437, 321, 366, 1217, 588, 665, 412, 11, 51382], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 654, "seek": 266750, "start": 2688.0, "end": 2688.86, "text": " node persistence.", "tokens": [51390, 9984, 37617, 13, 51433], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 655, "seek": 266750, "start": 2689.58, "end": 2692.54, "text": " The states, the files, the books, the data points,", "tokens": [51469, 440, 4368, 11, 264, 7098, 11, 264, 3642, 11, 264, 1412, 2793, 11, 51617], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 656, "seek": 266750, "start": 2692.66, "end": 2694.26, "text": " they must continue to exist.", "tokens": [51623, 436, 1633, 2354, 281, 2514, 13, 51703], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1841090809215199, "compression_ratio": 1.680327868852459, "no_speech_prob": 1.8112719440618874e-12}, {"id": 657, "seek": 269426, "start": 2694.26, "end": 2698.0, "text": " We still need the backups, the archives, the climate-controlled vaults,", "tokens": [50365, 492, 920, 643, 264, 50160, 11, 264, 25607, 11, 264, 5659, 12, 49344, 27134, 82, 11, 50552], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 658, "seek": 269426, "start": 2698.0, "end": 2699.5600000000004, "text": " but that is just the baseline.", "tokens": [50552, 457, 300, 307, 445, 264, 20518, 13, 50630], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 659, "seek": 269426, "start": 2699.94, "end": 2702.76, "text": " It is necessary, but completely insufficient.", "tokens": [50649, 467, 307, 4818, 11, 457, 2584, 41709, 13, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 660, "seek": 269426, "start": 2703.26, "end": 2703.6800000000003, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50815, 1779, 13, 50836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 661, "seek": 269426, "start": 2704.0, "end": 2706.0200000000004, "text": " So pillar number two is edge maintenance.", "tokens": [50852, 407, 27592, 1230, 732, 307, 4691, 11258, 13, 50953], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 662, "seek": 269426, "start": 2706.6400000000003, "end": 2711.5600000000004, "text": " The transformations that connect the states must remain available and traversable.", "tokens": [50984, 440, 34852, 300, 1745, 264, 4368, 1633, 6222, 2435, 293, 23149, 712, 13, 51230], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 663, "seek": 269426, "start": 2712.1000000000004, "end": 2714.86, "text": " The URLs must be updated and redirected.", "tokens": [51257, 440, 43267, 1633, 312, 10588, 293, 29066, 292, 13, 51395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 664, "seek": 269426, "start": 2715.0800000000004, "end": 2717.82, "text": " The language must be taught to the next generation.", "tokens": [51406, 440, 2856, 1633, 312, 5928, 281, 264, 958, 5125, 13, 51543], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 665, "seek": 269426, "start": 2718.32, "end": 2720.1600000000003, "text": " The passwords must be accessible.", "tokens": [51568, 440, 33149, 1633, 312, 9515, 13, 51660], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19668883506697837, "compression_ratio": 1.6612244897959183, "no_speech_prob": 1.9891191558457644e-12}, {"id": 666, "seek": 272016, "start": 2720.16, "end": 2724.3399999999997, "text": " The paths must be actively kept clear of overgrowth.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 14518, 1633, 312, 13022, 4305, 1850, 295, 670, 49747, 13, 50574], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 667, "seek": 272016, "start": 2724.46, "end": 2725.66, "text": " You can't just build the road.", "tokens": [50580, 509, 393, 380, 445, 1322, 264, 3060, 13, 50640], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 668, "seek": 272016, "start": 2725.7799999999997, "end": 2727.14, "text": " You have to pave it every year.", "tokens": [50646, 509, 362, 281, 28870, 309, 633, 1064, 13, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 669, "seek": 272016, "start": 2728.42, "end": 2730.56, "text": " And pillar number three is path coherence.", "tokens": [50778, 400, 27592, 1230, 1045, 307, 3100, 26528, 655, 13, 50885], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 670, "seek": 272016, "start": 2731.68, "end": 2735.2599999999998, "text": " This means that the composition of those available transformations", "tokens": [50941, 639, 1355, 300, 264, 12686, 295, 729, 2435, 34852, 51120], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 671, "seek": 272016, "start": 2735.2599999999998, "end": 2740.22, "text": " must remain capable of actually connecting the present state to the past one", "tokens": [51120, 1633, 6222, 8189, 295, 767, 11015, 264, 1974, 1785, 281, 264, 1791, 472, 51368], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 672, "seek": 272016, "start": 2740.22, "end": 2742.14, "text": " without losing the meaning.", "tokens": [51368, 1553, 7027, 264, 3620, 13, 51464], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 673, "seek": 272016, "start": 2742.52, "end": 2743.12, "text": " Coherence.", "tokens": [51483, 3066, 511, 655, 13, 51513], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1588449141558479, "compression_ratio": 1.5714285714285714, "no_speech_prob": 1.72793116620662e-12}, {"id": 674, "seek": 274312, "start": 2743.12, "end": 2743.42, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50380], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 675, "seek": 274312, "start": 2743.42, "end": 2749.5, "text": " The sequence of clicks or the sequence of translations has to make logical sense", "tokens": [50380, 440, 8310, 295, 18521, 420, 264, 8310, 295, 37578, 575, 281, 652, 14978, 2020, 50684], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 676, "seek": 274312, "start": 2749.5, "end": 2755.46, "text": " and arrive at the intended historical destination without being intercepted by a paywall", "tokens": [50684, 293, 8881, 412, 264, 10226, 8584, 12236, 1553, 885, 24700, 292, 538, 257, 1689, 16256, 50982], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 677, "seek": 274312, "start": 2755.46, "end": 2758.48, "text": " or laundered into a corporate billboard along the way.", "tokens": [50982, 420, 17245, 4073, 666, 257, 10896, 2961, 3787, 2051, 264, 636, 13, 51133], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 678, "seek": 274312, "start": 2758.94, "end": 2762.3599999999997, "text": " But here's the tragic asymmetry of our current technological era.", "tokens": [51156, 583, 510, 311, 264, 20385, 37277, 9889, 295, 527, 2190, 18439, 4249, 13, 51327], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 679, "seek": 274312, "start": 2763.48, "end": 2768.94, "text": " Node persistence, storing the massive amounts of data, is a technical property.", "tokens": [51383, 38640, 37617, 11, 26085, 264, 5994, 11663, 295, 1412, 11, 307, 257, 6191, 4707, 13, 51656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 680, "seek": 274312, "start": 2769.24, "end": 2771.16, "text": " It's incredibly easy to buy.", "tokens": [51671, 467, 311, 6252, 1858, 281, 2256, 13, 51767], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15021314012243392, "compression_ratio": 1.616, "no_speech_prob": 1.721454359268626e-12}, {"id": 681, "seek": 277116, "start": 2771.16, "end": 2772.68, "text": " You can measure it in terabytes.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 393, 3481, 309, 294, 1796, 24538, 13, 50441], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16025814378117942, "compression_ratio": 1.5512820512820513, "no_speech_prob": 1.973823231596339e-12}, {"id": 682, "seek": 277116, "start": 2772.8199999999997, "end": 2777.44, "text": " You can guarantee it contractually with Amazon Web Services or Google Cloud.", "tokens": [50448, 509, 393, 10815, 309, 4364, 671, 365, 6795, 9573, 12124, 420, 3329, 8061, 13, 50679], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16025814378117942, "compression_ratio": 1.5512820512820513, "no_speech_prob": 1.973823231596339e-12}, {"id": 683, "seek": 277116, "start": 2777.8399999999997, "end": 2780.68, "text": " You just pay a monthly fee and the nodes persist.", "tokens": [50699, 509, 445, 1689, 257, 12878, 12054, 293, 264, 13891, 13233, 13, 50841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16025814378117942, "compression_ratio": 1.5512820512820513, "no_speech_prob": 1.973823231596339e-12}, {"id": 684, "seek": 277116, "start": 2781.2799999999997, "end": 2786.8199999999997, "text": " But edge maintenance and path coherence, those are relational properties.", "tokens": [50871, 583, 4691, 11258, 293, 3100, 26528, 655, 11, 729, 366, 38444, 7221, 13, 51148], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16025814378117942, "compression_ratio": 1.5512820512820513, "no_speech_prob": 1.973823231596339e-12}, {"id": 685, "seek": 277116, "start": 2787.3799999999997, "end": 2794.5, "text": " Yes, they require ongoing active coordination among the human agents who constitute the system.", "tokens": [51176, 1079, 11, 436, 3651, 10452, 4967, 21252, 3654, 264, 1952, 12554, 567, 41658, 264, 1185, 13, 51532], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16025814378117942, "compression_ratio": 1.5512820512820513, "no_speech_prob": 1.973823231596339e-12}, {"id": 686, "seek": 277116, "start": 2794.92, "end": 2797.12, "text": " You can't archive a relationship.", "tokens": [51553, 509, 393, 380, 23507, 257, 2480, 13, 51663], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16025814378117942, "compression_ratio": 1.5512820512820513, "no_speech_prob": 1.973823231596339e-12}, {"id": 687, "seek": 279712, "start": 2797.12, "end": 2801.64, "text": " You can't put a conversation or a cultural context in cold storage.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 393, 380, 829, 257, 3761, 420, 257, 6988, 4319, 294, 3554, 6725, 13, 50591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 688, "seek": 279712, "start": 2802.0, "end": 2802.7999999999997, "text": " No, you can't.", "tokens": [50609, 883, 11, 291, 393, 380, 13, 50649], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 689, "seek": 279712, "start": 2803.2, "end": 2808.8399999999997, "text": " This raises an important question, perhaps the deepest philosophical point in the entire paper.", "tokens": [50669, 639, 19658, 364, 1021, 1168, 11, 4317, 264, 28288, 25066, 935, 294, 264, 2302, 3035, 13, 50951], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 690, "seek": 279712, "start": 2809.7799999999997, "end": 2812.3399999999997, "text": " How do we define meaning itself?", "tokens": [50998, 1012, 360, 321, 6964, 3620, 2564, 30, 51126], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 691, "seek": 279712, "start": 2813.18, "end": 2820.48, "text": " Because constraint-based accounts of meaning show us that meaning is a property of a system under transformation.", "tokens": [51168, 1436, 25534, 12, 6032, 9402, 295, 3620, 855, 505, 300, 3620, 307, 257, 4707, 295, 257, 1185, 833, 9887, 13, 51533], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 692, "seek": 279712, "start": 2820.8199999999997, "end": 2821.08, "text": " Whoa.", "tokens": [51550, 7521, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 693, "seek": 279712, "start": 2821.3399999999997, "end": 2821.7, "text": " Hold on.", "tokens": [51576, 6962, 322, 13, 51594], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 694, "seek": 279712, "start": 2821.8599999999997, "end": 2822.68, "text": " Let me interrupt you there.", "tokens": [51602, 961, 385, 12729, 291, 456, 13, 51643], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2055925700975501, "compression_ratio": 1.546218487394958, "no_speech_prob": 2.2017598248075254e-12}, {"id": 695, "seek": 282268, "start": 2822.68, "end": 2825.06, "text": " Constraint-based accounts of meaning.", "tokens": [50365, 8574, 424, 686, 12, 6032, 9402, 295, 3620, 13, 50484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1615282240368071, "compression_ratio": 1.5112107623318385, "no_speech_prob": 1.52513060774212e-12}, {"id": 696, "seek": 282268, "start": 2825.16, "end": 2829.74, "text": " That sounds like we just drop back into a dense philosophy textbook.", "tokens": [50489, 663, 3263, 411, 321, 445, 3270, 646, 666, 257, 18011, 10675, 25591, 13, 50718], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1615282240368071, "compression_ratio": 1.5112107623318385, "no_speech_prob": 1.52513060774212e-12}, {"id": 697, "seek": 282268, "start": 2829.8999999999996, "end": 2830.3399999999997, "text": " Fair enough.", "tokens": [50726, 12157, 1547, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1615282240368071, "compression_ratio": 1.5112107623318385, "no_speech_prob": 1.52513060774212e-12}, {"id": 698, "seek": 282268, "start": 2830.46, "end": 2832.12, "text": " Let's translate that for everyone listening.", "tokens": [50754, 961, 311, 13799, 300, 337, 1518, 4764, 13, 50837], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1615282240368071, "compression_ratio": 1.5112107623318385, "no_speech_prob": 1.52513060774212e-12}, {"id": 699, "seek": 282268, "start": 2832.3399999999997, "end": 2832.58, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50848, 865, 13, 50860], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1615282240368071, "compression_ratio": 1.5112107623318385, "no_speech_prob": 1.52513060774212e-12}, {"id": 700, "seek": 282268, "start": 2832.58, "end": 2841.68, "text": " Are you saying that a word or a document only means something based on the specific rules of how we are allowed to use it and connect it to other things in real time?", "tokens": [50860, 2014, 291, 1566, 300, 257, 1349, 420, 257, 4166, 787, 1355, 746, 2361, 322, 264, 2685, 4474, 295, 577, 321, 366, 4350, 281, 764, 309, 293, 1745, 309, 281, 661, 721, 294, 957, 565, 30, 51315], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1615282240368071, "compression_ratio": 1.5112107623318385, "no_speech_prob": 1.52513060774212e-12}, {"id": 701, "seek": 284168, "start": 2841.68, "end": 2843.74, "text": " That is precisely the translation.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 13402, 264, 12853, 13, 50468], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 702, "seek": 284168, "start": 2844.2999999999997, "end": 2851.3399999999997, "text": " We tend to think of meaning as a physical nugget of gold locked inside a vault, but it's not an object.", "tokens": [50496, 492, 3928, 281, 519, 295, 3620, 382, 257, 4001, 30279, 847, 295, 3821, 9376, 1854, 257, 27134, 11, 457, 309, 311, 406, 364, 2657, 13, 50848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 703, "seek": 284168, "start": 2851.56, "end": 2853.0, "text": " Meaning is a performance.", "tokens": [50859, 19948, 307, 257, 3389, 13, 50931], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 704, "seek": 284168, "start": 2853.08, "end": 2853.74, "text": " A performance.", "tokens": [50935, 316, 3389, 13, 50968], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 705, "seek": 284168, "start": 2854.14, "end": 2862.9199999999996, "text": " Semantic content is defined by what it rules out, by the specific constraints that make certain transitions valid and others invalid.", "tokens": [50988, 14421, 7128, 2701, 307, 7642, 538, 437, 309, 4474, 484, 11, 538, 264, 2685, 18491, 300, 652, 1629, 23767, 7363, 293, 2357, 34702, 13, 51427], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 706, "seek": 284168, "start": 2863.52, "end": 2865.3399999999997, "text": " Think of a game of chess.", "tokens": [51457, 6557, 295, 257, 1216, 295, 24122, 13, 51548], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 707, "seek": 284168, "start": 2865.58, "end": 2866.3199999999997, "text": " Okay, chess.", "tokens": [51560, 1033, 11, 24122, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18318328857421876, "compression_ratio": 1.5784753363228698, "no_speech_prob": 2.0923857264876222e-12}, {"id": 708, "seek": 286632, "start": 2866.32, "end": 2870.38, "text": " The meaning of the knight isn't in the carved piece of wood.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3620, 295, 264, 26054, 1943, 380, 294, 264, 28613, 2522, 295, 4576, 13, 50568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14107844233512878, "compression_ratio": 1.751111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682232852061052e-12}, {"id": 709, "seek": 286632, "start": 2871.0, "end": 2878.86, "text": " The meaning is entirely defined by the constraint of how it is allowed to move on the board, the L-shaped transformation.", "tokens": [50599, 440, 3620, 307, 7696, 7642, 538, 264, 25534, 295, 577, 309, 307, 4350, 281, 1286, 322, 264, 3150, 11, 264, 441, 12, 23103, 9887, 13, 50992], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14107844233512878, "compression_ratio": 1.751111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682232852061052e-12}, {"id": 710, "seek": 286632, "start": 2879.1800000000003, "end": 2879.46, "text": " Oh.", "tokens": [51008, 876, 13, 51022], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14107844233512878, "compression_ratio": 1.751111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682232852061052e-12}, {"id": 711, "seek": 286632, "start": 2879.8, "end": 2887.98, "text": " So if you change the rules of how it can move, or you take away the board entirely, the carved piece of wood still exists physically.", "tokens": [51039, 407, 498, 291, 1319, 264, 4474, 295, 577, 309, 393, 1286, 11, 420, 291, 747, 1314, 264, 3150, 7696, 11, 264, 28613, 2522, 295, 4576, 920, 8198, 9762, 13, 51448], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14107844233512878, "compression_ratio": 1.751111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682232852061052e-12}, {"id": 712, "seek": 286632, "start": 2888.6000000000004, "end": 2893.82, "text": " The node is preserved, but its operative meaning is completely destroyed.", "tokens": [51479, 440, 9984, 307, 22242, 11, 457, 1080, 2208, 1166, 3620, 307, 2584, 8937, 13, 51740], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14107844233512878, "compression_ratio": 1.751111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.6682232852061052e-12}, {"id": 713, "seek": 289382, "start": 2893.82, "end": 2894.44, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50396], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12686440851781275, "compression_ratio": 1.6559633027522935, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920823687176622e-12}, {"id": 714, "seek": 289382, "start": 2895.2000000000003, "end": 2902.3, "text": " To preserve meaning is to preserve the constraints, to preserve the active performance of navigating the graph.", "tokens": [50434, 1407, 15665, 3620, 307, 281, 15665, 264, 18491, 11, 281, 15665, 264, 4967, 3389, 295, 32054, 264, 4295, 13, 50789], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12686440851781275, "compression_ratio": 1.6559633027522935, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920823687176622e-12}, {"id": 715, "seek": 289382, "start": 2902.7400000000002, "end": 2910.7400000000002, "text": " When those paths, those rules of movement, are lost, the content is effectively lost no matter how many backup servers it lives on.", "tokens": [50811, 1133, 729, 14518, 11, 729, 4474, 295, 3963, 11, 366, 2731, 11, 264, 2701, 307, 8659, 2731, 572, 1871, 577, 867, 14807, 15909, 309, 2909, 322, 13, 51211], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12686440851781275, "compression_ratio": 1.6559633027522935, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920823687176622e-12}, {"id": 716, "seek": 289382, "start": 2911.2400000000002, "end": 2916.48, "text": " Modern information systems are systematically organized to maintain the completely wrong thing.", "tokens": [51236, 19814, 1589, 3652, 366, 39531, 9983, 281, 6909, 264, 2584, 2085, 551, 13, 51498], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12686440851781275, "compression_ratio": 1.6559633027522935, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920823687176622e-12}, {"id": 717, "seek": 289382, "start": 2916.6000000000004, "end": 2917.28, "text": " They really are.", "tokens": [51504, 814, 534, 366, 13, 51538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12686440851781275, "compression_ratio": 1.6559633027522935, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920823687176622e-12}, {"id": 718, "seek": 291728, "start": 2917.28, "end": 2925.1000000000004, "text": " They spend billions of dollars maintaining the carved piece of wood when they should be maintaining the rules of the game and the board it plays on.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 3496, 17375, 295, 3808, 14916, 264, 28613, 2522, 295, 4576, 562, 436, 820, 312, 14916, 264, 4474, 295, 264, 1216, 293, 264, 3150, 309, 5749, 322, 13, 50756], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11551318270094851, "compression_ratio": 1.779591836734694, "no_speech_prob": 2.6141502157406293e-12}, {"id": 719, "seek": 291728, "start": 2925.46, "end": 2929.2000000000003, "text": " They maintain the object when they should be maintaining the relation.", "tokens": [50774, 814, 6909, 264, 2657, 562, 436, 820, 312, 14916, 264, 9721, 13, 50961], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11551318270094851, "compression_ratio": 1.779591836734694, "no_speech_prob": 2.6141502157406293e-12}, {"id": 720, "seek": 291728, "start": 2929.4, "end": 2931.76, "text": " And I want to bring this back directly to you, the listener.", "tokens": [50971, 400, 286, 528, 281, 1565, 341, 646, 3838, 281, 291, 11, 264, 31569, 13, 51089], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11551318270094851, "compression_ratio": 1.779591836734694, "no_speech_prob": 2.6141502157406293e-12}, {"id": 721, "seek": 291728, "start": 2932.1400000000003, "end": 2939.94, "text": " Because this isn't just about massive digital archives or national language policies or the abstract math of information theory.", "tokens": [51108, 1436, 341, 1943, 380, 445, 466, 5994, 4562, 25607, 420, 4048, 2856, 7657, 420, 264, 12649, 5221, 295, 1589, 5261, 13, 51498], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11551318270094851, "compression_ratio": 1.779591836734694, "no_speech_prob": 2.6141502157406293e-12}, {"id": 722, "seek": 291728, "start": 2940.1600000000003, "end": 2941.5400000000004, "text": " This is not how you learn.", "tokens": [51509, 639, 307, 406, 577, 291, 1466, 13, 51578], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11551318270094851, "compression_ratio": 1.779591836734694, "no_speech_prob": 2.6141502157406293e-12}, {"id": 723, "seek": 294154, "start": 2941.54, "end": 2951.2599999999998, "text": " As someone who wants to understand the world deeply without drowning in information overload, this paper changes everything about personal knowledge management.", "tokens": [50365, 1018, 1580, 567, 2738, 281, 1223, 264, 1002, 8760, 1553, 37198, 294, 1589, 28777, 11, 341, 3035, 2962, 1203, 466, 2973, 3601, 4592, 13, 50851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15962970958036535, "compression_ratio": 1.3333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.5552061591664335e-12}, {"id": 724, "seek": 294154, "start": 2951.42, "end": 2952.38, "text": " It really does.", "tokens": [50859, 467, 534, 775, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15962970958036535, "compression_ratio": 1.3333333333333333, "no_speech_prob": 1.5552061591664335e-12}, {"id": 725, "seek": 295238, "start": 2952.38, "end": 2965.8, "text": " Relying on a massive, disorganized bookmark folder or a hard drive full of unread, meticulously saved PDFs or an intricate Notion database that you never actually look at is a trap.", "tokens": [50365, 497, 736, 278, 322, 257, 5994, 11, 717, 12372, 1602, 1446, 5638, 10820, 420, 257, 1152, 3332, 1577, 295, 517, 2538, 11, 41566, 25038, 6624, 17752, 82, 420, 364, 38015, 1726, 313, 8149, 300, 291, 1128, 767, 574, 412, 307, 257, 11487, 13, 51036], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16552210473395013, "compression_ratio": 1.4482758620689655, "no_speech_prob": 1.734316466481256e-12}, {"id": 726, "seek": 295238, "start": 2966.34, "end": 2968.04, "text": " It is the illusion of preservation.", "tokens": [51063, 467, 307, 264, 18854, 295, 27257, 13, 51148], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16552210473395013, "compression_ratio": 1.4482758620689655, "no_speech_prob": 1.734316466481256e-12}, {"id": 727, "seek": 295238, "start": 2969.0, "end": 2972.36, "text": " You think you are informed because you clicked save to pocket.", "tokens": [51196, 509, 519, 291, 366, 11740, 570, 291, 23370, 3155, 281, 8963, 13, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16552210473395013, "compression_ratio": 1.4482758620689655, "no_speech_prob": 1.734316466481256e-12}, {"id": 728, "seek": 295238, "start": 2972.54, "end": 2973.32, "text": " We all do it.", "tokens": [51373, 492, 439, 360, 309, 13, 51412], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16552210473395013, "compression_ratio": 1.4482758620689655, "no_speech_prob": 1.734316466481256e-12}, {"id": 729, "seek": 297332, "start": 2973.32, "end": 2976.26, "text": " But knowledge requires ongoing coordination.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 3601, 7029, 10452, 21252, 13, 50512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 730, "seek": 297332, "start": 2976.88, "end": 2978.42, "text": " It requires active traversal.", "tokens": [50543, 467, 7029, 4967, 23149, 304, 13, 50620], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 731, "seek": 297332, "start": 2978.54, "end": 2983.26, "text": " You have to synthesize it, write about it, connect it to other ideas, talk about it with friends.", "tokens": [50626, 509, 362, 281, 26617, 1125, 309, 11, 2464, 466, 309, 11, 1745, 309, 281, 661, 3487, 11, 751, 466, 309, 365, 1855, 13, 50862], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 732, "seek": 297332, "start": 2983.7000000000003, "end": 2985.1600000000003, "text": " You can't just archive knowledge.", "tokens": [50884, 509, 393, 380, 445, 23507, 3601, 13, 50957], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 733, "seek": 297332, "start": 2985.26, "end": 2986.2000000000003, "text": " You have to perform it.", "tokens": [50962, 509, 362, 281, 2042, 309, 13, 51009], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 734, "seek": 297332, "start": 2986.48, "end": 2989.6000000000004, "text": " You have to walk the paths or they disappear into the undergrowth.", "tokens": [51023, 509, 362, 281, 1792, 264, 14518, 420, 436, 11596, 666, 264, 833, 49747, 13, 51179], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 735, "seek": 297332, "start": 2990.1000000000004, "end": 2993.1200000000003, "text": " It is a vital, urgent lesson for the digital age.", "tokens": [51204, 467, 307, 257, 11707, 11, 19022, 6898, 337, 264, 4562, 3205, 13, 51355], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 736, "seek": 297332, "start": 2993.1200000000003, "end": 2999.1800000000003, "text": " We must shift our view from storing static objects to actively maintaining dynamic relations.", "tokens": [51355, 492, 1633, 5513, 527, 1910, 490, 26085, 13437, 6565, 281, 13022, 14916, 8546, 2299, 13, 51658], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 737, "seek": 297332, "start": 2999.44, "end": 3001.4, "text": " The relation is the reality.", "tokens": [51671, 440, 9721, 307, 264, 4103, 13, 51769], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1603364198104195, "compression_ratio": 1.7028985507246377, "no_speech_prob": 1.927623425462821e-12}, {"id": 738, "seek": 300140, "start": 3001.4, "end": 3011.52, "text": " So, to briefly recap the journey we've been on today, we started by shattering the false comfort of the perfectly preserved yet unsearchable library.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 11, 281, 10515, 20928, 264, 4671, 321, 600, 668, 322, 965, 11, 321, 1409, 538, 402, 14849, 264, 7908, 3400, 295, 264, 6239, 22242, 1939, 517, 405, 1178, 712, 6405, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11206726178731004, "compression_ratio": 1.5648148148148149, "no_speech_prob": 1.8977376094186926e-12}, {"id": 739, "seek": 300140, "start": 3012.06, "end": 3023.06, "text": " We learned that preservation and reachability are two entirely different mathematical properties and that our obsession with the former is blinding us to the collapse of the latter.", "tokens": [50898, 492, 3264, 300, 27257, 293, 2524, 2310, 366, 732, 7696, 819, 18894, 7221, 293, 300, 527, 30521, 365, 264, 5819, 307, 6865, 278, 505, 281, 264, 15584, 295, 264, 18481, 13, 51448], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11206726178731004, "compression_ratio": 1.5648148148148149, "no_speech_prob": 1.8977376094186926e-12}, {"id": 740, "seek": 300140, "start": 3023.32, "end": 3023.6800000000003, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51461, 1779, 13, 51479], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11206726178731004, "compression_ratio": 1.5648148148148149, "no_speech_prob": 1.8977376094186926e-12}, {"id": 741, "seek": 302368, "start": 3023.68, "end": 3043.3799999999997, "text": " We explored the invisible daily failures of our systems, how social platforms launder identities to hijack audiences, how encyclopedias compress history into oblivion to feign consensus, how paywalls gate our citations, and how link rot actively deletes our edges.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 24016, 264, 14603, 5212, 20774, 295, 527, 3652, 11, 577, 2093, 9473, 635, 6617, 24239, 281, 10625, 501, 15479, 11, 577, 465, 34080, 27277, 4609, 14778, 2503, 666, 47039, 313, 281, 579, 788, 19115, 11, 577, 1689, 16256, 82, 8539, 527, 4814, 763, 11, 293, 577, 2113, 4297, 13022, 1103, 37996, 527, 8819, 13, 51350], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09263673695650967, "compression_ratio": 1.4867724867724867, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827567764042151e-12}, {"id": 742, "seek": 302368, "start": 3043.54, "end": 3044.58, "text": " So much rotting.", "tokens": [51358, 407, 709, 4297, 783, 13, 51410], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09263673695650967, "compression_ratio": 1.4867724867724867, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827567764042151e-12}, {"id": 743, "seek": 304458, "start": 3044.58, "end": 3052.24, "text": " We saw how even the most vital archives can become isolated if they aren't indexed to the capabilities of normal agents.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 1866, 577, 754, 264, 881, 11707, 25607, 393, 1813, 14621, 498, 436, 3212, 380, 8186, 292, 281, 264, 10862, 295, 2710, 12554, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09981409219595103, "compression_ratio": 1.5377358490566038, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508307729648733e-12}, {"id": 744, "seek": 304458, "start": 3053.04, "end": 3065.7, "text": " And finally, we looked to the dense, redundant networks of local villages and the continuous, unbroken practice of ancient languages to understand that true survival requires active human path maintenance.", "tokens": [50788, 400, 2721, 11, 321, 2956, 281, 264, 18011, 11, 40997, 9590, 295, 2654, 20444, 293, 264, 10957, 11, 517, 37947, 3124, 295, 7832, 8650, 281, 1223, 300, 2074, 12559, 7029, 4967, 1952, 3100, 11258, 13, 51421], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09981409219595103, "compression_ratio": 1.5377358490566038, "no_speech_prob": 1.9508307729648733e-12}, {"id": 745, "seek": 306570, "start": 3065.7, "end": 3075.16, "text": " And so, I want to leave you with a final thought to mull over today.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 370, 11, 286, 528, 281, 1856, 291, 365, 257, 2572, 1194, 281, 275, 858, 670, 965, 13, 50838], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20195875329486393, "compression_ratio": 1.4277456647398843, "no_speech_prob": 2.0125784719327022e-12}, {"id": 746, "seek": 306570, "start": 3075.8599999999997, "end": 3078.3999999999996, "text": " Think about your own digital life right now.", "tokens": [50873, 6557, 466, 428, 1065, 4562, 993, 558, 586, 13, 51000], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20195875329486393, "compression_ratio": 1.4277456647398843, "no_speech_prob": 2.0125784719327022e-12}, {"id": 747, "seek": 306570, "start": 3079.06, "end": 3088.2, "text": " Your personal notes, your perfectly organized bookmark folders, those digital journals or saved articles you haven't opened in years.", "tokens": [51033, 2260, 2973, 5570, 11, 428, 6239, 9983, 1446, 5638, 31082, 11, 729, 4562, 29621, 420, 6624, 11290, 291, 2378, 380, 5625, 294, 924, 13, 51490], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20195875329486393, "compression_ratio": 1.4277456647398843, "no_speech_prob": 2.0125784719327022e-12}, {"id": 748, "seek": 308820, "start": 3088.2, "end": 3089.66, "text": " Yeah, think about them.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 519, 466, 552, 13, 50438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14337044292026097, "compression_ratio": 1.5123152709359606, "no_speech_prob": 2.3896093437336674e-12}, {"id": 749, "seek": 308820, "start": 3089.66, "end": 3104.3199999999997, "text": " If Flyxion is right, and meaning only truly exists in the paths we actively walk, what digital roads in your own mind are you letting wash away right now simply because you falsely believe the knowledge is safely stored?", "tokens": [50438, 759, 932, 4105, 307, 558, 11, 293, 3620, 787, 4908, 8198, 294, 264, 14518, 321, 13022, 1792, 11, 437, 4562, 11344, 294, 428, 1065, 1575, 366, 291, 8295, 5675, 1314, 558, 586, 2935, 570, 291, 16720, 736, 1697, 264, 3601, 307, 11750, 12187, 30, 51171], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14337044292026097, "compression_ratio": 1.5123152709359606, "no_speech_prob": 2.3896093437336674e-12}, {"id": 750, "seek": 308820, "start": 3105.7799999999997, "end": 3107.3599999999997, "text": " Keep walking the paths.", "tokens": [51244, 5527, 4494, 264, 14518, 13, 51323], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14337044292026097, "compression_ratio": 1.5123152709359606, "no_speech_prob": 2.3896093437336674e-12}, {"id": 751, "seek": 308820, "start": 3108.3199999999997, "end": 3110.16, "text": " Thanks for diving deep with us today.", "tokens": [51371, 2561, 337, 20241, 2452, 365, 505, 965, 13, 51463], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14337044292026097, "compression_ratio": 1.5123152709359606, "no_speech_prob": 2.3896093437336674e-12}], "language": "en"}
